ADR_13=_adr(id="AD-13",context="APPLICATION_OPs are identified by string names (L-layer). String identity is representation-dependent. Two deployments using different strings for the same semantic op have no shared coordinate identity.",decision="GOVERNANCE_OPS entries may declare csil_id to promote an op from L-layer to V-layer (CSIL) identity. Kernel validates collision-freedom. Deployer is responsible for semantic accuracy.",alternatives=["Auto-assign CSIL integers — requires GTI disambiguation logic in kernel (out of scope)","No op-level CSIL — coordinate shadowing remains an open attack surface for cross-deployment audits"],consequences="CSIL-S-01, CSIL-S-02. Identity cell in posture vector moves to partial for ops with declared csil_id.",bound_invariants=["CSIL-S-01","CSIL-S-02"])

ADR_14=_adr(id="AD-14",context="dimension_id = SHA-256(phase_code ‖ governor_pubkey) (‖ = U+2016, the DM-S-03 separator; see binding.canonical_dkn) is computed during kernel initialization and genesis/CSH ceremony. It does not appear in session_dkn. Future maintainers may ask why it exists if not in the chain.",decision="dimension_id is a compound identity anchor for use cases needing governor + deployment-type in one token: genesis seal verification, CSH ceremony, SuccessorLineage. session_dkn = SHA-256(mosaic_root:phase_code:session_id) is independently derivable from first principles. The two are parallel derivations, not a chain. session_dkn ordering is WHO×WHAT×WHICH (mosaic_root first).",alternatives=["dimension_id in session_dkn — double-encodes phase_code; redundant; obscures the three-layer semantic","phase_code first in session_dkn — inverts identity hierarchy; key identity should anchor derivation"],consequences="DKN-S-01. The formulation is self-describing. session_dkn can be verified from mosaic_root + phase_code + session_id alone.",bound_invariants=["DKN-S-01","CHARTER-S-01"])

ADR_15=_adr(id="AD-15",context="FGA §10 (Namespace Governance) was initially treated as largely absent in UGK. Investigation (r66) found UGK had implicitly split FGA's single namespace concept into TWO orthogonal dimensions: (1) MEMBERSHIP — which names are constitutionally valid (invariants.NAMESPACE_PHI_0, a frozenset of typed name_keys, committed via namespace.MOSAIC_ROOT_PHI_0 and enforced by decision.py NamespaceNonMember); and (2) OWNERSHIP — who may claim, allocate, delegate, revoke, invalidate, or contest names. Membership lives in invariants.py and therefore participates in law_hash: it is ALREADY CONSTITUTIONAL. Ownership-lifecycle governance did not exist.",decision="r66 realizes the OWNERSHIP lifecycle (gap #2 Phase 2a) IR-ONLY, OVER APPLICATION-LEVEL NAMES, as Tier-2 APPLICATION_OPs routed through execute(): namespace_claim and namespace_allocate are kept distinct (FGA: 'must not be collapsed'); ownership is a deterministic receipt-chain projection (NO table); conflict policy = REFUSE (fail-closed). No new invariant is added, so the frame triad is unmoved (law_hash / legend_hash / schema_hash all stable). The MEMBERSHIP namespace (NAMESPACE_PHI_0) is NOT mutated by r66 — governed mutation of the membership set is law_hash-moving and is reserved for the amendment milestone. Membership governance is credited as an existing constitutional realization in the FGA crosswalk. Ownership-lifecycle governance is recorded as a PROVISIONAL CONSTITUTIONAL CANDIDATE: whether it becomes a dedicated NS-S-* invariant family is DEFERRED to the amendment milestone (alongside the law_hash-succession work). This ADR is the durable record so the ownership layer is neither silently treated as constitutional truth nor silently demoted.",alternatives=["Add an NS-S-* invariant family now — moves law_hash; premature before the amendment milestone","Store ownership in a SQLite table — moves schema_hash (compute_schema_hash hashes every user table)","Collapse claim and allocation into one op — violates FGA §10 'must not be collapsed'","Mutate NAMESPACE_PHI_0 to host user names — conflates membership with ownership and is law_hash-moving"],consequences="Ownership lifecycle (claim→allocation→ownership + conflict-refuse) realized and proven by namespace_governance_gate; frame triad unmoved. The membership-vs-ownership distinction is now recorded in the governed registry. Phase 2b (delegation/revocation/invalidation with remediation policy) and 2c (supersession/expiration/adjudication) are deferred.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-01","CM-OP-01","EH-S-01","DM-S-01","DKN-S-01"])

ADR_16=_adr(id="AD-16",context="r67 installed the governed amendment mechanism but shipped a SINGLE genesis AmendmentRecord (ugk/genesis_amendment.json), and Proof Model B's amendment-link hard-loaded that one file. The continuity proof path was therefore effectively single-use: any second (ordinary) amendment produces a link whose baseline law leg is the r67 successor, which the genesis record cannot satisfy. The r68 Candidate-0 audit found the multi-record machinery ALREADY EXISTED — AmendmentArchive (append-only, multi-record), record_for_transition(prior, successor), the prior_successor/existing_successors lineage parameters on is_admissible, and the append-only lineage obligation already stated in AMD-S-03 condition (4). Only the wiring was missing.",decision="r68 ships a multi-record JSON ledger ugk/amendment_ledger.json as the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for shipped amendment records (the standalone genesis_amendment.json is removed), and wires Proof Model B to AmendmentArchive.record_for_transition plus the append-only lineage parameters. This is FRAME-STATIONARY substrate/proof-harness realization of existing machinery: NO new invariant, NO law_hash / legend_hash / schema_hash move; the ledger is JSON, never a SQLite table. Backward-compatible: Proof Model B falls back to the single-record genesis_amendment.json for pre-ledger candidate archives (r67), so the r66->r67 genesis link still proves. Multi-record support (per-transition selection + lineage admit/refuse) is demonstrated frame-stationary in amendment_admissibility_gate. This is NOT an amendment and NOT new constitutional content — the lineage law already lives in AMD-S-03; this ADR is the durable record of the shipped-ledger decision, not law.",alternatives=["Keep the single-record path — the mechanism stays single-use and blocks the first ordinary amendment","Store the ledger in a SQLite table — moves schema_hash (compute_schema_hash hashes every user table)","Add an AMD/NS invariant for the ledger — moves law_hash; unwarranted because the lineage obligation is already constitutional in AMD-S-03","Keep genesis_amendment.json alongside the ledger — two sources of truth, divergence risk"],consequences="The amendment mechanism is now multi-use: the first frame-moving ordinary amendment (Candidate A or B) can select its own record via record_for_transition. The proof-harness regression burden is paid once here, de-risking both A and B. Frame triad unmoved (r68 continuity is behavioral, not amendment).",bound_invariants=["AMD-S-01","AMD-S-03","CTR-S-07"])

ADR_17=_adr(id="AD-17",context="AD-15 (r66) recorded namespace OWNERSHIP governance as a PROVISIONAL constitutional candidate: the ownership lifecycle (claim/allocate distinctness, deterministic receipt-chain projection, conflict=REFUSE) was realized IR-only and proven by namespace_governance_gate, with promotion to a dedicated NS-S-* invariant family DEFERRED to the amendment milestone. The amendment mechanism was installed (r67), made multi-use (r68), and generalized (r69). r70 exercises it for its intended purpose: the first OBJECT-LEVEL constitutional amendment.",decision="r70 PROMOTES namespace ownership governance from provisional (AD-15) to CONSTITUTIONAL via the amendment mechanism, adding NS-S-01 (ownership = deterministic receipt-chain projection; no table; distinct from membership), NS-S-02 (claim/allocate distinct, must not collapse — FGA §10), and NS-S-03 (allocation conflict policy = REFUSE on same-canonical-name/different-authority; receipt conflict != namespace conflict). The three invariants ride the EXISTING namespace_governance_gate (no new gate; gate count stays 83) and are SCI-typed S-INH (genuine adjudicated constitutional obligation — NOT IR, which would launder law as mere realization; NOT S-RES, which is the un-adjudicated residue bucket). Installed as an ordinary law-leg AmendmentRecord (prior=10982c57, successor=9a858283, kind=ordinary) appended to the multi-use ledger (now three records). Frame profile: law_hash moves; legend_hash + schema_hash UNMOVED (Tier-2 uncompressed ops; no ownership table). Scope is exactly the r66 realized surface — Phase 2b/2c (delegation/revocation/invalidation, richer conflict policies) remain deferred; MEMBERSHIP (NAMESPACE_PHI_0) is not mutated.",alternatives=["Keep ownership IR / provisional — perpetuates the projection-laundering risk the codex audit flagged (realized law not recognized as law)","Type NS-S-* as IR — same laundering: constitutional obligation mislabeled as implementation realization","Type NS-S-* as S-RES — the un-adjudicated residue/declared-exclusion bucket; contradicts a deliberate promotion to law","Add a new namespace gate — unnecessary; namespace_governance_gate already proves all six properties","Promote the full ownership lifecycle (2b/2c) now — out of scope; only the r66-realized surface is adjudicated"],consequences="Namespace ownership is now constitutional law (NS-S-01/02/03), proven by namespace_governance_gate, riding the complete amendment mechanism. The audited Thread C queue is empty after r70; Thread B (capture hardening) becomes the next candidate. AD-15 is retained as the historical provisional record.",bound_invariants=["NS-S-01","NS-S-02","NS-S-03","AMD-S-03"])

ADR_18=_adr(id="AD-18",context="R2 (succession integration) was the SOLE required completion item under the robust-operational maturity bar (bar B) of the FGA roadmap reconciliation: a constitutional system that cannot rotate its constitutional signer is too brittle to be called a mature realization. SUCC-S-01 (SuccessorLineage) already provided full predecessor-signed cryptographic succession (verify_succession, load_from_package, an amendment_hash tying a rotation to an amendment record), but amendment admissibility (is_admissible) verified signatures against a SINGLE passed governor_pubkey and never consulted the succession lineage. The gap was integration, not cryptography: after a Governor key rotation, records signed by the successor key could not be admitted, and the retired key remained the only recognized authority.",decision="r71 makes amendment authority ERA-AWARE by clarifying AMD-S-03 condition (3): the authorizing key (identified by authority = SHA-256(signing pubkey)) must be the era-appropriate key authorized by the succession lineage — the genesis key K0 or a validly predecessor-signed successor — and the Ed25519 signature must verify under THAT resolved key. STRICT ERA: after a rotation only the active successor key authorizes NEW amendments, while historical records remain valid under their era key (the authorized set only grows; K0 is never removed, so old amendments are never retroactively invalidated). is_admissible gains an optional succession input plus a record_is_historical flag; with succession=None the authorized set is exactly {K0}, preserving current behavior EXACTLY (all genesis/B/A records still admit). No new cryptography (reuses SUCC-S-01 verify_succession + existing Ed25519 verify); no record-schema change; Proof Model B stays representation-agnostic (loads and passes the lineage only). Installed as an ordinary law-leg AmendmentRecord (prior=9a858283, successor=a89ec07d, kind=ordinary, invariants_added=[] — the AMD-S-03 statement modification is the law move, carried by the successor-frame-leg hash) appended to the multi-use ledger (now four records). Frame profile: law_hash moves; legend_hash + schema_hash UNMOVED. Capability proven SYNTHETICALLY in amendment_admissibility_gate (no live rotation; the installed Governor key is unchanged): a successor record admits only under a valid predecessor-signed lineage; an unlinked or forged-proof key fails closed; K0 historical records still admit; a retired K0 is refused for new amendments; succession=None is unchanged.",alternatives=["Permissive era (any authorized key may sign any record) — weaker; a compromised retired key could still sign new amendments, defeating rotation's purpose","Frame-stationary realization (no AMD-S-03 change) — would leave era-aware authority as mere substrate behavior, not law, understating the single required completion item","Add new succession crypto or a rotation table — unwarranted; SUCC-S-01 already provides the proof and schema_hash must not move","Perform a live key rotation in r71 — unnecessary and risky; the synthetic demo proves the capability without changing the installed Governor key"],consequences="Amendment authority survives Governor key rotation: the amendment system is no longer brittle to signer rotation. With r71, under bar B, UGK is a mature realization of the FGA core; all remaining work is hardening (R1 record hash-chaining, R3/R4 posture/pinning), optional (R5 build-layer refusal receipts), or future expansion (Φ composability, namespace 2b/2c). Registry stays 76 (AMD-S-03 clarified, not added); gate count stays 83 (era demo rides amendment_admissibility_gate).",bound_invariants=["AMD-S-03","SUCC-S-01","AMD-S-01"])

ADR_19=_adr(id="AD-19",context="The amendment ledger was law-hash-linked (each record cites prior/successor law_hash) and per-record Ed25519-signed, but records did not commit their PREDECESSOR record's amendment_hash. The FGA Roadmap Exhaustion Phase classified this as Thread B R1 — a law-moving record-hash-chaining capability (not a soundness blocker; the ledger was already cryptographically sound). Executed as E2 of the exhaustion phase.",decision="r73 adds an OPTIONAL prior_amendment_hash field to AmendmentRecord, committed (omit-when-empty) only by R1-and-later records, forming a tamper-evident record-hash chain that is ADDITIVE to — and never replaces — the AUTHORITATIVE law-hash lineage (dual-lineage). FORWARD-ONLY: genesis and all pre-R1 records do not carry it; their canonical bodies and amendment_hashes are byte-preserved (genesis stays 5fe68bbc; no retroactive rehashing; no reinterpretation of historical records). is_admissible gains an optional predecessor_amendment_hash input: where a record commits prior_amendment_hash it must equal the predecessor record's amendment_hash, else fail-closed; where uncommitted, the law-hash lineage check is authoritative and unchanged. AMD-S-01 (record may commit prior_amendment_hash) and AMD-S-03 condition (4) (additive record-hash lineage) are clarified -> law_hash moves a89ec07d->064f7476 as an ordinary law-leg amendment; legend + schema UNMOVED. Installed as the 5th ledger record (prior=a89ec07d, successor=064f7476, kind=ordinary, prior_amendment_hash=<r71 record 4b197df1...>). Proof Model B _amendment_link feature-detects predecessor_amendment_hash support and supplies it (forward-only; pre-R1 candidates fall back). Demonstrated: correct prior_amendment_hash admits; wrong fails closed; uncommitted pre-R1 records still admit; genesis preserved.",alternatives=["Frame-stationary substrate (no AMD-S-01/03 change) — would leave record-hash-chaining as mere behavior, not law; R1 was classified as a law-moving capability","Retroactively rehash existing records to carry prior_amendment_hash — violates no-retroactive-rehashing and would change genesis 5fe68bbc (ABORT condition)","Replace law-hash lineage with record-hash lineage — discards the authoritative lineage; dual-lineage keeps law-hash authoritative and record-hash additive","Make prior_amendment_hash mandatory — breaks backward-compat with genesis/B/A/r71 frozen records"],consequences="The amendment ledger is now a tamper-evident record-hash chain from R1 forward, additive to the authoritative law-hash lineage, with zero retroactive change. Exhaustion phase E2 complete. Registry stays 76 (AMD-S-01/03 clarified, not added); gate count stays 83 (R1 demo rides amendment_admissibility_gate). law_hash 064f7476; ledger 5 records.",bound_invariants=["AMD-S-01","AMD-S-03"])

ADR_20=_adr(id="AD-20",context="Through r76, EVERY admitted amendment moved the LAW leg; the legend and schema legs had never moved through an amendment, so the frame-general amendment machinery (AMD-S-03 condition 2, already stated frame-general) was proven only in theory for non-law legs. The amendment lineage (condition 4) was implemented LAW-HASH-keyed (existing_successors as law hashes; chain-walk by prior_law), which cannot admit a law-stationary leg move (successor_law already present; walk would loop). E5a (Roadmap Exhaustion) is the Schema-Leg Capability Validation milestone: prove continuity remains well-defined when a NON-LAW frame leg moves with law stationary.",decision="r77 generalizes the amendment lineage from successor_law_hash to the successor FRAME (frame-triple: law_hash, legend_hash, schema_hash) as the uniqueness/order key — the PRIMARY capability of E5a. is_admissible condition (4) now keys uniqueness/order on the frame triple (backward-compatible: while only law moves, frame-keying == law-keying; legacy callers passing law hashes are unchanged). A module flag _FRAME_KEYED_LINEAGE lets cross-release verifiers feature-detect it. The amendment_admissibility_gate chain-walk became FRAME-EVOLVING (lineage order; legend/schema evolve through committed leg moves; head frame must equal the live triad). Proof Model B _amendment_link feature-detects _FRAME_KEYED_LINEAGE and supplies frame-triple lineage params (forward-only). AMD-S-03 was NOT edited — its statement is already frame-general; only the implementation was lagging — so LAW and LEGEND remain STATIONARY (064f7476 / a7e2a9c9); only SCHEMA moves bcb3397f->c44bec33. The schema move is forced by a minimal disposable probe table (frame_leg_probe, one column) added via the existing safe-additive migration substrate in store.py. The E5a amendment record (6th; ordinary; prior_law==successor_law==064f7476; legend uncommitted; prior_schema=bcb3397f, successor_schema=c44bec33 committed; prior_amendment_hash=R1 record 8960453e) is the FIRST record whose successor_law==prior_law while a non-law leg moves.",alternatives=["Refresh AMD-S-03 wording to say 'frame' explicitly — would move the law leg to clarify something already stated frame-general, weakening the purity of the experiment (rejected; Governor ruling: keep law stationary)","Make the schema move ALSO move law trivially — conflates legs; violates law-stationary","Add an expires_at/TTL/clock for a richer schema feature — NONDETERMINISTIC (breaks NS-S-01 / determinism_gate); refused. Expiration collapses onto 2b revoke/invalidate (E4 ruling)","Give the probe table governance semantics — would blur E5a (capability validation) into E5b (legacy retirement); rejected — the probe is explicitly a DISPOSABLE validation artifact"],consequences="The frame-general amendment machinery is now DEMONSTRATED (not merely asserted) on every frame-leg class that exists: law (r67-r73), and schema (r77). Constitutional continuity is proven well-defined when a non-law leg moves with law stationary, through path=amendment. The probe table (frame_leg_probe) has NO governance semantics and exists solely to validate non-law-leg constitutional transition machinery; E5b may remove it (another schema-leg move). law_hash 064f7476 and legend_hash a7e2a9c9 UNMOVED; schema_hash bcb3397f->c44bec33; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 6 records; registry 76; gates 83 (E5a demo rides amendment_admissibility_gate). Forward-only record-hash chaining preserved.",bound_invariants=["AMD-S-01","AMD-S-03","NS-S-01"])

ADR_21=_adr(id="AD-21",context="r77 PROVED the schema-leg amendment machinery (capability validation via a disposable probe table; AD-20). E5b Tier 1 (r78) additively migrated production APIs to the M2 binding surface; Tier 2 (r79) re-anchored five conformance witnesses onto M2 while RETAINING the legacy CHC envelope transitionally. The legacy substrate — Receipt fields state_hash/prior_receipt_hash/semantic_hash, the receipt_hash @property, three SQL columns, and the legacy semantic_hash receipt chain (stream_hash/verify_stream_hash recompute) — remained as superseded-but-present constitutional substrate. E5b Tier 3 (r80) retires it.",decision="r80 is the FIRST PRODUCTION USE of the proven schema-leg amendment mechanism to REMOVE superseded constitutional substrate (vs r77 which PROVED the mechanism on a disposable probe). One coordinated schema-leg amendment: drops the three SQL columns + Receipt fields + the receipt_hash property + the legacy chain machinery; empties LEGACY_COMPAT_RECEIPT_FIELDS and LEGACY_ONLY_GATES; re-anchors verify_stream_hash()/stream_hash() and _verify_segment/last_valid_frontier from the retired semantic_hash recompute to the M2 h_r chain (parent_h_r->h_r linkage). broker.submit and GovResult.receipt_hash inherit M2 automatically via stream_hash(). Schema moves c44bec33->7ef925e0 through path=amendment; LAW 064f7476 and LEGEND a7e2a9c9 STATIONARY. The 7th ledger record (ordinary; prior_law==successor_law==064f7476; legend uncommitted; prior_schema=c44bec33, successor_schema=7ef925e0; prior_amendment_hash=59e3ef9e E5a) is the SECOND record whose successor_law==prior_law while a non-law leg moves. Dependency-discovered retirement consumers (binding_gate, audit.py, headless_runner, persistence_gate, nonretroactivity_gate, recovery_gate) re-anchored to M2 as necessary completion surface.",alternatives=["Split RT-3i (drop columns) from the verify_stream_hash/broker re-anchor — REJECTED: once semantic_hash is dropped the legacy verifiers/broker output have no coherent meaning; the re-anchor is a dependency-complete consequence of the drop, not separable work","Keep the legacy fields as dead/unread columns — REJECTED: produces an internally inconsistent retirement (live readers would dangle)","Re-anchor verify_stream_hash by replaying the full M2 binding pipeline per receipt (faithful body-recompute) — REJECTED: fragile and determinism-risky; instead verify_stream_hash proves M2 chain integrity (linkage) and binding_gate proves body<->H_r tamper-evidence (recompute), preserving the combined property at lower risk"],consequences="The legacy CHC envelope is RETIRED IN PRODUCTION — no longer merely superseded in theory. Schema-leg amendments are now DEMONSTRATED for real constitutional substrate evolution (r77 proved the machinery; r80 uses it to delete superseded substrate). LAW 064f7476 and LEGEND a7e2a9c9 UNMOVED; schema_hash c44bec33->7ef925e0; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 7 records; registry 76; gates 83 (all re-anchored to M2; no roster change). verify_stream_hash/stream_hash anchored on the M2 h_r chain; NO remaining runtime consumers of the retired fields. Closes E5b (Tier 1+2+3) — the longest-running migration thread in the roadmap.",bound_invariants=["AMD-S-01","AMD-S-03","PERSIST-S-01","DM-S-01"])

ADR_22=_adr(id="AD-22",context="The frame is a triple (law_hash, legend_hash, schema_hash). Through r80 only TWO of the three legs had been INDEPENDENTLY exercised through an amendment: the LAW leg (r67-r73) and the SCHEMA leg (r77 capability-validation + r80 production-retirement). The LEGEND leg used the SAME proven frame-general machinery (AMD-S-03 already frame-general; frame-keyed lineage from AD-20) but had never itself moved through an admitted amendment — its capability was proven only by analogy to the other legs. E6 (LEG-EX, Roadmap Exhaustion) is the final frame-leg exercise: move the legend leg, law+schema stationary, and prove continuity through the same path=amendment machinery, closing the constitutional capability matrix.",decision="r81 moves the LEGEND leg via the smallest possible legend-leg amendment: a single meta-tier CSIL legend entry (csil_id 6006, render 'LEG-EX', tier 'meta', NO governance semantics — not wired into FIELD_COMPRESS_MAPS or any op/intent/jurisdiction/confidence map). This is the legend analog of E5a's disposable schema probe table. LEGEND_HASH moves a7e2a9c9->db3c177d; LAW 064f7476 and SCHEMA 7ef925e0 STATIONARY. The 8th ledger record (ordinary; prior_law==successor_law==064f7476; legend COMMITTED a7e2a9c9->db3c177d; schema uncommitted/stationary; prior_amendment_hash=2ae30538 r80; amendment_hash 1f1f8ed1) is the FIRST record to commit a legend-leg move. Live legend pins cascaded a7e2a9c9->db3c177d: a1_conservativity_gate BASELINE_SURFACE, tools/b1_conformance + b2_conformance EXPECTED_LEGEND, RELEASE.txt. The PMB continuity verifier's record + predecessor selection generalized to CARRY-AWARE frame lineage (the selection-side completion of AD-20: a stationary leg is uncommitted/carried in the predecessor, so committed-only matching is insufficient; carry-aware frame matching selects the correct record + immediate predecessor for any leg move).",alternatives=["Modify an existing legend entry to force the hash move — REJECTED: perturbs live projection vocabulary semantics; the meta marker is non-semantic and disposable-clean","Move the legend by altering a wired vocab/op CSIL entry — REJECTED: would change governance-relevant CSIL mappings (compression/render), conflating the leg exercise with a semantic change","Skip LEG-EX as 'already proven by the schema leg via shared machinery' — REJECTED (Governor ruling): the legend leg must be INDEPENDENTLY exercised to CLOSE the capability matrix, not merely asserted by analogy; an unexercised path is an unproven path"],consequences="The constitutional capability matrix is CLOSED: every frame leg — LAW, SCHEMA, LEGEND — is now DEMONSTRATED through an admitted path=amendment, not merely asserted frame-general. LAW 064f7476 and SCHEMA 7ef925e0 UNMOVED; LEGEND a7e2a9c9->db3c177d; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 8 records; registry 76; gates 83; LEGEND entries 100->101 (meta marker). Record-hash chain continues forward-only (1f1f8ed1). E6 complete — the last unexercised constitutional path is now exercised.",bound_invariants=["AMD-S-01","AMD-S-03","LEGEND-S-01"])
ADR_23=_adr(id="AD-23",context="A red-team review (~350 findings) of v0.1.0 did not surface a failed architecture but a recurring TRUST-BOUNDARY pattern: the system trusts inputs, archives, manifests, receipts, and context before proving them, and several verifiers claim more than they prove. The dominant principle is THE CLAIM IS LARGER THAN THE PROOF. This was CONFIRMED in code: store.verify_stream_hash() (and `ugk verify`) verify only M2 chain LINKAGE (parent_h_r->h_r, ordering, no-truncation, no-relink) and pass after RECEIPT-BODY tampering (finding #27). AD-21 had relied on binding_gate for body<->H_r tamper-evidence, but binding_gate proves the COMMITMENT FUNCTION round-trips on a FIXTURE; it does NOT protect a LIVE store on the runtime/CLI path, leaving CHC-S-03 (altering a commitment is detectable) enforced only at the fixture, not at the boundary users actually call.",decision="Establish the Integrity Enforcement Layer (IEL) and ratify its Phase-0 VOCABULARY (module ugk/integrity/): VerificationLevel {LINKAGE, BODY, CONTEXT, IDENTITY, QUORUM, FULLY_VERIFIED} — every verifier must DECLARE which guarantee it established, FULLY_VERIFIED being the release bar — and the CorruptionKind taxonomy {missing, corrupt, malformed, forged, stale, orphaned, ambiguous, unverified} (Invariant B: corrupt is never downgraded to missing). Ratify five project-wide integrity invariants as the IEL program: (A) no mutation before all refusal conditions are known; (B) corrupt != missing, corrupt fails closed; (C) every verifier states what it verified; (D) read-only operations never mutate state; (E) every multi-step write is atomic. PILOT finding #27 as the first stone: add store.verify_receipt_bodies() which recomputes h_s = H_s(op, parameters) per stored receipt and compares to the stored h_s — a PURE, deterministic re-derivation from two stored fields (the SAFE subset; NOT the full H_c/H_m/H_j pipeline-replay AD-21 rejected as fragile/determinism-risky); keep verify_stream_hash() honestly LINKAGE-only (documented as such); make `ugk verify` require LINKAGE+BODY and FAIL CLOSED on body mismatch; and add body_integrity_gate (adversarial: tamper a stored receipt body, assert BODY verification FAILS while LINKAGE still passes) so the invariant is GATED, not merely coded. Phase 0 is FRAME-STATIONARY: no registry invariant is added, so law_hash/legend_hash/schema_hash are UNMOVED and no amendment is required; the formal IEL registry invariant(s) and subsystem migration onto IEL primitives are DEFERRED to Phase 1+ (where adding a law-bound invariant will be a proper law-leg amendment).",alternatives=["Replay the full M2 binding pipeline (H_c/H_m/H_j) inside verify_stream_hash — REJECTED (re-affirming AD-21): fragile and determinism-risky; the pilot uses only the pure H_s(op,parameters) subset as a SEPARATE verifier, which provably round-trips on clean receipts","Add a law-moving IEL registry invariant now — PREMATURE: Phase 0 ratifies the vocabulary and program documentarily (ADR); binding a formal invariant via amendment belongs to Phase 1 once the primitives are built and gated","Fix #27 ad-hoc without the shared vocabulary — REJECTED: the findings are systemic (one pattern across subsystems); a one-off fix misses the architectural point of shared enforcement","Make `ugk verify` tolerate body mismatch as a warning — REJECTED: violates Invariant B (corrupt must fail closed) and the hardening mandate (no silent pass on tampering)"],consequences="The VerificationLevel + CorruptionKind vocabulary is ratified and the IEL program established. Finding #27 is CLOSED on the runtime path: `ugk verify` now recomputes receipt bodies and fails closed on body tampering, extending CHC-S-03 enforcement from the binding_gate fixture to the live store. THE CLAIM IS LARGER THAN THE PROOF is recorded as a project principle. Phase 0 is frame-stationary: law_hash 064f7476 / legend_hash db3c177d / schema_hash 7ef925e0 UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 8 records; registry 76 (no formal IEL invariant yet — deferred to Phase 1). gates 83->84 (body_integrity_gate added). verify_stream_hash remains honestly LINKAGE-only; verify_receipt_bodies provides BODY; FULLY_VERIFIED composition and migration of subsystems onto IEL primitives are the Phase 1+ program.",bound_invariants=["CHC-S-01","CHC-S-03","DM-S-01","DM-S-03"])
ADR_24=_adr(id="AD-24",context="AD-23 established the IEL and ratified the VERIFICATION-side vocabulary (VerificationLevel/CorruptionKind) plus the #27 BODY pilot, explicitly DEFERRING the remaining core primitives, the formal IEL registry invariant, and subsystem migration to Phase 1. Phase 0 covered only verification (reading); the MUTATION side (writing) — Invariant A (no mutation before validation completes) and Invariant E (multi-step writes are atomic) — had no IEL primitive. Findings cluster heavily here: mutation-before-validation (e.g. gate_admit/receipt writes before parameter/authority/warrant checks) and transactionality gaps (e.g. schema migration mutating then failing to write its receipt).",decision="Phase 1 increment 1 builds the first MUTATION-side IEL primitives (module ugk/integrity/): ValidationResult (Invariant-A vocabulary: a preflight outcome carrying ok + a CorruptionKind classification) and MutationTransaction, which COUPLES A and E — it REFUSES to open (raises MutationRefused; body never runs; zero writes) unless the supplied ValidationResult is ok (A), and wraps the body in a single SQLite SAVEPOINT so any mid-body exception ROLLS BACK the entire block while a clean block commits (E); exceptions are never suppressed. SAVEPOINT (not BEGIN/COMMIT) is used so the wrapper is correct regardless of the connection isolation_level and is nestable. Enforced by mutation_atomicity_gate (adversarial: invalid validation writes nothing; mid-body exception leaves no partial state; clean block commits; exceptions propagate). FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: new ugk/integrity modules + one gate; NO registry invariant added, so law_hash/legend_hash/schema_hash are UNMOVED and no amendment is required. The primitive is PRODUCTION-READY but DELIBERATELY NOT YET WIRED into the kernel/store — wiring subsystems onto it is the deferred, finding-driven Phase 1 migration step. The formal IEL registry invariant (a law-moving amendment) and the remaining primitives (ReadOnlyGuard, IntegrityContext, ReceiptContextResolver) remain DEFERRED to subsequent Phase 1 increments, each to be separately authorized.",alternatives=["BEGIN/COMMIT instead of SAVEPOINT — REJECTED: fragile w.r.t. Python sqlite3 isolation_level auto-transaction behavior and not nestable; SAVEPOINT is correct regardless and composes","Wire MutationTransaction into the kernel/store now — REJECTED: migration is a separate finding-driven phase requiring per-subsystem evidence; the IEL doctrine is build+gate the primitive first, then migrate one subsystem at a time","Make MutationTransaction suppress exceptions or auto-retry — REJECTED: hides failures; fail-closed and propagate","Let MutationTransaction take a bool instead of a ValidationResult — REJECTED: loses the CorruptionKind classification and the explicit Invariant-A coupling"],consequences="The IEL gains its first MUTATION-side enforcement primitive (Invariants A+E), complementing the Phase-0 verification side (BODY level). frame-stationary: law_hash 064f7476 / legend_hash db3c177d / schema_hash 7ef925e0 UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 8 records; registry 76 (no formal IEL invariant yet — still deferred); gates 84->85 (mutation_atomicity_gate added). MutationTransaction is built and gated but unwired; ReadOnlyGuard, IntegrityContext, ReceiptContextResolver, the formal IEL invariant (amendment), and subsystem migration remain the deferred Phase 1 program.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-02","UL-S-02","PERSIST-S-01","DM-S-01"])
ADR_25=_adr(id="AD-25",context="AD-23 ratified the IEL verification vocabulary; AD-24 added the first mutation-side primitives (ValidationResult + MutationTransaction, Invariants A+E). The IEL doctrine names a SMALLEST HARD CORE of primitives to build (then migrate subsystems onto): verification levels, validation, atomic mutation, read-only guard, and receipt-time context. Two pieces remained: read-only enforcement (Invariant D: read-only ops never mutate; e.g. ugk attest creates a DB on a read path) and receipt-time context (context drift: verification using live authority/policy/epoch/legend rather than the frame the receipt committed).",decision="Phase 1 increment 2 COMPLETES the IEL smallest-hard-core spine with three additive primitives (ugk/integrity/): (1) ReadOnlyGuard (Invariant D), fail-closed + detection-based: require_existing refuses a read-only op against a non-existent on-disk DB (prevents accidental creation) and the context manager raises if a guarded block creates or destroys a DB; :memory:/None are ephemeral-exempt. A deeper PREVENTION variant via a read-only sqlite connection (mode=ro) is a NOTED follow-on; v1 makes the read-path-mutation class loud + fail-closed without grundnorm-store surgery. (2) ReceiptContextResolver + ReceiptContext: reconstructs the RECEIPT-TIME frame (law_hash/legend_hash/timestamp) from the receipt's own committed fields, not live state, and reports drift when a receipt predates an amendment. (3) IntegrityContext: a read-only bundle of the live frame triad + genesis anchor + required VerificationLevel bar. Gated by readonly_guard_gate and receipt_context_gate. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: new ugk/integrity modules + two gates; NO registry invariant added, so law/legend/schema UNMOVED and no amendment. With AD-25 the IEL core primitive set is COMPLETE; the formal IEL registry invariant (law-moving amendment) and subsystem migration are the remaining Phase 1 steps.",alternatives=["Implement ReadOnlyGuard as a prevention-mode read-only store (sqlite mode=ro, skipping schema setup) now: DEFERRED - grundnorm-store surgery with several schema-skip points + a new store semantic; the detection/fail-closed guard delivers Invariant D safely first.","Skip ReceiptContextResolver as premature: REJECTED - context drift is a named finding class and receipts already commit their frame, so receipt-time binding is cheap + correct now.","Source the full live frame inside IntegrityContext by reading invariants.py at runtime: AVOIDED - fragile under packaging; IntegrityContext is a caller-populated bundle.","Bundle all three into existing modules: REJECTED - separate small modules keep the spine legible and individually gated."],consequences="The IEL smallest-hard-core primitive spine is COMPLETE and each primitive is adversarially gated. frame-stationary: law_hash 064f7476 / legend_hash db3c177d / schema_hash 7ef925e0 UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 8 records; registry 76 (no formal IEL invariant yet); gates 85->87 (readonly_guard_gate + receipt_context_gate). All IEL primitives are built+gated but the mutation/read-only/context primitives remain UNWIRED (migration deferred). The formal IEL registry invariant via amendment (law-moving) is the immediate next action, then subsystem migration of the highest-severity findings.",bound_invariants=["AUDIT-S-01","DM-S-03","DM-S-01"])
ADR_26=_adr(id="AD-26",context="AD-23/24/25 built and adversarially gated the IEL smallest-hard-core primitive spine (verification levels, validation, atomic mutation, read-only guard, receipt-time context). The body-verifier (#27) closure - store.verify_receipt_bodies recomputing h_s per committed receipt, store.verify_chain composing LINKAGE+BODY, and ugk verify requiring LINKAGE+BODY (fail-closed on body tamper) - is WIRED into production. The remaining Phase 1 step was to formalize the ENFORCED IEL property as constitutional law via a law-moving amendment.",decision="r91 formalizes the runtime body-integrity property as registry invariant IEL-S-01 (SCI-typed IR, consistent with its sibling CHC-S-03; gate=body_integrity_gate), added via an ORDINARY law-leg AmendmentRecord. LAW MOVES 064f7476e01f->5f6daa36b973; legend_hash db3c177d + schema_hash 7ef925e0 UNMOVED (uncommitted legs, verified unchanged by is_admissible). Ledger record #9: prior_law=064f7476, successor_law=5f6daa36, invariants_added=[IEL-S-01], prior_amendment_hash=1f1f8ed1 (r81 record), authority=ad5ba7c5 (fixture governor mosaic), Ed25519-signed by the fixture governor key, amendment_hash=5e23078928a4. ONLY the enforced property is formalized: IEL-S-01 states receipt-body integrity is runtime-verifiable AND enforced (ugk verify fails closed CORRUPT on body tamper, on the runtime/CLI path not merely a fixture). The IEL mutation-side (A/E), read-only (D), and context primitives remain gated-but-UNWIRED into subsystems, so they are DELIBERATELY NOT yet formal invariants - formalizing them would claim enforcement no production path provides (claim > proof). Live-law pins cascaded 064f7476->5f6daa36 across b1/b2/b3/b4a/b5a + schema_hash + grbsa/verifier + g6 + phase6 + a1_conservativity_gate(law_hash, which backs a live 'law_hash unmoved' check) + RELEASE.txt; a1's frozen M2.3 commitment SURFACE elements (id_c_*, domains_hash) and m2_vectors_runner LH remain FROZEN at 064f7476 (M2 h_r is empirically law-insensitive; PASS unchanged post-move); continuity_surfaces.json + amendment_ledger.json retain 064f7476 as historical facts.",alternatives=["Formalize all IEL primitives (A/E/D/context) as invariants now: REJECTED - those primitives are gated but UNWIRED into subsystems; formalizing them as law would claim enforcement that exists on no production path (claim exceeds proof).","Regenerate the frozen a1/m2 conservativity baselines to the new law: REJECTED - M2 h_r is law-insensitive and both gates PASS unchanged; regenerating golden vectors that already pass is unnecessary churn and risk (minimal-surgical).","Keep IEL-S-01 as a gate with no registry invariant (no law move): REJECTED - the goal is to make the enforced integrity property CONSTITUTIONAL, which requires a registry invariant + amendment.","Type IEL-S-01 as S-INH (constitutional obligation): AVOIDED - its sibling CHC-S-03 is IR; IR is the honest, consistent classification (the verifier REALIZES runtime body detection)."],consequences="The IEL's enforced body-integrity property is now constitutional law. law_hash 064f7476->5f6daa36; legend db3c177d + schema 7ef925e0 unmoved; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 8->9 records; registry 76->77 (IEL-S-01); gates stay 87 (no new gate - IEL-S-01 binds the existing body_integrity_gate). FIRST law move since r73. The r90->r91 continuity link is an AMENDMENT link (frame moves with an admitted record), not behavioral. Subsystem migration (wiring the unwired primitives into the highest-severity findings, with regression gates) is the remaining IEL-establishment step.",bound_invariants=["IEL-S-01","CHC-S-03","AMD-S-01","AMD-S-03"])
ADR_27=_adr(id="AD-27",context="The IEL spine is built + gated (r88-r90) and formalized as constitutional law (r91, IEL-S-01). The remaining IEL-establishment step is to DEMONSTRATE subsystem migration: route a real subsystem through an IEL primitive, with an adversarial regression gate, proving no regression. The migrate_schema (storage-frame governed) cluster carries input-validation findings #60 (migrate_schema(None,...) crashes with a raw TypeError) and #59 (migrate_schema([]) writes a spurious migration receipt for a no-op), plus the atomicity finding #30 (mutate-then-fail-receipt).",decision="r92 performs the FIRST IEL subsystem migration: ValidationResult (Invariant A, validate-before-mutate) is wired into migrate_schema as a preflight gate, closing #60 (None -> clean ValueError refusal, not a raw TypeError) and #59 (empty -> refused with NO spurious receipt; no-op migrations are not receipted). Valid migrations still apply + are receipted (no regression); the pre-existing empty-intent and unsafe-statement refusals are preserved (governance not weakened). Proven by migrate_schema_validation_gate (adversarial: None refused cleanly, empty refused with no receipt, valid still applies+receipted, empty-intent still refused). FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: this is realization strengthening migrate_schema's EXISTING storage-frame governance, NOT a new law move or invariant; law 5f6daa36 / legend db3c177d / schema 7ef925e0 UNMOVED. MutationTransaction (Invariant E) is DELIBERATELY NOT wired into migrate_schema's atomicity gap (#30): store.write() commits internally, so a SAVEPOINT-based MutationTransaction cannot compose without first refactoring write() to a deferred-commit path (the SAVEPOINT-nesting dependency noted in AD-24). ReadOnlyGuard (Invariant D) wiring into ugk attest (#54) requires a read-only kernel/store path (no open_session receipt; the kernel also requires founding to exercise). Both are tracked follow-ons. r92 DEMONSTRATES the migration pattern with the primitive that composes cleanly here (ValidationResult) and HONESTLY reports the architectural dependencies (write() internal commit; read-only store path) that make full migration a follow-on campaign, not a one-shot.",alternatives=["Wire MutationTransaction into migrate_schema for #30 now: REJECTED - store.write() commits internally; a SAVEPOINT wrapper would be defeated by that commit; forcing it would be clever, not correct (the deferred-commit write refactor is a separate, higher-risk change).","Migrate the execute() validate-before-mutate cluster (#22/#33/#34/#35/#55) in this release: DEFERRED - execute() is the central governance path; a separately-gated migration is prudent (minimal-surgical, fail-closed).","Do a non-primitive inline fix for #59/#60 without ValidationResult: REJECTED - the goal is to DEMONSTRATE the IEL primitives wired; ValidationResult is the Invariant-A preflight primitive and the honest vehicle.","Remove the premature commit in migrate_schema to tighten #30 atomicity: NOT DONE in r92 - it demonstrates no primitive and changes grundnorm transaction semantics; tracked with the deferred-commit-write follow-on."],consequences="First IEL subsystem migration COMPLETE: ValidationResult is wired into a production subsystem (migrate_schema), closing #59 + #60 with an adversarial regression gate and no behavioral regression for valid use. The IEL is now ESTABLISHED on all three axes: (1) smallest-hard-core primitive spine built + gated (r88-r90); (2) formalized as constitutional law (r91, IEL-S-01); (3) demonstrated subsystem migration (r92). frame-stationary: law 5f6daa36 / legend db3c177d / schema 7ef925e0 unmoved; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 9 records; registry 77; gates 87->88 (migrate_schema_validation_gate). Remaining (tracked follow-on campaign): execute() validate-before-mutate cluster; atomicity #30/#63/#123 via a deferred-commit write path + MutationTransaction; attest #54 via a read-only kernel path + ReadOnlyGuard; and the broader ~350-finding remediation.",bound_invariants=["PERSIST-S-01","DM-S-01","GK-S-02"])
ADR_28=_adr(id="AD-28",context="An external review of r92 found IEL-S-01's BODY claim OVERSTATED (the claim was larger than the proof, INSIDE the enacted constitutional law): store.verify_receipt_bodies recomputed only h_s = H_s(op,parameters), so 20 committed fields (authority, intent, jurisdiction, confidence, timestamp, failed, session_dkn, law_hash, legend_hash, warrant_id, intent_ref, h_c, h_m, h_j, mode, version, id_c_s/c/m/j) could be rewritten post-commit and still pass verify_chain. The review also found from_checkpoint failing OPEN (a missing checkpoint returned ok, violating IEL Invariant B: missing != verified). Investigation confirmed both, and confirmed WHY full-body recompute is not a verifier-only change: the merkle leaves h_c/h_j bind inputs derived from MUTABLE LIVE STATE not stored on the receipt (authority-graph path, policy lookup, computed capabilities, a Governor-signed freshness epoch, key-registry lookup), so recomputing them from stored data risks FALSE POSITIVES when that state changes (the fragility AD-21 rejected). Only h_s and h_m recompute robustly from stored fields.",decision="r93 makes BODY genuinely full-body via a SCHEMA move plus a LAW move (a multi-leg amendment, the gravest change to date). SCHEMA leg: each receipt gains h_body = sha256(UGK-BODY-v1 || canonical(every committed field except h_body)), computed at write PURELY from the canonical (pre-compression) values; schema_hash moves 7ef925e0 -> a49e520e (its first move since r80). store.verify_receipt_bodies now recomputes h_body per receipt from stored data and compares, detecting tampering of ANY committed field, with an h_body-era guard that fails closed if a later receipt's commitment is stripped; verify_chain composes LINKAGE + full BODY. LAW leg: IEL-S-01's statement is amended to the truthful full-body claim and rebound from body_integrity_gate to receipt_commitment_integrity_gate (the new adversarial gate that tampers EVERY committed field and a clean-chain anti-false-positive check); law_hash moves 5f6daa36 -> da88cb41. The from_checkpoint fail-open (#2) is fixed on BOTH verify_stream_hash and verify_receipt_bodies (missing checkpoint -> fail closed). h_body is the verification-grade WHOLE-body commitment (a flat hash over stored values), deliberately DISTINCT from the merkle root h_r (whose leaves bind live-derived context); it does not replace h_r (inclusion proofs) and adds no live-state dependency, so clean receipts never false-positive (verified). The multi-leg amendment (record e2debfea) commits BOTH moved legs (law + schema) with legend db3c177d stationary; is_admissible ADMITTED it (ordinary) against both frames; ledger 9 -> 10 records.",alternatives=["Path 2 - narrow IEL-S-01 to claim only what a verifier-only change proves ({op,parameters,intent,intent_ref,legend_hash}, 5 fields): REJECTED by the Governor in favor of making BODY true. Path 2 would close the overclaim by shrinking the claim; Path 1 closes it by making the claim accurate.","Recompute h_c/h_j from re-derived live state (authority graph, policy, capabilities, freshness, key registry) to cover all fields without a schema change: REJECTED - re-derivation matches only while live state is unchanged; after any succession/policy/epoch change it would report FALSE-POSITIVE tampering on clean receipts. A body verifier that false-positives is worse than the gap (AD-21).","Bind all fields into the existing merkle h_r instead of a new column: REJECTED - h_r's leaf inputs are not all stored and the live-derived ones cannot be robustly recomputed; changing the leaf set is a deeper binding change with the same recompute problem. A flat h_body over stored values is the minimal verification-grade commitment.","Keep h_body optional / skip it when empty without an era guard: REJECTED - an attacker could strip h_body to downgrade a full-body receipt to h_s-only. The h_body-era guard fails closed once any receipt in the chain carries a commitment.","Ship full-body as a frame-stationary realization change (no amendment): REJECTED - adding a committed column moves schema_hash and changing IEL-S-01's statement moves law_hash; both are frame legs and MUST be carried by an admitted amendment (no silent semantics)."],consequences="BODY now genuinely means the WHOLE stored receipt body is intact: receipt_commitment_integrity_gate tampers every committed field and verify_chain fails closed on each; clean chains still verify (no false positives). The external review's two integrity findings are CLOSED: #1 (body claim larger than proof) by making the claim true via h_body; #2 (from_checkpoint fail-open) by failing closed on a missing checkpoint. MULTI-LEG frame move: law 5f6daa36 -> da88cb41 AND schema 7ef925e0 -> a49e520e, legend db3c177d stationary; amendment record e2debfea admitted; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 9 -> 10; registry 77 (IEL-S-01 statement amended, not added/removed); gates 88 -> 89 (receipt_commitment_integrity_gate). Law + schema pins cascaded across probes/gates (a1 baseline, g6 law-unmoved, phase6, b1/b2/b3/b4a/b5a, schema_hash + grbsa verifier, RELEASE.txt; store EXPECTED_SCHEMA_HASH); m2 vector surfaces stay frozen (law-insensitive). Remaining review items are wiring follow-ons, not integrity overclaims: #3 ReadOnlyGuard into ugk verify/attest (needs a read-only kernel path) and #4/#30 MutationTransaction atomicity (needs the deferred-commit write refactor). The IEL claim and its proof are now equal in scope.",bound_invariants=["IEL-S-01","CHC-S-03","AMD-S-01","AMD-S-03"])
ADR_29=_adr(id="AD-29",context="An external review of r93 found a DOWNGRADE attack on the full-body verifier. r93 detected tampering while h_body was present, but its h_body-era guard caught only the present-then-absent TRANSITION, not WHOLESALE absence: stripping h_body from EVERY receipt (UPDATE receipts SET h_body='') made verify_receipt_bodies fall back to h_s-only and verify_chain still reported BODY, so a tampered non-h_s field (e.g. authority='mallory') passed undetected. IEL-S-01's claim (detects tampering of ANY committed field) was therefore again slightly LARGER than the proof - the second such finding (the first, AD-28, closed the h_s-only gap; this closes the strip-all downgrade). Both were found by external adversarial review, not by the in-tree gate, which had not exercised the strip-all class.",decision="r94 makes h_body MANDATORY. store.verify_receipt_bodies now requires a non-empty, correctly recomputing h_body on EVERY verified receipt: a missing or stripped h_body - even if stripped from every receipt wholesale - does NOT establish BODY (no downgrade to h_s-only). The insufficient era guard (transition-only) is REPLACED by this presence requirement, so verify_chain fails closed (CorruptionKind.CORRUPT, level < BODY) on a stripped/absent h_body, and ugk verify (which requires BODY) fails on any such chain. IEL-S-01's statement is corrected to state the mandatory rule and the no-downgrade property explicitly. receipt_commitment_integrity_gate gains two downgrade cases: strip-all + tamper-a-non-h_s-field must fail closed, and strip-all alone must be < BODY. This is a single-leg LAW move (statement correction only): law_hash da88cb41 -> a3992e45; schema a49e520e and legend db3c177d STATIONARY (the h_body column already exists from r93); amendment record #11 (291f511c) commits the law leg with schema+legend uncommitted; is_admissible ADMITTED it (ordinary). Clean r94 chains still verify with no false positive (verified); all receipts in this system carry h_body because store.write() always sets it (migrate_schema, epoch seal/prune included), so the mandatory rule never breaks a legitimate chain.",alternatives=["Option B - add a LEGACY_BODY VerificationLevel < BODY so a hypothetical migrated pre-r93 DB is reported honestly rather than failed: NOT CHOSEN by the Governor. This system has NO legacy receipts (write() has always set h_body), so an empty h_body under the h_body schema is necessarily anomalous; hard-fail is correct here and avoids machinery for a non-existent case. LEGACY_BODY can be added later if pre-r93 stores ever need support.","Keep the r93 era guard (transition-only): REJECTED - it provably misses wholesale absence (strip every h_body), the exact downgrade the review demonstrated.","Narrow IEL-S-01 to claim only 'detects tampering while h_body is present': REJECTED - that closes the overclaim by shrinking the claim; the discipline (as in AD-28) is to make the claim TRUE by strengthening the verifier.","Treat the fix as frame-stationary realization (no amendment): REJECTED - IEL-S-01's statement asserted the era guard rejects a stripped commitment, which is FALSE for strip-all; correcting a false statement in the law is a law move (no silent semantics)."],consequences="The strip-all downgrade is CLOSED: BODY now requires h_body on every receipt; verify_chain fails closed on any stripped/absent commitment; the gate exercises the downgrade class directly. The external review's downgrade finding is closed. Single-leg LAW move: law da88cb41 -> a3992e45; schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d stationary; amendment record #11 (291f511c, prior_amendment_hash e2debfea) ADMITTED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 10 -> 11; registry 77 (IEL-S-01 statement amended, not added/removed); ADRs through AD-29; gates 89 (downgrade cases added to the existing receipt_commitment_integrity_gate, not a new gate). Law pin cascaded across a1 baseline, g6 law-unmoved, phase6, b1/b2/b3/b4a/b5a, schema_hash + grbsa verifier, RELEASE.txt; m2 vector surfaces frozen (law-insensitive). META-PATTERN (recorded honestly): two successive external reviews found two successive overclaims in IEL-S-01 (h_s-only; strip-all downgrade), both fixed by making the claim true rather than narrowing it. The in-tree gate now covers per-field tampering AND the downgrade; 'fully closed' should still be qualified by the attack classes actually exercised. Remaining review items are wiring follow-ons, not integrity overclaims: #3 ReadOnlyGuard into ugk verify/attest (read path still creates ugk.db) and #4/#30 MutationTransaction atomicity (deferred-commit write refactor).",bound_invariants=["IEL-S-01","CHC-S-03","AMD-S-01","AMD-S-03"])

ADR_30=_adr(id="AD-30",context="r94 closed the BODY downgrade. The remaining external-review item #3 was an IEL Invariant D violation: the read-only commands (ugk verify/status/attest) bootstrapped state - verify/status constructed a normal UGKReceiptStore (creating EMPTY_DIR/ugk.db) and attest went through _make_kernel (ceremony + open_session, writing receipts) - so a read path silently CREATED a database and emitted session receipts. AD-25 had built ReadOnlyGuard (detection/fail-closed: require_existing + a create/destroy-detecting context manager) and EXPLICITLY deferred the deeper PREVENTION variant (a read-only sqlite mode=ro connection + a read-only kernel path) as a follow-on. The Governor authorized r95 to wire Invariant D as a production SUBSTRATE (not a narrow CLI workaround), covering verify/status/attest uniformly, plus a mint-time archive-hygiene assertion.",decision="r95 realizes the IEL Invariant D read-only SUBSTRATE - the prevention variant AD-25 deferred - and wires all three read commands onto it. (1) STORE: UGKReceiptStore(read_only=True) opens a TRUE read-only connection via sqlite mode=ro (ReadOnlyGuard.require_existing fails closed if the on-disk DB is absent; no PRAGMA/CREATE/migrate are issued; the connection itself cannot create the file or write); write() and migrate_schema fail closed (ReadOnlyViolation) on a read-only store. (2) KERNEL: GovernanceKernel.hydrate_readonly() reconstructs ACTIVE state from an existing founded deployment by PURE COMPUTE (law_hash/mosaic_root/dimension_id/manifest_hash/legend_hash) + LOAD-ONLY CSH (reads genesis ValidatorSet/LaunchIC and computes finality/quorum in memory), with NO seal_legend, NO session_open, NO receipts; _activate_csh(read_only=True) fails closed (quorum unachieved) rather than CREATING CSH artifacts when founded artifacts are absent. (3) CLI: verify/status bind the mode=ro store, attest binds the mode=ro store + the hydrate-only kernel, all inside a ReadOnlyGuard context, returning a structured fail-closed result (error=state_absent_or_unreadable, exit 2) on absent/unreadable state. Proven by readonly_invariant_gate (adversarial, subprocess-orchestrated because GOVERNOR_PUBKEY_HEX resolves at import): empty/absent state-dir -> no ugk.db created + structured error + nonzero exit for all three; founded state -> all three succeed with receipt_count byte-identical and zero new genesis files; mode=ro store write() raises ReadOnlyViolation. (4) HYGIENE: tools/archive_hygiene_check.py is run at mint and fails the build if the release tarball index contains any pyc/pyo/__pycache__ entry, making the (already pyc-clean) archive hygiene MACHINE-CHECKED so the recurring reviewer ambiguity (pyc generated only by RUNNING extracted code) cannot recur. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d ALL UNMOVED (kernel.py and cli.py are NOT law; the store read-only path adds no committed column - schema_hash recomputes identical); NO registry invariant added (Invariant D is now ENFORCED on the production read path but DELIBERATELY NOT formalized as a law invariant this release, consistent with formalize-only-what-is-wired-and-adjudicated: the property is now wired+gated, which is the precondition for an honest future law-moving formalization should the Governor elect it); NO amendment; r94->r95 continuity is BEHAVIORAL.",alternatives=["Implement A as a narrow CLI workaround (special-case verify to not create the DB): REJECTED by the Governor - special-cases one command rather than forcing the production read path to inherit IEL discipline; the substrate (mode=ro store + hydrate-only kernel) eliminates more technical debt and covers verify/status/attest uniformly.","Re-derive attest s attestation in the CLI from read-only sources (bypassing the kernel snapshot): AVOIDED - duplicates kernel snapshot logic in the CLI (drift risk); the hydrate-only kernel is DRY and is the substrate-correct read path the Governor asked for.","Formalize Invariant D as a registry invariant (law-moving amendment) now: NOT TAKEN this release - kept frame-stationary per the Governor (no law move unless implementation discovers a pin must move; it did not). Formalization is a later law-moving step once the Governor elects it; r95 supplies its precondition (wired + adversarially gated).","Make the hygiene check a conformance gate instead of a mint-time assertion: the release ARTIFACT (tarball) only exists at mint, so the assertion is mint-time tooling; the in-process conformance gates already run pyc-clean and there is no tarball at gate time."],consequences="The external review s #3 (read-only path creates ugk.db) is CLOSED: verify/status/attest now use a true read-only substrate that cannot create schema or ugk.db, open a session, or emit receipts; missing state fails closed with a structured result (exit 2); existing founded states still verify/status/attest successfully with ZERO receipt/file mutation (proven by readonly_invariant_gate, not merely asserted). Archive hygiene is now machine-checked at mint (tools/archive_hygiene_check.py). FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger stays 11 (no amendment); registry stays 77 (no invariant added); ADRs through AD-30; gates 89 -> 90 (readonly_invariant_gate). The r94->r95 continuity link is BEHAVIORAL (frame-stationary), not amendment. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the read-only substrate is PRODUCTION (wired into the live CLI read commands + gated), distinct from AD-25 s ReadOnlyGuard which was a built-but-unwired primitive. Remaining review follow-on is #4/#30 MutationTransaction atomicity (needs the deferred-commit store.write refactor) - the phase AFTER C; C (execute() validate-before-mutate cluster) is the Governor s chosen next release.",bound_invariants=["IEL-S-01","DM-S-01","DM-S-03"])

ADR_31=_adr(id="AD-31",context="r95 closed IEL Invariant D (read-only). The Governor chose the central governed MUTATION path next: execute(). An evidence pack (founded-kernel probes with receipt_count/stream_hash deltas) established that execute() wrote the gate_admit receipt at step 5 but ran will/intent coverage AND warrant materialization at step 6 - AFTER the admit - and called gate() unguarded. Concretely: (case 4, headline) a will/intent coverage failure wrote a gate_admit AND then a gate_refuse for a REFUSED op (admit-then-refuse, +2 receipts); (case 3) a bad warrant_basis crashed AFTER gate_admit (+1 receipt) with an UnboundLocalError on _am (undefined when no AuthorityModel is attached) - a real bug in the warrant error path; (cases 1/2/5) non-JSON parameters, a non-string authority, and a raising gate surfaced as RAW uncontrolled exceptions (0 mutation but uncontrolled). Governing phrase: no admit before the refusal horizon is exhausted.",decision="r96 wires IEL Invariant A into execute() (validate-before-mutate), reordering it so the full refusal/protocol horizon is exhausted BEFORE any gate_admit. (1) A PREFLIGHT block at the top raises a controlled ProtocolError (new exception type) with ZERO chain mutation for malformed inputs: non-string authority, non-JSON-serializable parameters (validated against the store s OWN _params_json serializer so preflight accepts exactly what write() accepts), or a malformed warrant_basis (must be a list of strings). NO receipt is written - a non-string authority cannot even be written into a protocol_error receipt (re-crashes on .encode), so a true no-op is the fail-closed outcome (Governor ruling a). (2) gate() is GUARDED: a raising gate emits exactly ONE classified protocol_error receipt and raises ProtocolError (Governor ruling b - a raising gate is a malfunction, not a constitutional refusal), not a propagated raw exception. (3) The will/intent coverage check is MOVED above the gate_admit write, so a coverage failure writes a single gate_refuse with NO preceding gate_admit (closes the admit-then-refuse). (4) _am is initialized to None unconditionally (fixing the post-admit warrant-handler UnboundLocalError), with warrant_basis now pre-validated. Both semantic choices (a) and (b) were CONFIRMED by the Governor before implementation (no-silent-semantics on the central path). Proven by execute_validate_before_mutate_gate (founded; NOT_ESTABLISHED standalone, runs under verify_release charter): each malformed case leaves receipt_count + stream_hash UNCHANGED with no admit; the raising gate yields exactly one protocol_error receipt and no admit; the intent-coverage failure yields one gate_refuse and no admit; the happy path still admits. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (execute() lives in kernel.py, not law; no committed column); NO registry invariant added (Invariant A is now ENFORCED on the production execute() path but, consistent with the r95 discipline for D, not yet formalized as a law invariant - wiring precedes formalization); NO amendment; r95->r96 behavioral.",alternatives=["Emit a classified protocol_error receipt for malformed inputs instead of zero mutation: NOT CHOSEN (Governor ruling a) - a non-string authority re-crashes inside the receipt write (.encode), so a true no-op is the strongest fail-closed and uniform across the three malformed sub-cases.","Treat a raising gate as gate_refuse instead of protocol_error: NOT CHOSEN (Governor ruling b) - a gate that raises is a malfunction, not a constitutional decision to refuse; protocol_error classifies it honestly.","Keep the will/intent check after gate_admit and retract the spurious admit afterward: REJECTED - the admit is load-bearing (NBER-1/EH-S-02); the discipline is to NOT write it until the refusal horizon is exhausted, not to write-then-retract.","Wrap execute() in MutationTransaction now (atomic admit+refuse): DEFERRED to phase B - requires the deferred-commit store.write() refactor (higher risk). r96 is the lower-risk validate-before-mutate reorder, the central-path win taken first."],consequences="execute() now exhausts the input/gate/intent refusal horizon BEFORE any gate_admit: malformed authority/parameters/warrant_basis fail closed with ZERO mutation; a raising gate yields exactly one classified protocol_error receipt; an intent-coverage failure yields a single gate_refuse - never an admit-then-refuse or a crash-after-admit. The case-3 UnboundLocalError is fixed. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger stays 11 (no amendment); registry stays 77; ADRs through AD-31; gates 90 -> 91 (execute_validate_before_mutate_gate). r95->r96 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link. Remaining follow-ons: phase B (MutationTransaction atomicity, needs the deferred-commit write refactor); and the recorded read-path corruption-taxonomy item (a malformed/incomplete existing ugk.db still throws a raw SQLite traceback in verify/status/attest), deferred to a later read-path hardening pass.",bound_invariants=["EH-S-02","CM-S-03","WILL-S-06"])

ADR_32=_adr(id="AD-32",context="r96 wired Invariant A into execute() but an external adversarial review found the preflight checked JSON-serializability WITHOUT enforcing dict-ness (issue #33 plus extensions), leaving the malformed-input -> admit -> raw-crash shape for some inputs. Founded probes with receipt_count/gate_admit deltas: parameters=[] was silently normalized to {} by `or {}` and admitted (+2 receipts, gate_admit +1); parameters='bad' and parameters=1 are JSON-serializable so PASSED the r96 preflight, wrote gate_admit, then crashed RAW (ValueError/TypeError) AFTER the admit (+1 receipt, gate_admit +1); authority='' was silently defaulted to self._authority by `or` and admitted; authority_set=[non-JSON] crashed in the success-receipt write AFTER admit. So r96 closed PART of the validate-before-mutate cluster, not the whole cluster.",decision="r97 validates the protocol boundary BEFORE any normalization or write, sealing the input-refusal horizon r96 left partially open. (1) authority: None -> self._authority; otherwise must be a NON-EMPTY string (rejects both non-string and empty-string, which the old `or` silently defaulted). (2) parameters: None -> {}; otherwise must be a DICT (rejects [], 'bad', 1; the `or {}` normalization that turned falsy non-None values into {} is removed). (3) _params_json on the now-confirmed dict (contents JSON-serializable, via the store s own serializer). (4) warrant_basis sortability (unchanged from r96). (5) authority_set (which is folded into the post-admit success receipt): must be a JSON-serializable LIST. Every malformed protocol-boundary input -> controlled ProtocolError with ZERO mutation (no receipt, no admit). The execute_validate_before_mutate_gate is EXTENDED with parameters=[]/'bad'/1, authority='', and non-JSON authority_set, each asserting receipt_count + stream_hash UNCHANGED with no admit; happy path and the None-defaulting of authority/parameters still admit. FRAME-STATIONARY + corrective: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (execute() is in kernel.py, not law); NO registry invariant added; NO amendment; r96->r97 behavioral. With this, the validate-before-mutate cluster (#22/#33/#34/#35/#55) is CLOSED.",alternatives=["Keep r96 s JSON-only check and fix the downstream crash sites instead: REJECTED - the discipline is to seal the boundary (no admit before the refusal horizon is exhausted), not to admit a non-dict and patch each crash site.","Coerce non-dict parameters (wrap or stringify): REJECTED - silent semantics; a non-dict parameters is a caller/protocol error, not something to normalize.","Continue defaulting authority='' as before: REJECTED - an empty authority is meaningless and was silently masked; fail closed.","Defer authority_set validation: REJECTED - authority_set reaches a post-admit write, so an unvalidated authority_set is the same admit-then-crash shape; sealed now."],consequences="Every malformed protocol-boundary input to execute() - non-string or empty authority, non-dict or non-JSON parameters, non-sortable warrant_basis, non-list or non-JSON authority_set - now fails closed with a controlled ProtocolError and ZERO mutation: no admit-then-crash, no silent normalization. Valid inputs (parameters None|dict, authority None|non-empty-str, sortable warrant_basis, JSON-list authority_set) admit exactly as before. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77; ADRs through AD-32; gates stay 91 (the existing execute_validate_before_mutate_gate is extended, not a new gate). r96->r97 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link. With the input-refusal horizon sealed, the next phase is B (MutationTransaction atomicity, requiring the deferred-commit store.write() refactor); the read-path corruption-taxonomy follow-on (malformed existing ugk.db -> raw SQLite traceback in verify/status/attest) also remains for a later read-path pass.",bound_invariants=["EH-S-02","CM-S-03","WILL-S-06"])

ADR_33=_adr(id="AD-33",context="The Three Hash Rule and Fractal Governance Architecture (FGA) are the foundational theory the UGK substrate instantiates - Three Hash Rule section 17 states UGK instantiates the Three Hash Rule as a receipt discipline. Before designing MutationTransaction (the post-admit atomicity phase, B), the Governor directed a SHORT alignment ADR mapping the IEL/UGK runtime vocabulary onto the two papers so the next phase s atomicity semantics are grounded in the papers terms rather than invented. This ADR records the correspondence; it is a RECORD-ONLY governance act and changes NO behavior.",decision="Six mappings between the UGK/IEL runtime and the Three Hash Rule + FGA, with a frame-stationarity determination. (M1) ProtocolError vs REFUSE vs ADMIT: FGA section 7 binds delta=ADMIT iff Adm=TOP and delta=REFUSE iff Adm=BOT, both emitting a receipt (UGK is a FULL FGA realization - gate_admit AND gate_refuse). FGA section 15.5 separates a PROTOCOL failure (rejected at the protocol layer PRIOR TO admissibility evaluation, distinguishable from a constitutional REFUSE) from a constitutional REFUSE (Adm=BOT within a known root). UGK maps exactly: gate_admit = ADMIT (aggregation F(D)=TOP); gate_refuse + GateRefusal = REFUSE (fail-closed: delta=REFUSE whenever Adm != TOP); ProtocolError (r96/r97) = the protocol failure, caught at preflight before admissibility, distinguishable from gate_refuse by type. CRISIS (FGA 15.5 root-disambiguation) is out of scope for single-root v0.1.0, noted as a frontier. (M2) Evaluator context epsilon: FGA section 4 has Adm:P x C x J x E -> {TOP,BOT} with epsilon the constitutionally qualified evaluator; FGA Property 6 and Three Hash Rule section 7 (Evaluator as Implementation) hold that epsilon IMPLEMENTS the decision procedure and its identity is a PROVENANCE fact in the witness family pi, not a semantic input, under a DETERMINISTIC constitution. UGK is deterministic: epsilon maps to authority + gate/AuthorityModel + governor_sig; the gate outcome is evaluator-invariant (two evaluators on the same inputs reach the same verdict - UGK determinism), while epsilon stays load-bearing for receipt issuance authority, attestation (the authority field), auditability, accountability. FUTURE (frontier): full evaluator context epsilon should eventually include kernel/build identity, the law/schema/legend frame, jurisdiction, phase/epoch, the policy/authority frame, verification level, and the decision-surface set; UGK currently binds epsilon to authority + gate/AuthorityModel + governor_sig. (M3) Decision surfaces D_i: FGA section 5.1 defines D={D_1..D_n}, D_i:(x,c,J,epsilon)->R_i, Adm=F(D), F the aggregation operator. UGK s runtime decision surfaces are the per-axis kernel checks - D_s (state/H_s), D_c (admissibility - gate + AuthorityModel + authority graph), D_m (meaning/H_m), D_j (locality/H_j), and the will/intent coverage surface (WILL-S-06); F is UGK s CONJUNCTIVE aggregation (all surfaces must pass to admit), which is why adding a surface can only refuse (FGA Property 3 monotonicity). The r96/r97 preflight checks are PROTOCOL surfaces (well-formedness), evaluated BEFORE the constitutional surfaces, consistent with M1. (M4) Receipt commitments H_s/H_c/H_m/H_j/H_r/h_body: Three Hash Rule sections 4-9 define H_s (state), H_c (admissibility), H_m (meaning), H_j (locality) as the four independent decision-surface commitments, and H_r = root(H_s,H_c,H_m,H_j[+context]) as the receipt IDENTITY. By FGA Property 5 the receipt commits the trace vector componentwise (R ~ Commit(D)), so H_s/H_c/H_m/H_j ARE the cryptographic dual of UGK s decision-surface vector. UGK s h_body (AD-28, IEL-S-01) is a STRENGTHENING BEYOND the papers H_r: a domain-separated whole-body commitment over EVERY committed field computed purely from stored values, operationalizing the binding-verification/recoverability concern (Three Hash Rule section 4.5) and FGA structural tamper-evidence (section 6) at the FIELD level - detecting tampering of any field, not only the four-axis root. (M5) Trace-vector evidence: FGA section 5.1 makes the constitutional trace vector D=(D_1..D_n) a FIRST-CLASS object - the commitment target for receipts and the basis for differential evaluation (which surfaces changed). Three Hash Rule verify(R,C)->[(Domain,Result,ErrorCode)] is that vector in verification form, error codes from the Three Hash Rule taxonomy (ExpiredEdge, NamespaceNonMember, ...). UGK realizes it as the per-axis verify outcome vector (D_s/D_c/D_m/D_j + codes) committed in the receipt; differential evaluation across RELEASES is a release-lineage ANALOGUE of trace-vector differential evaluation (an analogy, NOT an identity), realized by the continuity-surface diff (B4 substrate/verification/codex change-confinement). (M6) Transaction atomicity as preservation of a whole governed transition: FGA section 3 defines the governed transition T=(rho,J,E,v,delta,R,alpha) as the unit of governance, and section 8.1 places UGK in the class that SEPARATES decision (gate_admit) from execution (effect), with admit + effect + success-receipt together realizing T. Atomicity = the WHOLE T preserved all-or-nothing: a partial transition (admit without effect, effect without success-receipt, admit-then-crash) is a BROKEN transition that must not persist. r96/r97 sealed the PRE-admit (refusal) horizon (no delta is written until the refusal horizon is exhausted); MutationTransaction (phase B) must seal the POST-admit horizon, making T - not the individual receipt write - the unit of atomicity, with rollback preserving the pre-transition state and a structural abort record. FRAME DETERMINATION: this alignment is RECORD-ONLY and FRAME-STATIONARY. UGK already instantiates the papers (Three Hash Rule section 17); UGK s receipt frame is a SUPERSET of the papers receipt (adds h_body and the committed fields); H_r and the four axes match; ADMIT/REFUSE match gate_admit/gate_refuse. No discrepancy requires a law/schema move. law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; no amendment; r97->r98 behavioral.",alternatives=["Skip the alignment and start MutationTransaction directly: REJECTED (Governor directive) - the post-admit atomicity semantics must be grounded in the papers whole-governed-transition T, not invented at implementation time.","Treat the papers as mandating a frame change: REJECTED - UGK already instantiates the Three Hash Rule (its section 17) and exceeds it (h_body beyond H_r); the four-axis commitments and ADMIT/REFUSE already match. No committed-frame change is exposed by the alignment.","Add a structural-error receipt for malformed-input ProtocolErrors to match the papers missing-jurisdiction structural-error receipt: NOT TAKEN here - UGK already emits protocol_error receipts for the other protocol violations (kernel_internal, not_founded, undeclared, require_gate, gate_exception); the malformed-INPUT subclass uses zero mutation (Governor ruling a) because a non-string authority cannot be safely written into a receipt. Distinguishability (the architectural requirement) is satisfied. Recorded as an alignment observation and a future option, NOT a frame change and NOT a behavior change in this ADR."],consequences="The UGK/IEL runtime is shown to be a faithful, slightly stronger realization of the Three Hash Rule + FGA: ProtocolError/REFUSE/ADMIT = FGA protocol-failure/REFUSE/ADMIT; epsilon = the deterministic-constitution evaluator (provenance, outcome-invariant); the per-axis checks = FGA decision surfaces aggregated conjunctively; H_s/H_c/H_m/H_j/H_r = the papers commitments with h_body an additional whole-body strengthening; the verify outcome vector = the constitutional trace vector; atomicity = preservation of the whole governed transition T. One divergence is recorded (zero-mutation malformed-input protocol errors vs the papers structural-error receipt) - distinguishability is satisfied, it is a realization choice (Governor ruling a), NOT a committed-frame change, and a future option rather than an action here. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11; registry 77; ADRs through AD-33; gates stay 91 (no gate change). r97->r98 behavioral. A companion cross-walk, SHIPPED IN THE ARCHIVE at docs/architecture/UGK_IEL_ThreeHash_FGA_Alignment.md, records the detailed mapping table. (Record note: in r98 the cross-walk lived only in the outputs presentation; r99 folds it into the archive so this statement is literally true. The r97->r98 RUNTIME diff was adr.py + codex/CODEX; continuity metadata (continuity_surfaces.json, CONTINUITY_ATTESTATION.json) also changed as expected.) With the alignment recorded, the MutationTransaction/deferred-commit design proceeds next, grounded in M6 (atomicity = the whole transition T is the atom).",bound_invariants=["EH-S-02","IEL-S-01","CM-S-03"])

ADR_34=_adr(id="AD-34",context="AD-33 (r98) grounded Phase B: atomicity = preservation of the WHOLE governed transition T (M6). The known blocker (AD-24/AD-27): store.write() commits internally, so a SAVEPOINT-based MutationTransaction could not compose, and migrate_schema committed the schema BEFORE writing the migration receipt - a receipt-write failure left the schema mutated with no receipt (#30 mutate-then-fail-receipt). The Governor authorized the smallest production seam to make MutationTransaction real, piloted on migrate_schema, without breaking existing callers, with an explicit tightening that a failed transaction must persist NOTHING and prefer no outer commit.",decision="r99 introduces the DEFERRED-COMMIT SEAM in UGKReceiptStore and pilots it on migrate_schema (Invariant E - atomic multi-step write). (1) A TRANSACTION-DEPTH GUARD in store.write(): write() always does its INSERT and advances the in-memory frontier, but issues the durable conn.commit() ONLY at _txn_depth == 0; inside an enclosing store.transaction() (depth>0) the commit is DEFERRED to the outer transaction. Existing callers run at depth 0 and commit exactly as before (byte-identical). (2) store.transaction(validation, name): a context manager wrapping the existing MutationTransaction SAVEPOINT (Invariant A: refuses to open via MutationRefused if validation is not ok; Invariant E: SAVEPOINT all-or-nothing). It SNAPSHOTS the Python-side frontier (_prior_h_r/_prior_h_m/_prior_intent_ref/_schema_hash) on entry and RESTORES it on rollback (a SAVEPOINT cannot revert these in-memory attrs), and tracks _txn_depth. CRITICAL (Governor tightening): NO outer conn.commit() on EITHER path - empirically RELEASE of the outermost savepoint commits the clean block durably (in_transaction=False) and ROLLBACK TO + RELEASE persists NOTHING and leaves a clean, usable connection (in_transaction=False), so a failed transaction needs no connection-level commit and cannot persist any escaped schema/receipt/effect side effect. (3) migrate_schema REWIRED: the None/empty/unsafe preflight (AD-27 ValidationResult) is UNCHANGED and refuses-before-mutation; the schema ALTER, the after-hash, and the migration receipt now run inside store.transaction(), committing together or rolling back together; self._schema_hash is refreshed ONLY after the transaction commits. Proven by migrate_schema_atomicity_gate (standalone; also under verify_release): valid migration commits schema+receipt together (durable in a FRESH connection); a receipt-boundary fault rolls the schema back; a schema-boundary fault (duplicate ADD COLUMN - passes the receipt-safe validator, fails at execute) persists nothing; EACH fault is verified from a FRESH connection (schema, receipt count, AND stream hash all == pre-transaction) with no outer commit; the in-memory frontier is restored and the next write (same-instance AND fresh-reopen) links to the PRE-rollback frontier, not the rolled-back receipt's h_r; empty/invalid refuse before mutation; depth-0 writes still commit. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: store.write/migrate_schema/store.transaction live in store.py (not law); NO schema column added (the receipts table shape is unchanged); law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; r98->r99 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED (Governor): only migrate_schema is piloted; MutationTransaction remains the primitive; Invariant E is NOT formalized as law (the wiring covers only this path; formalizing would overclaim, same discipline as A/D); no global atomicity is claimed; seal_and_prune_epoch, charter artifacts, and other archive writes are UNTOUCHED.",alternatives=["Make write() always commit and retry on failure: REJECTED - hides failures and does not compose; the seam must let an outer governed transaction own the durable commit.","Issue an outer conn.commit() on the FAILURE path to close the transaction frame: REJECTED (Governor tightening) - empirically unnecessary (ROLLBACK TO + RELEASE leaves a clean connection that persisted nothing) and a commit risks persisting an escaped side effect; prefer no outer commit on failure.","Remove the in-memory chain-tip update from write() instead of snapshot/restore: REJECTED - the tips are load-bearing for the next write's parent linkage on the SUCCESS path; snapshot/restore is the surgical fix that keeps success-path behavior while making rollback correct.","Wire every multi-step operation (execute(), seal_and_prune_epoch, charter) now: REJECTED (Governor scope) - prove the seam on the smallest high-value path (migrate_schema) first, not finish all transactionality.","Formalize Invariant E as law now: DEFERRED - the production wiring covers only migrate_schema; formalizing the claim before the wiring covers it would overclaim (a primitive becomes law when migration covers the claim)."],consequences="MutationTransaction is now a PRODUCTION-PROVEN SEAM, not merely a primitive: store.transaction() composes receipt write + effect mutation + terminal status into ONE atomic governed transition, and migrate_schema is the first production path wired onto it (#30 mutate-then-fail-receipt closed for migrate_schema). A transition is not committed until its schema change, its receipt, and its terminal status commit together; a fault at any boundary rolls the whole transition back with NO persisted side effect and a restored in-memory frontier (verified from a fresh connection). FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11; registry 77; ADRs through AD-34; gates 91->92 (migrate_schema_atomicity_gate). r98->r99 behavioral. NOT claimed: global atomicity (only migrate_schema is wired) and Invariant E as law (deferred until the wiring covers the claim). Remaining transactionality - execute() post-admit composition, seal_and_prune_epoch, charter artifacts, archive writes - is future per-path work on this same seam. AUDITED-TOPOLOGY DISCLOSURE: the seam REPLACES migrate_schema's direct conn.commit() with a deferred-commit transaction (durable receipt writes still flow ONLY through write(); the seam adds no new raw-data-mutation path, but it is a new audited COMMIT/RELEASE mechanism - the deferred-commit counterpart of write()'s direct commit). The B4a single-writer / mutation-surface probe (tools/b4a_conformance.py) was updated DELIBERATELY (not loosened) to enumerate store.transaction() as an EXPLICITLY AUDITED mutation surface and to positively prove: durable receipt writes flow only through write(); migrate_schema uses the seam with NO direct commit; the seam is built on MutationTransaction (A+E) with NO unmanaged outer commit; all commit/release points are under the store lock; and a failed transaction persists nothing (schema/receipts/stream/frontier, from a fresh connection).",bound_invariants=["PERSIST-S-01","EH-S-02","DM-S-01"])

ADR_35=_adr(id="AD-35",context="r99 (AD-34) introduced the deferred-commit seam store.transaction(), proven on migrate_schema and audited by B4a. The Governor's architectural follow-on: store.transaction() is now a HIGH-POWER mutation surface, and r99 proved current callsites open it under the store lock - but that is a CALLER CONVENTION. Before broadening the seam (to seal_and_prune_epoch, execute(), charter/archive writes) the lock discipline must be INTRINSIC / mechanically enforced, not a convention a future caller could forget.",decision="r100 makes lock discipline a PROPERTY OF THE SEAM (hardening only). store.transaction() now acquires self._lock INTRINSICALLY (the existing RLock; re-entrant) and holds it across the ENTIRE governed transition (SAVEPOINT open -> body -> RELEASE/ROLLBACK), so a future caller CANNOT open a governed transaction without the store lock - serialization is guaranteed by the seam, not by callers remembering to wrap it. RLock re-entrancy makes this compose cleanly: it nests under migrate_schema's outer `with self._lock` and under write()'s internal `with self._lock` with NO deadlock (proven: lock-free caller works; double-acquire works; nested works). migrate_schema's outer lock is RETAINED (it also serializes the before/after schema_hash reads that sit OUTSIDE the transaction) - the change is purely ADDITIVE to transaction(). B4a's seam-ii proof is upgraded to MECHANICAL ENFORCEMENT: the PRIMARY check now proves transaction() acquires self._lock intrinsically over the FULL savepoint lifecycle (MutationTransaction construction + __enter__/__exit__ inside the `with self._lock`); the caller-side 'opened under lock' check is retained as DEFENSE-IN-DEPTH. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: store.py only (not law); NO schema column; law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; r99->r100 behavioral. SCOPE: hardening ONLY - NO new pilot migration (seal_and_prune_epoch is the r101 target, deferred); NO global atomicity claim; Invariant E is NOT formalized as law (the wiring still covers only migrate_schema).",alternatives=["Option 2 (private/audited-only seam + assert it is already executing under the store lock): REJECTED - an assert only DETECTS a caller who forgot to take the lock; intrinsic acquisition makes the omission IMPOSSIBLE. For a high-power durable-truth surface, a guarantee beats detection.","Leave lock discipline as a caller convention (status quo after r99): REJECTED (Governor) - a transaction primitive that relies on callers remembering to acquire the lock is a sharp edge; if the seam becomes the path for durable truth, serialization must live inside the seam.","Acquire a NON-re-entrant Lock in the seam: REJECTED - it would deadlock under migrate_schema's existing outer `with self._lock` and under write()'s internal lock; RLock (already in use) is the correct shape.","Broaden the seam to seal_and_prune_epoch / execute() now, before hardening: REJECTED (Governor scope) - intrinsic lock discipline is a PRECONDITION for broadening; do the small hardening step first."],consequences="store.transaction() now carries its OWN lock discipline - it is safe to reuse on additional paths (the r101 seal_and_prune_epoch pilot, and later execute()) without depending on callers to serialize. B4a mechanically enforces this: the seam owns its lock, verified structurally over the full savepoint lifecycle (caller-side check retained as defense-in-depth). FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc; ledger 11; registry 77; ADRs through AD-35 (33); gates 92 (no new batch gate - B4a is a deep-probe; the existing migrate_schema_atomicity_gate still passes). r99->r100 behavioral. NOT claimed: global atomicity; Invariant E as law (still wired only into migrate_schema). NEXT: r101 designs seal_and_prune_epoch (receipt writes + destructive DELETE + postcondition integrity) onto the now-hardened seam, with the design presented BEFORE implementation; execute() post-admit composition is deferred until the seam has survived at least these two store-level paths - its effect() callback is arbitrary, possibly non-rollback-able caller code and must not be smuggled into r101.",bound_invariants=["PERSIST-S-01","DM-S-01","GK-S-02"])

ADR_36=_adr(id="AD-36",context="r100 (AD-35) hardened the seam (intrinsic lock). The Governor directed seal_and_prune_epoch as the r101 pilot - the SECOND store-level destructive path - and flagged a future-hardening note: make rollback cleanup maximally defensive (restore the Python frontier even if MutationTransaction.__exit__ raises during rollback). seal_and_prune_epoch had the same atomicity gap as migrate_schema's #30 (a multi-step mutation: two provenance receipts + a destructive prefix DELETE + postconditions, with write()'s internal commit, a direct DELETE commit, and postconditions checked AFTER the commit - too late to roll back) = #63.",decision="r101 wires seal_and_prune_epoch onto the (r100-hardened) seam AND folds in the defensive rollback cleanup. (1) DEFENSIVE CLEANUP in store.transaction(): the Python-side frontier restore on rollback now runs in a FINALLY, so it happens EVEN IF MutationTransaction.__exit__ raises during ROLLBACK TO / RELEASE - the seam is now reused across paths, so rollback must be maximally resilient. (2) seal_and_prune_epoch REWIRED: the preflight (intent present / seal_hash in chain / frontier chains from S) is UNCHANGED and refuses-before-mutation; the two provenance receipts (epoch_sealed, epoch_pruned), the destructive prefix DELETE, and the postconditions now run INSIDE store.transaction() as ONE governed transition. The postconditions are PRE-COMMIT GATES (moved from post-commit assertions): the block commits (RELEASE) ONLY if both receipts are written, the prefix is deleted, the tip is stable, AND the retained chain verifies from the seal commitment S; ANY failure ROLLS BACK both receipts AND the DELETE (and restores the frontier). The tip is measured AFTER the two terminal receipts are appended (the retained tail already includes them); the prune must not move or rewrite that tail. The direct self._conn.commit() is REMOVED (the seam commits via RELEASE). Proven by seal_and_prune_atomicity_gate (standalone + verify_release): valid seal/prune commits the two receipts + the DELETE together (durable; verify_from_seal(S) passes from a FRESH connection; tip stable); a fault at ANY boundary - write failure, DELETE failure, postcondition failure (verify_from_seal False) - rolls back both receipts AND the DELETE, and from a FRESH connection the receipt count, the full receipt-id set (PRUNED ROWS and frontier), and the stream hash all match pre-transaction with NO outer commit; preflight refuses before mutation. B4a positively audits the SECOND seam-backed path: seal_and_prune_epoch uses the seam with NO direct commit, its receipts flow through write() (seam-i), and its destructive DELETE executes ONLY inside the store.transaction() block. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: store.py only (not law); NO schema column; law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; r100->r101 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED: seal_and_prune_epoch is the second wired path; MutationTransaction remains the primitive; Invariant E is NOT formalized as law (the wiring now covers migrate_schema + seal_and_prune_epoch, not the full claim); NO global atomicity claim; execute() post-admit composition, charter artifacts, and archive writes are UNTOUCHED.",alternatives=["Keep postconditions as POST-commit assertions: REJECTED - a postcondition failure would then leave the prune committed while raising an error (partial/inconsistent); pre-commit gates make the whole transition atomic (the Governor's required semantics).","Measure the tip BEFORE the two terminal receipts (the pre-seal/prune tip): REJECTED (Governor clarification) - the invariant is that the tip AFTER prune equals the tip AFTER the two terminal receipts are appended; the retained tail must already include them and the prune must not move/rewrite it.","Defer the defensive rollback cleanup to a later micro-step: REJECTED (Governor) - r101 is exactly the moment to make the seam more resilient, before relying on it again.","Wire execute() now (highest governance value): DEFERRED (Governor scope) - execute()'s effect() callback may be arbitrary, non-rollback-able caller code; prove the seam on a second STORE-level path first."],consequences="seal_and_prune_epoch is now the SECOND production path on the seam - a governed, ALL-OR-NOTHING destructive transition: the seal receipt, the prune receipt, the prefix deletion, and the integrity postconditions commit together or roll back together (#63 closed). The seam's rollback is now defensively resilient (frontier restored even if __exit__ raises). FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc; ledger 11; registry 77; ADRs through AD-36 (34); gates 92->93 (seal_and_prune_atomicity_gate). r100->r101 behavioral. NOT claimed: global atomicity; Invariant E as law (wired into TWO paths now, not the full claim). NEXT: the seam has survived two store-level paths (migrate_schema, seal_and_prune_epoch); execute() post-admit composition is the candidate next phase but requires a DEDICATED design for the non-rollback-able effect() callback - not to be rushed.",bound_invariants=["PERSIST-S-01","EH-S-02","DM-S-01"])

ADR_37=_adr(id="AD-37",context="r101 (AD-36) wired the deferred-commit seam onto a SECOND store-level path (seal_and_prune_epoch) and flagged execute() post-admit composition as the candidate next phase but requiring a DEDICATED design, because execute()'s effect() callback is ARBITRARY, possibly non-rollback-able caller code that must not be smuggled onto the seam. The Governor directed an EffectAtomicity design before any wiring. The design's hard answer: execute() atomicity is EFFECT-CLASS-RELATIVE - the kernel cannot honestly claim an arbitrary effect() is rollback-able, because a SQLite seam can roll back store-local state but cannot roll back a payment, a network call, a file write, or an unknown external mutation. A second flaw was identified: execute() today writes the SUCCESS receipt BEFORE running effect(), so a receipt asserts effect success before the effect has actually succeeded. A fail-closed HALT during scoping found 23 execute(effect=...) callsites: 16 pass a REAL effect (6 of them conformance gates inside the verify_release batch, plus production cli.py and transport/broker.py), and 7 pass effect=None (namespace_governance.py, which the contract correctly does not touch). Failing closed on all real-effect callsites at once would break the verify_release suite and production functionality with no functional gain. The Governor chose Option A: an explicit, transitional EffectAtomicity.NON_ATOMIC legacy-bridge posture, rather than a convention-based grandfather (rejected per the r100 no-convention discipline) or a hard break. Concurrent Three Hash Rule v3-v4 / FGA v16-v17 updates refined the framing twice: from artifact CLASSES to constitutional ROLES (receipt-ness, authority-ness, and evidence-ness are ROLES an artifact may be admitted under, each with different validity criteria, not fixed artifact ontologies, the constitution determining which roles apply), and from mechanical guarantee to SOFT ENFORCEMENT (receipts make compliance, noncompliance, discharge, supersession, and escalation DECIDABLE under policy, not mechanically guaranteed, with escalation proceeding through evidence-use when a receiving constitution recognizes the receipt) - so an effect-outcome receipt must not be confused with the authority role, the external effect, proof that an irreversible action can be rewound, or a mechanical guarantee of compliance.",decision="r102-a introduces the EffectAtomicity CONTRACT and the NON_ATOMIC legacy bridge - classification, not repair. (1) A five-class EffectAtomicity enum in kernel.py: PURE, STORE_LOCAL (both store-local and rollback-able via the AD-34/36 seam), EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE (compensation/saga), EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE (two-phase prepare/commit), and NON_ATOMIC (the transitional bridge). (2) execute() gains an effect_atomicity parameter and a PREFLIGHT check placed with the r96/r97 protocol-boundary validations - BEFORE gate evaluation, gate_admit, the success receipt, and effect itself: an effect supplied with NO declaration raises a controlled ProtocolError with ZERO chain mutation (no gate_admit, no success receipt); an effect declared with any of the four real classes ALSO fails closed (ProtocolError, zero mutation) because r102-a implements no per-class protocol; only NON_ATOMIC proceeds. (3) NON_ATOMIC proceeds under the UNCHANGED legacy execution order (gate -> gate_admit -> success receipt -> effect) and stamps an effect_atomicity marker into the gate_admit parameters and the success-receipt parameters. The marker lives in the parameters JSON ONLY - no schema column and no law change. (4) All 16 real-effect callsites are backfilled to declare NON_ATOMIC; the 7 effect=None callsites are untouched (the 'if effect is not None' guard skips them, so no-effect calls behave exactly as before). (5) A runtime gate (effect_atomicity_declaration_gate) proves: undeclared effect -> ProtocolError before admit with zero mutation and no gate_admit; each of the four real classes fails closed with zero mutation; NON_ATOMIC proceeds with the marker present in both receipts. (6) A static probe (tools/effect_declaration_probe.py, a deep/clean-room scaffold, NOT in the batch) proves every in-tree execute() callsite with a non-None effect declares an EffectAtomicity. DECISION-vs-OUTCOME: gate_admit remains BEFORE effect and means 'admitted to ATTEMPT', preserving receipt-before-effect (NBER-1); stopping the success receipt being written before effect success is per-class future work. THR v3-v4 / FGA v16-v17 INTEGRATION (load-bearing). ROLE-BASED (THR v3 / FGA v16): NON_ATOMIC is NOT an artifact type - it is a ROLE-NEUTRAL EXECUTION-PROTOCOL classification recorded in the governance trail, NOT an authority artifact, NOT an evidence artifact by itself, and NOT an atomicity or rollback claim. NON_ATOMIC does not describe what the effect PRODUCED; it describes the kernel's EXECUTION PROTOCOL for a supplied effect. Any artifact the effect produces may later be admitted under receipt, authority, or evidence ROLES according to the constitution - each role carrying different validity criteria, per THR v3's role formulation and FGA v16's clarification that a commitment artifact may carry receipt-role and authority-role contracts in one object or as separate objects. SOFT-ENFORCEMENT (THR v4 / FGA v17): the marker does not MECHANICALLY enforce compliance - receipts make compliance, noncompliance, discharge, supersession, and escalation DECIDABLE under policy, not mechanically guaranteed, and escalation proceeds through evidence-use when a receiving constitution recognizes the receipt. NON_ATOMIC likewise does not make an effect safe or compliant; it does not grant authority, does not establish rollbackability, and does not mechanically enforce compliance - it makes the non-atomic posture of the effect LEGIBLE so later policy can evaluate compliance, noncompliance, escalation, or migration under the appropriate constitutional role-recognition rules. The marker is SOFT-ENFORCEMENT INFRASTRUCTURE: it does not make the effect atomic; it prevents the system from silently treating an unclassified effect as if it had atomic semantics. STORAGE-NEUTRAL / SUPPRESSION-AWARE: the marker does not by itself solve custody or availability - it is part of the receipt trail and inherits whatever receipt availability/custody rules the constitution adopts; if policy later expects to consult the marker and it is absent, that is a MISSING-EVIDENCE / fail-closed concern, NOT permission to infer atomicity. NON_ATOMIC preserves the legacy execution order while making the effect's non-atomic character EXPLICIT and AUDITABLE, not safe. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: the enum, the preflight, and the marker live in kernel.py (not law); the marker is in parameters JSON (NO committed column); law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; r101->r102 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED: only NON_ATOMIC is implemented; the four real-protocol classes fail closed; execute() effects are NOT routed through the seam; NO compensation or two-phase semantics; Invariant E is NOT formalized as law (the wiring still does not cover the claim, and NON_ATOMIC is explicitly NOT an Invariant-E posture).",alternatives=["Fail closed on ALL 23 effect callsites immediately (strict reading, no bridge): REJECTED - it would break 6 verify_release batch gates and production paths (cli.py, transport/broker.py) with no functional gain; r102-a could not certify standalone, and the migration churn is higher than the explicit-bridge path.","Grandfather existing callers by convention (exempt pre-existing callsites): REJECTED per the r100 no-convention discipline - a convention a future caller could lean on is exactly the sharp edge the seam-hardening work removed; every effect must declare, with NO silent exemption.","Implement the PURE / STORE_LOCAL seam protocol now (give the store-local effects real atomicity): DEFERRED to r102-b - it requires routing execute() effects through the AD-34/36 MutationTransaction seam AND explicit clean-path MutationTransaction.__exit__(None) failure semantics (class 1/2 success depends on clean-release durability); that is a dedicated design, presented before implementation, not bundled into the classification step.","Implement EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE two-phase or EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE compensation now: DEFERRED to later phases - irreversible effects need a truthful two-phase prepare/commit-or-abort trail and reversible effects need compensation/saga; neither is a classification concern and both are out of scope for the bridge.","Write the effect_atomicity marker as a new committed schema column: REJECTED - it would move the schema/frame for a record that fits in the existing parameters JSON; the marker is visible and auditable in parameters with NO schema/law churn.","Treat NON_ATOMIC as 'current behavior' without qualification, or as an atomicity/authority claim: REJECTED (Governor wording) - NON_ATOMIC preserves legacy execution order while making the lack of atomicity EXPLICIT and AUDITABLE; it is a transitional receipt/execution-protocol classification, not an authority artifact and not a success/rollback/Invariant-E guarantee.","Formalize Invariant E as law now: DEFERRED - the wiring still does not cover the global claim, and NON_ATOMIC is by construction NOT Invariant-E-compliant; formalizing would overclaim, consistent with the A/D/E wiring-precedes-formalization discipline."],consequences="Silent unknown effects are ELIMINATED: every execute() callsite that passes a real effect must now DECLARE its atomicity class, and an undeclared effect fails closed with a controlled ProtocolError and ZERO mutation BEFORE gate_admit (proven by effect_atomicity_declaration_gate and by the static effect_declaration_probe over the whole tree). The four real-protocol classes fail closed pending their protocols; only NON_ATOMIC proceeds, under the unchanged legacy execution order, stamping an explicit, auditable effect_atomicity marker into the gate_admit and success-receipt parameters. r102-a REPLACES SILENCE WITH CONFESSION - it does not lower the standard and does not make existing effects safe; it makes them explicit. NOT CLAIMED: that NON_ATOMIC is rollback-safe, success-proof, or Invariant-E-compliant; that any effect is atomic; global atomicity; Invariant E as law. The decision/outcome distinction is recorded: gate_admit means 'admitted to attempt' and stays before effect (receipt-before-effect / NBER-1 preserved); eliminating the success-before-effect receipt is per-class future work. THR v3-v4 / FGA v16-v17 are referenced (role-based + soft-enforcement formulation) so future phases treat receipt-ness, authority-ness, and evidence-ness as constitutional ROLES an artifact may be admitted under - each with different validity criteria - rather than fixed artifact classes, treat receipts (and the NON_ATOMIC marker) as making compliance/noncompliance/escalation DECIDABLE under policy rather than mechanically guaranteed, and do not conflate the NON_ATOMIC execution-protocol marker with any artifact the effect may produce or read it as a custody/availability or compliance guarantee; a later missing marker is a missing-evidence / fail-closed concern, not permission to infer atomicity. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (kernel.py is not law; the marker is parameters-JSON, not a committed column); genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added - EffectAtomicity is a kernel contract, not a law invariant; wiring precedes any future formalization); ADRs through AD-37 (35); gates 93 -> 94 (effect_atomicity_declaration_gate). r101->r102 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link. STAGED ROADMAP: NON_ATOMIC bridge NOW (r102-a); the PURE/STORE_LOCAL seam protocol NEXT (r102-b, design-first, including explicit clean-path MutationTransaction.__exit__(None) failure semantics); EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE two-phase prepare/commit and EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE compensation LATER, each design-first and separately authorized. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the contract + fail-closed preflight + NON_ATOMIC marker are PRODUCTION (live on the central execute() path and batch-gated); the four real classes are DECLARED-BUT-UNIMPLEMENTED (fail closed); the static probe is clean-room scaffolding.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-02","EH-S-02","DM-S-01"])
ADR_38=_adr(id="AD-38",context="r102-a (AD-37) shipped the EffectAtomicity contract and the NON_ATOMIC legacy bridge - classification, not repair - and recorded the staged roadmap: the PURE/STORE_LOCAL seam protocol NEXT, design-first, including explicit clean-path MutationTransaction.__exit__(None) failure semantics (class 1/2 success depends on clean-release durability). The Governor approved the r102-b design with five decisions: (1) confess-and-audit containment with NO restricted store handle yet; (2) a dedicated classified failed=True abort receipt in the EXISTING receipt shape, NO schema column; (3) one conformance-only pilot OR zero migrations plus a purpose-built gate, with NO production callsite migration; (4) clean-path RELEASE failure hardening as a REQUIRED precondition before relying on [effect + success] as a commit unit; (5) approve the core protocol - gate_admit a durable decision-before-effect receipt at depth 0, [effect + success] atomic through the seam, success written after effect, failure leaving gate_admit plus a structural abort rather than a false success, NON_ATOMIC unchanged, external classes still fail-closed, and NO global Invariant E law.",decision="r102-b wires the PURE and STORE_LOCAL effect classes onto the AD-34/36 deferred-commit seam, giving rollback-able effects a REAL atomic outcome transition, and hardens the seam's clean-path commit first. (1) CLEAN-PATH RELEASE FAILURE HARDENING (the precondition): MutationTransaction.__exit__(None) now wraps the clean RELEASE - on a RELEASE failure it attempts ROLLBACK TO + RELEASE to leave a clean, usable connection and raises a DISTINCT TransactionCommitError (a new exception); store.transaction()'s clean exit restores the Python-side frontier in a guard if the clean __exit__ raises, mirroring the AD-36 exception-path defensive restore. A commit/RELEASE failure is treated as a FAILED transition (fail-closed) - nothing durable, frontier restored, distinct error - and is NEVER reported as success. (2) execute() PREFLIGHT relaxed for the two rollback-able classes ONLY: PURE and STORE_LOCAL now PROCEED; an undeclared effect still fails closed before gate_admit, and EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE / EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE still fail closed (their protocols are later phases); NON_ATOMIC and no-effect ops keep the UNCHANGED legacy order. (3) ATOMIC OUTCOME for PURE/STORE_LOCAL: gate_admit is written and committed at depth 0 BEFORE the effect (the durable decision-before-effect receipt, NBER-1 preserved); then [effect() + success receipt] run INSIDE store.transaction() - the success receipt is written AFTER effect() returns (eliminating success-before-effect for these classes), and a STORE_LOCAL effect's store writes commit TOGETHER with the success receipt on clean RELEASE. (4) STRUCTURAL ABORT: on effect failure, success-receipt-write failure, or clean-path RELEASE failure, the seam rolls the whole outcome transition back (the effect's store writes AND the would-be success receipt persist nothing, frontier restored), and the kernel writes a durable structural abort receipt at depth 0 via _emit_effect_abort - a dedicated classified failed=True receipt in the EXISTING receipt shape (NO schema column), deterministic, carrying op/intent linkage, the effect_atomicity class, a classified abort_reason ('effect_failure' / 'success_receipt_failure' / 'commit_release_failure'), and the gate_admit h_r ('gate_admit_ref') as explicit linkage. It deliberately does NOT use protocol_error wording: it is the abort of an ADMITTED effect attempt, not malformed-protocol input rejected before admissibility (the FGA section 15.5 distinction). gate_admit + abort are durable, with NO false success. (5) CONTAINMENT = confess-and-audit (Governor decision 1): NO restricted transaction-scoped store handle this release. STORE_LOCAL asserts that the effect's durable mutations are store-local and flow ONLY through audited store surfaces; the seam guarantees rollback ONLY for those audited store mutations; external state touched by a STORE_LOCAL effect is a CALLER CONTRACT VIOLATION, not something the kernel has made atomic. Restricted handles are a later hardening phase. (6) PILOT (Governor decision 3): ZERO production callsite migrations - the 16 NON_ATOMIC callsites are UNCHANGED; the protocol is exercised only by conformance-only callsites inside the purpose-built effect_atomicity_class12_gate. (7) GATES: effect_atomicity_declaration_gate UPDATED - case (b) now fails closed ONLY for the external classes, and a new case (d) proves PURE/STORE_LOCAL PROCEED; a NEW effect_atomicity_class12_gate proves, with FRESH-CONNECTION checks, PURE success-after-effect, STORE_LOCAL atomic commit, failure leaving gate_admit + a classified structural abort with no false success, and the clean-path RELEASE-failure path (distinct error + frontier restore + nothing persists + commit_release_failure abort). (8) B4a EXTENDED (not loosened): execute() is positively audited as the THIRD seam-backed caller - it opens self._store.transaction() with no direct commit and no raw receipts INSERT, the success write executes INSIDE the seam, gate_admit precedes the seam, and the abort flows through _emit_effect_abort to self._store.write at depth 0; mutation-surface discipline is TIGHTENED with a third audited caller. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: transaction.py / store.py / kernel.py / the gates live outside law; the abort receipt and the marker live in parameters JSON (NO committed column); law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; r102->r103 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED: only PURE/STORE_LOCAL are wired; the external classes still fail closed; NO production migration; Invariant E is NOT formalized as law.",alternatives=["Introduce the restricted transaction-scoped store handle now (enforce-by-construction containment): NOT TAKEN (Governor decision 1) - a heavier contract change; r102-b proves the protocol seam first under confess-and-audit, leaving restricted handles to a later hardening phase.","Make the abort a new committed schema column or a new artifact type: REJECTED (Governor decision 2) - it fits the existing receipt shape in parameters JSON, so there is no schema/frame move.","Reuse protocol_error wording for the abort: REJECTED (Governor) - a structural abort of an ADMITTED effect is a different class from malformed protocol input rejected before admissibility (FGA 15.5); blurring them would lose the distinction the trail needs.","Migrate production NON_ATOMIC callsites to PURE/STORE_LOCAL in r102-b: REJECTED (Governor decision 3) - each migration is a per-callsite BEHAVIORAL change that needs separate review; r102-b wires the protocol and proves it via a purpose-built gate with zero production migrations.","Treat the clean-path RELEASE-failure hardening as optional or defer it: REJECTED (Governor decision 4) - relying on [effect + success] as a commit unit REQUIRES explicit clean-path failure semantics first; a silent RELEASE failure would otherwise leave the frontier advanced while nothing durably committed.","Formalize Invariant E as law now: DEFERRED - execute() still admits NON_ATOMIC and fails closed on the external classes, so a GLOBAL E claim would overclaim; consistent with the A/D/E wiring-precedes-formalization discipline, E becomes law only when the wiring covers the claim (it does not while NON_ATOMIC and external effects exist). A NARROW scoped class-1/2 atomicity invariant is a possible FUTURE option, explicitly not global E and not r102-b."],consequences="PURE and STORE_LOCAL effects now have a REAL atomic outcome transition: gate_admit is the durable decision-before-effect receipt at depth 0, and [effect + success receipt] commit-or-roll-back together through the seam with the success receipt written only AFTER effect() returns. A failed effect, a failed success-receipt write, or a clean-path RELEASE (commit) failure rolls the whole outcome transition back - the effect's store writes AND the would-be success receipt persist nothing (proven from a FRESH connection), a distinct TransactionCommitError surfaces on a commit failure, and the kernel records a durable, deterministic structural abort receipt (classified effect_failure / success_receipt_failure / commit_release_failure, carrying effect_atomicity and the gate_admit_ref) - leaving gate_admit + abort, NEVER a false success. r102-b makes the decision/outcome split from AD-37 REAL for rollback-able effects: it does not merely classify, it gives class-1/2 effects atomicity onto the audited seam. NOT CLAIMED: that NON_ATOMIC or external-class effects are atomic; that the kernel sandboxes a STORE_LOCAL effect (confess-and-audit - external state by a STORE_LOCAL effect is a caller violation, not kernel-made-atomic); global atomicity; Invariant E as law. CONTAINMENT is confess-and-audit (no restricted handle yet); the PILOT is zero production migrations (the 16 NON_ATOMIC callsites unchanged; the protocol proven by conformance-only callsites in effect_atomicity_class12_gate). FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (transaction.py/store.py/kernel.py are not law; the abort receipt and marker are parameters-JSON, not a committed column); genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added - the class-1/2 atomic outcome is a kernel contract wired onto the seam, not a law invariant; wiring precedes any future formalization); ADRs through AD-38 (36); gates 94 -> 95 (effect_atomicity_class12_gate; effect_atomicity_declaration_gate updated; B4a extended as a deep probe). r102->r103 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link. STAGED ROADMAP CONTINUES: PURE/STORE_LOCAL atomic NOW (r102-b); EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE two-phase prepare/commit and EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE compensation/saga LATER, each design-first and separately authorized; broad per-callsite NON_ATOMIC -> PURE/STORE_LOCAL migration is later, each authorized and gated; a narrow scoped class-1/2 atomicity invariant is a possible future formalization, not global E. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the clean-path RELEASE hardening, the class-1/2 atomic-outcome protocol, the structural abort, and the updated/new gates plus extended B4a are PRODUCTION (live on the central execute() path and gated); the external classes remain DECLARED-BUT-UNIMPLEMENTED (fail closed).",bound_invariants=["PERSIST-S-01","EH-S-02","DM-S-01"])
ADR_39=_adr(id="AD-39",context="r104 (frame-stationary cleanup, no ADR, CODEX stationary 22a51776) was accepted. The Governor authorized Path A first but NARROWLY: migrate ONE Group-1 conformance callsite from NON_ATOMIC to PURE, one real-effect callsite per release, each proven by a dedicated focused gate, with a short ADR when the classification enters the governed record. During Evidence-Before-Action analysis a requirements conflict was HALTED and reported (Fail Closed): the chosen first target, enforcement_gate, has TWO real-effect execute() callsites, not one - callsite A (gate=False, the effect never runs because admission refuses first) and callsite B (gate=True, the pure effect actually runs). The Governor resolved it - the cadence unit is a SINGLE real-effect callsite, migrate callsite B ONLY, leave callsite A NON_ATOMIC because it does not exercise the success path. Two candidates were classified by evidence: enforcement_gate (GK-S-01, the property 'effect runs iff gate admits') is ORDER-AGNOSTIC so the success-after-effect change is provably benign; will_coverage_gate (WILL-S-06, 'coverage precedes receipt precedes effect') is ABOUT receipt/effect ordering, so migrating its own fixture to PURE would introduce interpretive ambiguity over whether 'receipt' means gate_admit or the success receipt - REJECTED as the first target. The authorized analysis-only read/classify of transport/broker.py found BrokerClient.submit() is a PASS-THROUGH that relays a caller-supplied effect into kernel.execute(); it defines no effect of its own, so a hardcoded PURE/STORE_LOCAL there would be a FALSE classification - it stays NON_ATOMIC unless a later design propagates a caller-declared EffectAtomicity. cli.py write_charter_artifacts is external file writes (EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE territory), explicitly NOT a Path-A target.",decision="r105 migrates enforcement_gate callsite B (the gate=True admit case, whose pure effect actually runs) from NON_ATOMIC to PURE - the FIRST Path-A pilot, classification-by-evidence applied to one real-effect callsite. CLASSIFICATION EVIDENCE: the migrated effect is a local-list append (lambda: effect_admitted.append(True)); it writes NOTHING to the store (proven at runtime by the focused gate - running the effect advances no receipts) and touches no external state (by construction). It is therefore PURE under the r102-b confess-and-audit definition (durable mutations, if any, are store-local through audited surfaces; here there are none). PER-CALLSITE SEMANTIC CHANGE (called out, not silent): reclassifying NON_ATOMIC -> PURE changes this callsite's execution order from the legacy success-before-effect to the r103 atomic-outcome - gate_admit remains the durable decision-before-effect receipt at depth 0 (NBER-1 preserved), but the SUCCESS receipt is now written AFTER effect() returns, inside the seam, committing or rolling back with the effect. This is the intended r102-b/AD-38 protocol, now APPLIED to its first real callsite. CALLSITE A UNCHANGED: enforcement_gate's gate=False callsite keeps NON_ATOMIC - the gate refuses before the effect, the effect never runs, the success path is never reached; its class is moot and migrating it would add a callsite to the release with no atomicity exercised. DEDICATED FOCUSED GATE (Governor decision): pure_migration_r105_gate proves the per-callsite migration property on a FRESH file-backed connection - (1) the effect is store-pure by evidence (advances no receipts in isolation); (2) gate_admit is present before the effect runs (the effect observes gate_admit already written and zero success receipts); (3) success-after-effect (the effect observes no success receipt at the moment it runs, and exactly one exists afterward); (4) a forced effect failure leaves a durable classified structural abort (abort_reason effect_failure, effect_atomicity pure, gate_admit_ref present) and NO false success, with gate_admit still durably present; (5) all re-read on a fresh read-only connection. GK-S-01 is NOT modified in substance - enforcement_gate keeps asserting that gate=False blocks the effect and writes gate_refuse and that gate=True admits and runs the effect; the migration property lives in the dedicated gate, not buried in GK-S-01. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: the change is one effect_atomicity literal in a conformance gate plus a new conformance gate; law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; CODEX moves ONLY because this ADR is added; r104->r105 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED: exactly one real-effect callsite migrated; callsite A, will_coverage_gate, broker.py, and cli.py UNTOUCHED; NO external-class implementation; Invariant E NOT formalized as law.",alternatives=["Migrate BOTH enforcement_gate callsites in r105: REJECTED (Governor) - the cadence unit is a single real-effect callsite, and callsite A (gate=False) never runs its effect so it exercises no atomicity; bundling it would exceed one-callsite-per-release for no gain.","Use will_coverage_gate as the first target: REJECTED - WILL-S-06 is itself about receipt/effect ordering, so migrating its own fixture to PURE (success-after-effect) introduces interpretive ambiguity about whether 'receipt' means gate_admit or the success receipt; enforcement_gate's GK-S-01 is order-agnostic and the cleaner pilot.","Bury the migration proof inside GK-S-01: REJECTED (Governor) - GK-S-01 should keep asserting 'effect runs iff gate admits'; the per-callsite atomicity property is a DISTINCT claim and gets its own dedicated focused gate.","Migrate transport/broker.py or cli.py under Path A: REJECTED - broker.py relays caller-supplied effects of unknown class (a hardcoded PURE/STORE_LOCAL would be a false classification; it stays NON_ATOMIC pending a caller-declared-class API), and cli.py write_charter_artifacts is external file writes (EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE, not rollback-able).","Formalize Invariant E as law now: DEFERRED - execute() still admits NON_ATOMIC callsites and fails closed on the external classes, so a global E claim would overclaim; consistent with wiring-precedes-formalization, E becomes law only when the wiring covers the claim.","Migrate broadly (many NON_ATOMIC callsites at once): REJECTED (Governor) - one callsite per release, each with its own classification evidence, focused gate, and ADR; r105 is the first pilot on the safest order-agnostic conformance callsite."],consequences="The first Path-A callsite migration is COMPLETE: enforcement_gate callsite B now runs its pure effect through the AD-34/36 seam under the r103 atomic-outcome (gate_admit decision-before-effect at depth 0; [effect + success] committed together with the success written after effect; a forced failure leaving gate_admit + a durable classified structural abort and no false success). The migration methodology is PROVEN end-to-end on one real-effect callsite and is repeatable: classify by evidence, migrate one callsite, prove with a dedicated focused gate, record the classification in an ADR. The standing NON_ATOMIC real-effect callsite count drops by one (the production cli.py/broker.py callsites are NOT Path-A targets - external and relay respectively - so full NON_ATOMIC retirement still requires Path B). NOT CLAIMED: that callsite A, NON_ATOMIC, or external-class effects are atomic; global atomicity; Invariant E as law. GK-S-01's assertion is unchanged in substance. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (the change is one effect_atomicity literal in a conformance gate plus a new conformance gate; no law, schema, or legend touched); genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added - the migration applies the existing class-1/2 contract to a callsite; wiring precedes any future formalization); ADRs through AD-39 (37); gates 95 -> 96 (pure_migration_r105_gate). r104->r105 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link; CODEX moves only because AD-39 is added. STAGED ROADMAP CONTINUES: one Path-A conformance-callsite migration per release, each evidence-classified, gated, and ADR-recorded; transport/broker.py needs a caller-declared-class API design before it can move; cli.py and the external classes are Path B (design-first, separately authorized); a narrow scoped class-1/2 atomicity invariant remains a possible future formalization, not global E. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the migrated callsite and the focused gate are PRODUCTION-GATED conformance; the external classes remain DECLARED-BUT-UNIMPLEMENTED (fail closed); callsite A remains the explicit NON_ATOMIC bridge.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-01","PERSIST-S-01","EH-S-02"])
ADR_40=_adr(id="AD-40",context="r105 (first Path-A pilot, AD-39) and the r106 broker caller-declared-class API design pass were accepted. The r106 design classified the transport/broker.py relay defect: the broker SILENTLY chose NON_ATOMIC (a hardcode at line 141) for an arbitrary caller-supplied effect, so the broker - not the caller - was the declarer. The Governor authorized r107 to implement the broker propagation cutover under four r106 decisions: (1) a structured GovernedRequest carrier as the target shape, not a loose optional parameter beside a legacy signature, minimal for r107; (2) in-process LocalBrokerServer only, the isolated / named-op model design-reserved; (3) registry defaults deferred, every effectful broker request carrying an explicit caller declaration, a future registry default never silently overriding a caller declaration and a mismatch failing closed; (4) a fail-closed cutover that removes the hardcode and updates in-tree effectful callers in the same release with no transition default. Evidence-Before-Action found NO in-tree caller passes an effect to the broker - both submit() callers (ugk/transport/agent.py ugk_govern and ugk/migration/abletools.py govern) are no-effect (op/authority/parameters only) - so the cutover breaks no production caller and the effectful broker path was previously unexercised in-tree.",decision="r107 makes the CALLER the declarer of effect atomicity at the broker boundary and the broker a faithful conduit. (1) ABI/INTERFACE CHANGE (called out, not silent - approved as r106 decision 1): a structured GovernedRequest dataclass (op, authority, parameters, intent, jurisdiction, gate, effect, effect_atomicity) becomes the carrier; the abstract BrokerClient.submit() signature changes from submit(op, authority, parameters, intent, jurisdiction) to submit(request: GovernedRequest), and LocalBrokerServer.submit() is rewritten to match. The caller-declared request.effect_atomicity is propagated VERBATIM to kernel.execute(); the broker never defaults, downgrades, or invents a class. (2) THE LINE-141 NON_ATOMIC HARDCODE IS REMOVED - the broker no longer silently classifies a caller's effect. (3) FAIL-CLOSED CUTOVER: an effect present with NO declaration (request.effect is not None and request.effect_atomicity is None) is refused AT THE BROKER with a RECEIPTED refusal - the broker writes a classified failed=True receipt (broker_refused=True, refuse_reason=missing_effect_atomicity_declaration) via its Ring-2 chain-append authority and returns admitted=False (NBER-1: refusal is first-class and receipted, not silent). This differs deliberately from the kernel zero-mutation undeclared-effect preflight (AD-37): the broker records its OWN discipline refusal before execute() is reached. (4) NO-EFFECT EXEMPTION PRESERVED: request.effect is None proceeds with no declaration needed (the two in-tree callers, both no-effect, are unaffected). (5) EXPLICIT NON_ATOMIC remains the legacy bridge - it proceeds under the unchanged legacy order with the marker, but only as an EXPLICIT caller declaration (the choice moves from broker to caller). (6) EXPLICIT PURE/STORE_LOCAL propagate to the r103 atomic-outcome seam. (7) UNKNOWN OR UNIMPLEMENTED CLASSES (today EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE, EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE) fail closed: the kernel preflight raises ProtocolError (zero mutation) which the broker catches and surfaces as admitted=False with no receipt, consistent with the existing protocol-error handling. (8) THE TWO NO-EFFECT CALLERS (agent.py, abletools.py) are ported to GovernedRequest in the SAME release (fail-closed cutover, no transition default). Proven by broker_propagation_gate on fresh file-backed connections: no-effect admitted; explicit PURE propagates and the effect runs with exactly one non-failed success receipt; missing declaration yields a receipted failed broker_refused refusal with NO false success; explicit NON_ATOMIC proceeds; both external classes fail closed with no receipt. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (the change lives in transport/broker.py plus two callers plus a new conformance gate; broker.py is substrate, not law); NO amendment; CODEX moves ONLY because this ADR is added; r105->r107 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED to r106 decisions 2-4: in-process LocalBrokerServer only; NO isolated broker, NO named-op registry, NO registry-default class, NO external-class implementation, NO production effect migration beyond the broker contract change itself, NO global Invariant E law.",alternatives=["Widen submit() with a loose effect_atomicity parameter beside the legacy signature instead of a carrier: REJECTED (Governor decision 1) - the declaration belongs WITH the governed request; a structured GovernedRequest is the target shape, not an optional kwarg hanging off a legacy signature.","Keep a broker-side default and let callers override: REJECTED (Governor decision 4) - a default IS the silent classification the defect names; the cutover is fail-closed, the hardcode is removed, NON_ATOMIC available only as an explicit declaration.","Treat the missing-declaration refusal as zero-mutation like the kernel preflight (no receipt): NOT CHOSEN (Governor scope) - the broker NBER-1 contract makes refusal first-class and receipted; the broker records its discipline refusal with a failed receipt, distinct from the kernel pre-admissibility protocol rejection.","Implement the isolated broker / named-op registry / registry-default class now: REJECTED (Governor decisions 2-3) - design-reserved; r107 is the in-process joint only. A future named-op registry default must never silently override an explicit caller declaration, and a mismatch must fail closed.","Migrate a production effect through the broker in r107: REJECTED (Governor) - r107 changes the broker API CONTRACT only; no production effect is reclassified beyond the contract change. The external classes remain declared-but-unimplemented (fail closed).","Formalize Invariant E as law now: DEFERRED - execute() still admits NON_ATOMIC and fails closed on the external classes; even with the broker now propagating, a global E claim would overclaim. E becomes law only when the wiring covers the claim, and even then at most as a scoped, non-global claim."],consequences="The broker boundary is now HONEST about effect atomicity: the caller declares, the broker propagates verbatim, the kernel enforces, and the broker never chooses a class on the caller's behalf. The line-141 NON_ATOMIC hardcode - the r106-named defect - is gone. An effectful broker request with no declaration fails closed with a receipted refusal; a no-effect request is exempt; explicit NON_ATOMIC is the (now caller-chosen) legacy bridge; explicit PURE reaches the r103 atomic-outcome; unimplemented external classes fail closed. The structured GovernedRequest carrier is the stable shape future brokers (isolated / named-op) will implement, so future class routing needs no broker change. NOT CLAIMED: that an isolated broker, a named-op registry, a registry-default class, or any external class is implemented; that any production effect was reclassified; global atomicity; Invariant E as law. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (the change is transport/broker.py plus two no-effect caller ports plus broker_propagation_gate; broker.py is substrate); genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added - the cutover wires caller-declared propagation into the broker; wiring precedes any future formalization); ADRs through AD-40 (38); gates 96 -> 97 (broker_propagation_gate). r105->r107 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link; CODEX moves only because AD-40 is added. VERIFICATION SURFACE: r107 introduces the FIRST legitimate dynamic declaration seam (the broker propagating effect + class verbatim from a GovernedRequest), and the static effect_declaration_probe is updated to recognize that EXACT propagated-declaration pattern (effect=request.effect AND effect_atomicity=request.effect_atomicity) as a propagated declaration, NOT an unknown class - a prior probe run misread request.effect_atomicity as an unknown class named effect_atomicity and wrongly implied 'kernel fails these closed', which is false for a propagation callsite. The refinement preserves every hard guarantee: undeclared real-effect callsites still FAIL; genuine unknown literal enum/classes still WARNING; literal class counts and the NON_ATOMIC hardcode-removal count shift stay visible; and recognition is narrow (it does not bless any attribute named effect_atomicity) so a future accidental dynamic callsite still earns recognition explicitly. STAGED ROADMAP CONTINUES: the broker now propagates a caller-declared class; the isolated broker / named-op registry model remains design-reserved; cli.py charter-write stays a Path-B gray-area classification problem (atomic rename); Path B EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE remains designed-not-implemented; further Path-A per-callsite PURE migrations remain available. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the broker propagation path and broker_propagation_gate are PRODUCTION-GATED conformance; the external classes remain DECLARED-BUT-UNIMPLEMENTED (fail closed); explicit NON_ATOMIC remains the caller-chosen bridge; the isolated broker remains a design-reserved stub posture (is_isolated() False).",bound_invariants=["EH-S-02","PERSIST-S-01","GK-S-02"])
ADR_41=_adr(id="AD-41",context="r107 (broker propagation cutover, AD-40) was accepted as the broker propagation joint - not a production effect migration, not an Invariant E claim. The Governor authorized r108 as the next Path-A one-callsite migration (NOT Path B), to prove the post-r107 world still behaves under the ordinary Path-A cadence before any external-irreversible work. Same r105 discipline: classify first by evidence, halt on ambiguity, migrate exactly one real-effect callsite, record a short ADR, add/extend a focused gate, keep law/schema/legend stationary, no production effect migration, no external-class implementation, no isolated broker or named-op registry, no global Invariant E law. Evidence-Before-Action classified the 8 conformance-internal NON_ATOMIC real-effect callsites: nber1_gate (UL-S-02) is ORDER-CONTRADICTORY - it asserts the SUCCESS receipt is written BEFORE effect (success-before-effect, the legacy order), which the r103 PURE atomic-outcome (success-after-effect) would both break and misrepresent - REJECTED, its NON_ATOMIC is load-bearing (the will_coverage_gate-class trap, classified rather than forced); canary_gate (CR-S-02 / CR-04) is SEMANTICALLY MUDDY - its effect represents 'ungoverned I/O' for the CR-04 opacity canary, so declaring it PURE (store-pure) contradicts the canary's point - REJECTED; effect_atomicity_declaration_gate is SELF-REFERENTIAL - it is the gate that tests the NON_ATOMIC bridge marker - REJECTED; application_ops_gate is order-agnostic and store-pure but heavy (warrants, ceremony, GOVERNANCE_OPS injection, GovernanceNotFounded standalone) - DEFERRED; enforcement_gate gate=False callsite and admission_gate refusal-path callsite are refusal-path (the effect never runs, class moot) - SKIPPED, as r105 left enforcement_gate callsite A; will_coverage_gate remains the already-rejected order-muddy WILL-S-06 fixture. admission_gate's ADMIT-PATH callsite is the safest clean candidate.",decision="r108 migrates admission_gate's ADMIT-PATH callsite (gate=True, whose store-pure effect actually runs) from NON_ATOMIC to PURE - the SECOND Path-A pilot, classification-by-evidence applied to one real-effect callsite, proving the post-r107 (post-broker-cutover) world still behaves under the ordinary Path-A cadence. CLASSIFICATION EVIDENCE: the migrated effect is a store-READING probe (it reads receipts_by_op('gate_admit') and appends to a local list); it writes NOTHING to the store (proven at runtime by the focused gate - running it in isolation advances no receipts) and touches no external state (by construction). It is therefore PURE under the r102-b confess-and-audit definition (durable mutations, if any, are store-local through audited surfaces; here there are none, and reads are pure). PER-CALLSITE SEMANTIC CHANGE (called out, not silent): reclassifying NON_ATOMIC -> PURE changes this callsite's execution order from the legacy success-before-effect to the r103 atomic-outcome - gate_admit remains the durable decision-before-effect receipt at depth 0 (NBER-1 preserved), but the SUCCESS receipt is now written AFTER effect() returns, inside the seam, committing or rolling back with the effect. ORDER-AGNOSTIC BY EVIDENCE: GK-S-02 (admission_gate's property: W/G/E - gate fires before effect; the gate_admit receipt is present when the effect fires; refusal blocks the effect) asserts ONLY gate_admit + gate ordering, which r103 PRESERVES; NONE of its assertions depend on success-before vs success-after-effect, so the success-after-effect change is provably benign - admission_gate still PASSES under PURE. REFUSAL-PATH CALLSITE UNCHANGED: admission_gate's gate=False callsite keeps NON_ATOMIC - the gate refuses before the effect, the effect never runs, the success path is never reached; its class is moot. DEDICATED FOCUSED GATE: pure_migration_r108_gate proves the per-callsite migration property on a FRESH file-backed connection for the admission-gate store-READING effect SHAPE - (1) store-pure by evidence (reading advances no receipts); (2) gate_admit present before the effect runs; (3) success-after-effect (no success receipt at the moment the effect runs, exactly one afterward); (4) a forced effect failure leaves a durable classified structural abort (abort_reason effect_failure, effect_atomicity pure, gate_admit_ref present) and NO false success, with gate_admit still durably present; (5) all re-read on a fresh read-only connection. GK-S-02 is NOT modified in substance - admission_gate keeps asserting W/G/E; the migration property lives in the dedicated gate, not buried in GK-S-02. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: the change is one effect_atomicity literal in a conformance gate plus a new conformance gate; law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; CODEX moves ONLY because this ADR is added; r107->r108 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED: exactly one real-effect callsite migrated; admission_gate refusal-path callsite, nber1_gate, canary_gate, will_coverage_gate, effect_atomicity_declaration_gate, application_ops_gate, and the production/external callsites UNTOUCHED; NO production effect migration; NO external-class implementation; NO isolated broker or named-op registry; Invariant E NOT formalized as law.",alternatives=["Migrate nber1_gate (UL-S-02): REJECTED - nber1_gate asserts the SUCCESS receipt is written BEFORE effect (success-before-effect, the legacy order); PURE writes success AFTER effect, which would BOTH break the gate AND misrepresent the property. Its NON_ATOMIC callsite is load-bearing - the will_coverage_gate-class order-contradictory trap, classified rather than forced (the Governor's explicit halt-on-order-muddy instruction).","Migrate canary_gate (CR-S-02 / CR-04): REJECTED - its effect represents 'ungoverned I/O' for the CR-04 opacity canary; declaring it PURE (store-pure) contradicts the canary's whole point (effects whose internals are opaque). Order-agnostic on receipt count, but semantically muddy.","Migrate effect_atomicity_declaration_gate: REJECTED - it is the gate that TESTS the NON_ATOMIC bridge marker; migrating its own fixture would muddy what it asserts (self-referential).","Migrate application_ops_gate: DEFERRED - order-agnostic and store-pure effect, but heavy machinery (warrants, ceremony, GOVERNANCE_OPS injection, GovernanceNotFounded standalone); admission_gate's admit-path callsite is the safer minimal pilot.","Migrate the admission_gate refusal-path callsite (or enforcement_gate gate=False): REJECTED - gate=False callsites never run their effect, so they exercise no atomicity (class moot), exactly as r105 left enforcement_gate callsite A.","Migrate a production or external callsite (cli.py charter-write, examples, execution_adapter): REJECTED - external/production effects are not Path-A targets (cli.py charter-write is external file writes; the broker relay is now caller-declared via r107 but carries no effect in-tree); Path B (design-first, separately authorized) covers external irreversible effects.","Formalize Invariant E as law now: DEFERRED - NON_ATOMIC real-effect callsites remain and execute() fails closed on the external classes, so a global E claim would overclaim; wiring precedes formalization."],consequences="The SECOND Path-A callsite migration is COMPLETE and the post-r107 world is shown to behave under the ordinary Path-A cadence: admission_gate's admit-path callsite now runs its store-pure effect through the AD-34/36 seam under the r103 atomic-outcome (gate_admit decision-before-effect at depth 0; [effect + success] committed together with the success written after effect; a forced failure leaving gate_admit + a durable classified structural abort and no false success). The migration methodology - classify by evidence, migrate one callsite, prove with a dedicated focused gate, record in an ADR - is now PROVEN on a second, order-agnostic conformance callsite, and the evidence discipline correctly REJECTED the order-contradictory nber1_gate rather than forcing it. The standing NON_ATOMIC real-effect callsite count drops by one. NOT CLAIMED: that the refusal-path callsite, the rejected/deferred gates, NON_ATOMIC, or external-class effects are atomic; global atomicity; Invariant E as law. GK-S-02's assertion is unchanged in substance. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (the change is one effect_atomicity literal in a conformance gate plus a new conformance gate; no law, schema, or legend touched); genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added - the migration applies the existing class-1/2 contract to a callsite; wiring precedes any future formalization); ADRs through AD-41 (39); gates 97 -> 98 (pure_migration_r108_gate). r107->r108 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link; CODEX moves only because AD-41 is added. STAGED ROADMAP CONTINUES: one Path-A conformance-callsite migration per release, each evidence-classified, gated, and ADR-recorded; the order-contradictory (nber1_gate), order-muddy (will_coverage_gate), semantically-muddy (canary_gate), and self-referential (effect_atomicity_declaration_gate) gates are NOT Path-A targets; application_ops_gate is a possible future candidate (heavier); cli.py charter-write and the external classes are Path B (design-first, separately authorized); the isolated broker / named-op registry remains design-reserved; a narrow scoped class-1/2 atomicity invariant remains a possible future formalization, not global E. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the migrated callsite and pure_migration_r108_gate are PRODUCTION-GATED conformance; the external classes remain DECLARED-BUT-UNIMPLEMENTED (fail closed); the refusal-path callsite remains the explicit NON_ATOMIC moot-class case.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-02","PERSIST-S-01","EH-S-02"])
ADR_42=_adr(id="AD-42",context="r108 (admission_gate admit-path PURE migration, AD-41) was accepted; the r109 NON_ATOMIC cartography and the r110 ExecutionAdapter caller-declared-class design pass followed. r109 found the clean conformance Path-A vein essentially MINED OUT - the two safe stones (enforcement_gate callsite B at r105, admission_gate admit-path at r108) are migrated, and the remaining conformance callsites are order-load-bearing (nber1_gate), order-muddy (will_coverage_gate), semantically-muddy (canary_gate), self-referential (effect_atomicity_declaration_gate), refusal-path/class-moot, or external/Path-B - and identified the GRBSA ExecutionAdapter (tools/grbsa/grbsa_runtime/execution_adapter.py) as the important new finding: a SECOND relay joint repeating the pre-r107 broker defect. r110 classified it - the adapter is BOTH a legitimate receipt-bound OBSERVER (it observes the real execute() outcome and mints no receipt; ratified invariants: no ugk/ change, no kernel.py change, never originates authority, never founds the kernel, writes no receipt, gate refusal first-class) AND a RELAY whose run() at line 112 HARDCODED EffectAtomicity.NON_ATOMIC for an arbitrary caller-supplied effect, so the adapter - not the caller - was the declarer. The r110 conclusion (accepted): the r107 principle applies (caller declares, relay propagates, kernel enforces); the API shape is a constructor keyword effect_atomicity (the adapter constructor already IS the call spec, so the declaration rides with it - a deliberate divergence from the broker GovernedRequest carrier); fail-closed for a missing declaration; and the g5 direct-vs-adapter equivalence stays apples-to-apples if the atomicity class is declared once and fed to both views. The Governor authorized r111 as the narrow second-relay cutover, to HALT if the g5 equivalence could not remain apples-to-apples.",decision="r111 makes the CALLER the declarer of effect atomicity at the GRBSA ExecutionAdapter boundary and the adapter a faithful relay, mirroring the r107 broker cutover at the second relay joint. (1) ABI/INTERFACE CHANGE (called out, not silent - r110 design accepted): ExecutionAdapter.__init__ gains an effect_atomicity keyword (Optional, default None) beside the existing effect keyword, and the effect default changes from a no-op lambda to the TRUE None sentinel ('no effect'). self.effect_atomicity is propagated VERBATIM to kernel.execute() at the former hardcode site; the adapter never defaults, downgrades, or invents a class. (2) THE LINE-112 NON_ATOMIC HARDCODE IS REMOVED - the adapter no longer silently classifies a caller's effect. (3) FAIL-CLOSED ADAPTER-VS-BROKER RECEIPT DISTINCTION (the central r111 semantic): a caller-supplied effect with NO declaration (self.effect is not None and self.effect_atomicity is None) is refused BEFORE execute() is called, but - because the adapter has NO chain-append authority by ratified invariant (it observes, it does not mint) - the refusal is a RETURNED refused ExecutionReceipt envelope (gate_outcome 'refuse', refusal_class 'UndeclaredEffect', execution_success False) with ZERO written receipts and NO execute() call, NOT a receipted refusal. This is the deliberate distinction from the r107 broker, whose missing-declaration refusal is a RECEIPTED failed=True row written via the broker's Ring-2 chain-append authority: same caller-declares principle, different receipt posture, because the broker has chain-append authority and the adapter does not. (4) NO-EFFECT EXEMPTION: self.effect is None proceeds with no declaration needed (the kernel no-effect exemption applies). (5) EXPLICIT NON_ATOMIC remains the caller-chosen legacy bridge; EXPLICIT PURE/STORE_LOCAL propagate to the r103 atomic-outcome seam (a failing PURE effect reaches the kernel's classified structural abort - abort_reason 'effect_failure', effect_atomicity 'pure' - the kernel re-raising the effect exception afterward, which the adapter PROPAGATES as a thin observer of effect failures; it does not swallow them). (6) EXTERNAL/UNIMPLEMENTED DECLARED CLASSES (EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE, EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE) propagate to execute(), whose preflight raises ProtocolError with ZERO mutation and NO receipt; the adapter now CATCHES ProtocolError and surfaces it as a first-class refused envelope (refusal_class 'ProtocolError', no written receipt), consistent with the broker's external-class handling and distinct from the missing-declaration UndeclaredEffect case. (7) THE SIX IN-TREE ADAPTER CONSTRUCTION SITES (g5_execution_adapter_gate: the positive-control adapter_execute, the gate-refusal neg-i, the unfounded neg-ii, the authority-origination neg-iii, the posture-op neg-iv; and category_separation_gate) are updated to DECLARE explicitly, ALL preserving NON_ATOMIC - the point here is the relay/API comparison, NOT a Path-A migration (the g5 effects' store-purity is deliberately NOT reclassified). The gate-refusal and unfounded negative controls MUST declare NON_ATOMIC so they reach their intended GateRefusal / GovernanceNotFounded refusal rather than the new UndeclaredEffect refusal; the authority/posture negative controls refuse at _admissibility() BEFORE the declaration check, so their declaration is moot but supplied for uniformity. (8) g5 COMPARISON PRESERVED (the r110 satisfiable constraint, the halt condition - which did NOT fire): g5 declares the atomicity class ONCE (CLS = EffectAtomicity.NON_ATOMIC) and feeds it to the adapter side; the direct-execute baseline uses the SAME class as a static literal pinned to CLS by a module-load assertion. The probe recognizes effect_atomicity only as a static literal or a recognized propagation seam at an execute() callsite by design, so the direct baseline stays a literal while the adapter constructions - which the probe does NOT scan - read CLS; a bare CLS at the scanned direct callsite would register as an unknown class, hence the literal-pinned-to-CLS shape. The equivalence holds because the atomicity class is INVISIBLE to the Receipt-Sufficiency comparison (admit + failed + receipts-written shape are identical for NON_ATOMIC and the others) and 'same call, two views' is preserved by construction (both sides carry the same class). The g5 gate PASSES all ten checks after the cutover. (9) FOCUSED GATE: adapter_atomicity_propagation_gate (a GRBSA TOOL gate, NOT a ugk/conformance gate and NOT a member of the G6 fixed aggregate set; run DIRECTLY by the certification) proves via a kernel.execute spy that captures the propagated class - no-effect exempt (class None, succeeds); explicit NON_ATOMIC bridge (propagated verbatim, succeeds); explicit PURE reaches the r103 atomic abort (no false success); missing declaration returns a refused envelope with NO written receipt and NO execute() call (not silently defaulted to NON_ATOMIC); external class fails closed through the kernel preflight (ProtocolError, zero mutation); and across all classes the adapter never defaults, downgrades, or invents the class. (10) VERIFICATION SURFACE: the static effect_declaration_probe gains recognition of a SECOND propagation seam - the adapter's effect=self.effect AND effect_atomicity=self.effect_atomicity - recognized as narrowly as the r107 broker's effect=request.effect AND effect_atomicity=request.effect_atomicity (any other dynamic value still earns recognition explicitly). After the cutover the probe is clean: NON_ATOMIC literal count drops by one (the line-112 hardcode removed), propagated declarations rise from one to two (broker + adapter seams), zero unknown classes, zero undeclared real-effect callsites. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: the change lives in tools/grbsa/grbsa_runtime/execution_adapter.py, tools/grbsa/g5_execution_adapter_gate.py, tools/grbsa/category_separation_gate.py, tools/effect_declaration_probe.py, and a new tools/grbsa/adapter_atomicity_propagation_gate.py - ALL OUTSIDE ugk/ (the adapter's ratified invariant forbids any ugk/ change); the ONLY ugk/ touch is this ADR in adr.py; law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; CODEX moves ONLY because this ADR is added; r108->r111 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED: in-process GRBSA ExecutionAdapter only; NO Path B implementation; NO application_ops_gate migration; NO cli.py charter-write change; NO isolated broker; NO named-op registry; NO registry defaults; NO external-class implementation; NO global Invariant E law.",alternatives=["Widen ExecutionAdapter with a GovernedRequest carrier like the broker instead of a constructor keyword: REJECTED (r110 design) - the adapter constructor already IS the call spec (it bundles op/authority/parameters/gate/effect), so the declaration rides with it as a keyword; reusing GovernedRequest would restructure the constructor for no benefit.","Make the adapter's missing-declaration refusal a RECEIPTED failed row like the broker: REJECTED - the adapter has NO chain-append authority by ratified invariant (it observes, it mints nothing); a receipted refusal would violate that invariant. A returned refused envelope with no written receipt is the authority-correct fail-closed for an observer.","Migrate the g5 adapter effects to PURE while declaring (treat the cutover as a Path-A migration): REJECTED - r111 is the relay/API cutover; the g5 effects' store-purity is not the point, and reclassifying them would conflate the second-relay joint with a Path-A pilot. The six sites preserve NON_ATOMIC.","Route the g5 direct-execute baseline's class through the CLS symbol too (full 'declared once' via one symbol at every callsite): NOT TAKEN - the effect-declaration probe recognizes effect_atomicity only as a static literal or a recognized propagation seam at an execute() callsite (a deliberate static-recognizability property); a bare CLS at the scanned direct callsite would register as an unknown class. The direct baseline therefore stays a literal pinned to CLS by a module-load assertion, which guards drift (a CLS change without the matching literal change fails loudly) while keeping the probe clean.","Add the focused gate to the ugk/conformance registry or the G6 aggregate set: REJECTED - the adapter is GRBSA tooling, not ugk/conformance; a conformance gate for it would be a category mismatch and a ugk/ change beyond adr.py. It is a GRBSA tool gate run directly by the certification.","Catch the external-class ProtocolError and convert it to an UndeclaredEffect refusal: REJECTED - an external/unimplemented DECLARED class is a different fail-closed case from a MISSING declaration; the adapter surfaces ProtocolError as its own refusal_class, preserving the distinction.","Formalize Invariant E as law now: DEFERRED - NON_ATOMIC real-effect callsites and external-class fail-closed remain, so a global E claim would overclaim; wiring precedes formalization."],consequences="The GRBSA ExecutionAdapter boundary is now HONEST about effect atomicity: the caller declares, the adapter propagates verbatim, the kernel enforces, and the adapter never chooses a class on the caller's behalf - the second relay joint closed, mirroring the r107 broker cutover. The line-112 NON_ATOMIC hardcode - the r110-named defect - is gone. A caller-supplied effect with no declaration fails closed as a RETURNED refused ExecutionReceipt envelope with NO written receipt and NO execute() call (the adapter-vs-broker receipt distinction: the broker receipts its refusal via chain-append authority, the adapter cannot and does not); a no-effect call is exempt; explicit NON_ATOMIC is the caller-chosen bridge; explicit PURE reaches the r103 atomic-outcome; an external/unimplemented class fails closed through the kernel preflight (ProtocolError, zero mutation), surfaced as a refused envelope. The OBSERVER role is untouched (the adapter still mints no receipt and observes the real execute() outcome). The g5 direct-vs-adapter equivalence remains apples-to-apples ('same call, two views' - the class declared once and fed to both, invisible to the Receipt-Sufficiency comparison), so the halt condition did NOT fire. NOT CLAIMED: that an isolated broker, a named-op registry, a registry-default class, or any external class is implemented; that any production effect was reclassified (the six adapter sites preserve NON_ATOMIC; the cutover is the relay/API contract, not a Path-A migration); global atomicity; Invariant E as law. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (the change is in tools/ - the adapter, g5, category_separation, the probe, and a new GRBSA tool gate; the adapter forbids any ugk/ change, so the only ugk/ touch is this ADR); genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added - the cutover wires caller-declared propagation into the adapter; wiring precedes any future formalization); ADRs through AD-42 (40); gates stay 98 (the focused gate is a GRBSA tool gate run directly by the certification, not a ugk/conformance gate). r108->r111 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link; CODEX moves only because AD-42 is added. VERIFICATION SURFACE: the static effect_declaration_probe now recognizes the adapter's self.effect + self.effect_atomicity propagation seam as narrowly as the r107 broker seam; after the cutover the probe is clean (NON_ATOMIC literal count down one, propagated declarations one to two, zero unknown classes, zero undeclared). STAGED ROADMAP CONTINUES: both relay joints (broker r107, adapter r111) now propagate a caller-declared class; the isolated broker / named-op registry remains design-reserved; application_ops_gate is a possible (heavier) future Path-A candidate; cli.py charter-write and the external classes are Path B (design-first, separately authorized); a narrow scoped class-1/2 atomicity invariant remains a possible future formalization, not global E. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the adapter propagation path and adapter_atomicity_propagation_gate are PRODUCTION-GATED GRBSA tooling; the external classes remain DECLARED-BUT-UNIMPLEMENTED (fail closed); explicit NON_ATOMIC remains the caller-chosen bridge.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-02","EH-S-02","PERSIST-S-01"])
ADR_43=_adr(id="AD-43",context="r111 (GRBSA ExecutionAdapter caller-declared-class cutover, AD-42) was accepted; both relay joints (broker r107, adapter r111) now propagate a caller-declared class. The r112 EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE pre-implementation plan was delivered and PARKED (design-only, for later implementation; not relabeled). The Governor then flagged the turn-by-turn certification friction observed across releases - rediscovering tool paths, setsid launches whose launching shell timed out and looked like job failure, and manual polling - as TOOLING DEBT, not an architecture flaw, and re-prioritized building a certification handle BEFORE further protocol work. A shared external proposal floated a canonical-cert bypass to save turns; this was REJECTED in analysis (a canonical release without proof is not canonical; the irreversible-effect work is the worst place to bypass; the irreducible deep cert is non-blocking if launched correctly). The Governor authorized r113 (release-cert orchestrator DESIGN, design-only) and then r114 (the IMPLEMENTATION) under explicit decisions: thin recorder not judge; gates remain authoritative; the manifest summarizes raw evidence and does not replace proof; the first orchestrator release cannot certify itself (bootstrap); the environment fingerprint must be concrete not hand-waved; --quick is an iteration lane (not acceptance, not continuity, not a canonical release) with full B1-B4 reserved for the canonical mint; both layers ship in ONE governed r114 staged internally (launcher -> orchestrator -> self-test gate), NOT an ungoverned quick-win; and NO canonical-release bypass.",decision="r114 implements the release-certification orchestrator as governed EVIDENTIARY tooling, staged launcher -> orchestrator -> self-test gate, all under tools/release/. (1) run_detached.py: a TRUE detached launcher (subprocess.Popen start_new_session, close_fds, stdin from /dev/null, stdout/stderr to a log) that prints PID/log/status and EXITS IMMEDIATELY, so a harness timeout on the launching shell can never be mistaken for a job failure; it captures the detached job's exit code DURABLY in an atomic sidecar status file (write-temp + os.replace) and a poll helper reports RUNNING / DONE <rc> / LOST (LOST = pid dead with no status, a fail-closed condition); the launcher participates in EVIDENCE PRODUCTION (its launch and completion records feed the manifest). (2) certify_release.py: a THIN-RECORDER orchestrator that runs the EXISTING certification surface against the EXTRACTED archive (clean-room: the archive's own tools certify the archive's own ugk/) and emits a machine-readable EVIDENCE MANIFEST. A check's verdict is the check's OWN exit code; where a check is not a single exit-code gate (frame stationarity, ugk-confinement diff, no-drift, in-archive attestation) the orchestrator performs only a MECHANICAL comparison whose computed-vs-expected inputs are RECORDED so the verdict is re-derivable - it makes NO semantic judgment, decides nothing about what the correct frame IS (the expected frame is an input), and NEVER mints, re-attests, re-pins CODEX, or writes governance artifacts (the closure record, continuity surfaces, ADRs, and CODEX remain human/governed; the orchestrator emits evidence the Governor acts on). PHASES: --quick (fast structural green - hygiene, frame, verify_release, probe, focused gates, b4a, attestation, ugk-confinement, no-drift; the ITERATION LANE, explicitly NOT acceptance); --deep (--quick plus G6 and the 8 cgproj gates); --compose (the continuity composition over all links); and full B1-B4 (the canonical clean-room cert = quick + deep + compose). HASH-BOUND --resume reuses a cached PASS ONLY IF archive sha256, the check's tool sha256, the exact command, the env fingerprint, and the orchestrator sha256 all match; any mismatch discards the stale verdict and re-runs. CONCRETE ENV FINGERPRINT: sha256 over a canonical field set {python version, python implementation, platform system/machine, PYTHONHASHSEED pinned to 0 for every subprocess, LANG, LC_ALL, TZ} with the cleartext retained in the manifest. PATH PREFLIGHT asserts the repo root, verify_release.sh, proof_model_b.py, the focused/G6 gates, the 8 cgproj gates, the hygiene checker, the CODEX hash file, and the archive under test; any miss is HOLD(preflight) and nothing else runs. FAIL-CLOSED: missing tool/path, a check non-zero exit (FAIL), a phase exceeding its max budget (HOLD timeout), a lost detached job (HOLD), a dirty extract (source files not matching archive content, pycache excluded), an archive/tool/env/orchestrator hash mismatch on resume, or unexpected output (exit 0 but a required marker absent) all yield HOLD/FAIL - never an inferred PASS; aggregate PASS requires every check PASS (justified SKIPPED, e.g. no-drift with no worktree, does not block). RESOURCE-AWARE SCHEDULING (the first-use lesson, recorded): heavy detached checks (G6, the 8 cgproj gates, and --compose) are run SERIALLY by the orchestrator (launched and polled to completion one at a time) and are NEVER blindly co-scheduled at maximum concurrency; effective concurrency is 1, with --max-concurrency as a recorded ceiling that serial execution trivially respects, and the scheduling policy is recorded in the manifest header. Each detached check records its timeout_budget_s and a concurrent_context (effective_concurrency plus the co-running set), so a HOLD(timeout) is DIAGNOSABLE from the manifest alone: a timeout under effective_concurrency=1 with nothing co-running is a strong real-stall signal, whereas a timeout amid heavy co-running is a harness/resource artifact. The orchestrator turns 'maybe timeout, maybe real fail' into an explicit HOLD(timeout) record (command, duration, timeout budget, exit code, log, concurrent context, verdict) - never a FAIL and never an inferred PASS - so the distinction between a real continuity failure and a harness/resource artifact is unavoidable, not a judgment call. (This requirement was added after the first manual use surfaced the ambiguity: a hand-launched 11-way-parallel cert run starved three mid-chain --compose child batches past the 360s budget, which the manual method reported as a bare FAIL; the orchestrator's serial scheduling plus the HOLD(timeout) manifest entry make that class of ambiguity self-evident.) ARCHIVE IMMUTABILITY: the orchestrator re-hashes the archive at preflight, extracts only into a scratch dir, writes logs only outside the certified tree, and never mutates the tarball or a source tree; runtime pycache is confined to scratch and EXCLUDED from the source-only dirty check. MANIFEST + EVIDENCE (Governor residual decision 1): the manifest is emitted into the final outputs alongside the release, and raw logs are copied into a durable evidence directory so verdicts re-derive from the shipped evidence package, not only from scratch. (3) cert_selftest_gate.py: a GRBSA-STYLE TOOL GATE (run DIRECTLY, NOT a member of the G6 fixed aggregate set, NOT a ugk/conformance gate, so gates stay 98) that proves the orchestrator FAILS CLOSED on five adversarial fixtures - bad archive -> HOLD(preflight); missing tool -> HOLD(preflight); planted forbidden artifact (a .pyc) -> hygiene FAIL; mismatched resume fingerprint -> stale verdict refused (no reuse); simulated failing command -> FAIL not PASS - plus ANTI-VACUITY (a clean base archive PASSes, so the gate distinguishes good from broken and is not trivially failing everything). (4) BOOTSTRAP RULE: r114 is certified by the EXISTING MANUAL method, NOT by the orchestrator - the orchestrator cannot certify the release that introduces it; an orchestrator manifest is corroborating evidence ONLY for LATER releases, and the manual method remains the ROOT OF TRUST until a separate, explicit decision (not taken here) makes the orchestrator the canonical or sole cert path. FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: run_detached.py, certify_release.py, and cert_selftest_gate.py live entirely under tools/release/ (NOT law, NOT ugk/conformance, NOT the G6 set); the ONLY ugk/ touch is this ADR in adr.py; law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; CODEX moves ONLY because this ADR is added; gates stay 98; r111->r114 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED to the authorized list: NO Path B implementation; NO protocol/kernel change; NO application_ops_gate migration; NO cli.py charter-write; NO isolated broker; NO named-op registry; NO registry defaults; NO external-class implementation; NO global Invariant E law; NO canonical-release bypass.",alternatives=["Ship run_detached.py as an ungoverned quick-win release ahead of the orchestrator: REJECTED (Governor residual decision 2) - the launcher participates in evidence production, so it belongs INSIDE the governed tooling increment; both layers ship in one reviewed r114, staged internally launcher -> orchestrator -> self-test gate.","Let the orchestrator interpret a gate's OUTPUT TEXT to decide pass/fail: REJECTED - that makes it a JUDGE; a verdict is the gate's own exit code (or a recorded mechanical comparison with recorded inputs), keeping the orchestrator a thin recorder and the gates authoritative.","Let the orchestrator certify r114 (the release that introduces it): REJECTED (bootstrap) - it cannot certify itself; r114 is certified by the manual method and the orchestrator is evidence only for later releases.","Make the self-test gate a ugk/conformance gate (98 -> 99): REJECTED (Governor residual decision 3) - it is certification tooling, not a kernel/conformance invariant; a GRBSA-style tool gate run directly keeps the conformance count at 98 unless a later reason justifies moving the core count.","Hand-wave the environment fingerprint: REJECTED (Governor) - a resumed phase could otherwise silently validate against a shifted interpreter/OS/locale; the fingerprint is a concrete field set with PYTHONHASHSEED pinned to 0, hashed, with cleartext retained.","Allow a canonical-release cert bypass to save turns while iterating: REJECTED (Governor) - a canonical release without proof is not canonical; --quick is an iteration lane (not acceptance, not continuity, not a canonical release) and full B1-B4 remains the canonical mint bar; the goal is to stop wasting human turns on shell choreography while keeping the proof intact."],consequences="The release-certification surface is now governed evidentiary tooling: a true detached launcher (no harness-timeout-as-failure, durable exit capture), a thin-recorder orchestrator (exit-code verdicts plus recorded mechanical comparisons, a machine-readable manifest, hash-bound resume, a concrete env fingerprint, fail-closed handling, archive immutability), and a GRBSA-style self-test gate proving fail-closed behavior plus anti-vacuity. Turn-by-turn certification friction - path rediscovery, setsid launch timeouts, manual polling - is removed WITHOUT weakening any proof: the full B1-B4 phase runs the SAME checks, merely orchestrated, recorded, and non-blocking per turn. NOT CLAIMED: that the orchestrator certified itself (it did not - r114 is manually certified, the bootstrap rule); that the orchestrator is the canonical or sole cert path (it is corroborating evidence; the manual method remains the root of trust until a separate decision); that any proof was made cheaper by weakening it; that any Path B, protocol, or kernel change was made. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (the three tools live in tools/release/, not law and not ugk/conformance; the only ugk/ touch is this ADR); genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added - the orchestrator is evidentiary tooling, not a law invariant); ADRs through AD-43 (41); gates stay 98 (the self-test gate is a GRBSA tool gate run directly, not a ugk/conformance gate). r111->r114 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link; CODEX moves only because AD-43 is added. STAGED ROADMAP: with a steadier certification handle in place, the parked r112 EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE pre-implementation plan is the next implementation candidate, design-first and separately authorized; the orchestrator earns standing as corroborating evidence over later releases before any decision to make it the canonical cert path. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: run_detached.py, certify_release.py, and cert_selftest_gate.py are PRODUCTION cert tooling (built, tested, and self-test-gated); they are NOT wired into ugk/ and do NOT alter the conformance surface.",bound_invariants=["DM-S-03","PERSIST-S-01","IEL-S-01"])
ADR_44=_adr(id="AD-44",context="r111/r114 accepted; both relay joints propagate a caller-declared class and the release-cert orchestrator (AD-43) is in place as corroborating evidentiary tooling. The r112 EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE pre-implementation plan, PARKED since r111, is the governing design (its internal r113/AD-43 numbering predates the orchestrator track; the Governor fixed it to r115/AD-44). EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE is the one effect class the r103 atomic seam structurally CANNOT cover - an irreversible external act cannot be rolled back - so the r112 honest four-state two-phase trail (NOT a rollback seam) was designed for it. The Governor returned to Path B and authorized r115 as the EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE implementation increment with a fixed scope (kernel two-phase path; required idempotency_key; ExternalEffectNotPerformed as the confirmed-non-performance signal; PREPARE/COMMIT/ABORT markers; orphan-PREPARE detector; conformance-only append-once sink pilot; a focused gate proving success, confirmed non-performance, ambiguous/in-doubt, outcome-write failure, and orphan detection; this ADR; frame-stationary unless evidence forces a halt) and an explicit not-authorized list. Canonical r115 acceptance still requires the full governed manual B1-B4 certification trail; the orchestrator may corroborate iteration.",decision="r115 implements the kernel two-phase PREPARE/COMMIT/ABORT path for EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE. (1) PREFLIGHT RELAX + REQUIRED KEY (called out, not silent): the kernel.execute preflight no longer fails EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE closed as unimplemented; it PROCEEDS but REQUIRES a caller-supplied, deterministic, non-empty idempotency_key passed via a NEW execute() keyword idempotency_key (a called-out signature addition, exactly as effect_atomicity was added in r102-a; the value rides in the parameters-JSON markers, NO schema column). A missing or empty key raises ProtocolError with ZERO mutation BEFORE gate_admit (the AD-37 undeclared-effect posture; locked decision Q1: REQUIRE, no auto-retry). The kernel checks non-empty only; DETERMINISM of the key is the caller's audited contract (it is what makes a MANUAL retry externally dedup-safe). EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE STILL fails closed (compensation/saga is a separate later phase). (2) NEW EXCEPTION (called out, not silent): ExternalEffectNotPerformed, the DESIGNATED signal an EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE effect raises ONLY when it can PROVE the irreversible act did not happen. (3) FOUR-STATE TWO-PHASE PATH, deliberately NOT inside store.transaction() (wrapping an unrollback-able act in a rollback scope would be misleading; the three phases commit independently at depth 0): PREPARE (intent-to-act, depth 0, committed BEFORE the effect, preserving NBER-1, carrying idempotency_key + gate_admit_ref) -> effect() -> on return COMMIT (confirmed performed, depth 0, written AFTER the effect so success is no longer before-effect for this class) | on ExternalEffectNotPerformed ABORT (confirmed NOT performed, failed=True, abort_reason 'external_effect_not_performed', a NON-rollback terminal that NEVER claims the act was undone) | on ANY OTHER exception the kernel writes NO terminal and re-raises, leaving an orphan PREPARE (in-doubt). gate_admit remains the generic admission; PREPARE is the EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE intent-to-act anchor that outcomes link back to via prepare_ref. (4) RECEIPT MARKERS in parameters-JSON, NO committed schema column (mirroring the r102-a marker and _emit_effect_abort): phase in {prepare, commit, abort}, effect_atomicity 'external_irreversible', idempotency_key, prepare_ref, gate_admit_ref, abort_reason. (5) MANDATORY ORPHAN-PREPARE DETECTOR: ugk/integrity/external_irreversible.py, a PURE deterministic chain scan (detect_orphan_prepares + summarize) flagging every PREPARE with no terminal sharing its idempotency_key and pointing back via prepare_ref, classified in_doubt; it NEVER auto-commits, auto-aborts, or auto-retries - it REPORTS, and missing evidence fails closed for any verifier requiring a clean terminal state. (6) CONFORMANCE-ONLY PILOT: external_irreversible_pilot_gate (a ugk/conformance gate; gates 98 -> 99) drives a purpose-built external append-once sink (irreversible external state living in the gate, not the store, so the seam genuinely cannot roll it back; an idempotent append-once effect modelling external dedup) through all five cases - clean success -> COMMIT (sink has the entry); confirmed non-performance -> ABORT (sink unchanged); ambiguous post-act failure -> orphan (no terminal, act performed); outcome-write failure (the COMMIT store.write raises) -> orphan (no terminal persists); the orphan detector flagging exactly the in-doubt PREPAREs and not the success/abort attempts - plus required-key fail-closed with zero mutation and the append-once dedup. (7) BLAST RADIUS (called out): effect_atomicity_declaration_gate is UPDATED to prove EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE proceeds with a key / fails closed without one while EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE still fails closed (mirroring the r102-b update for PURE/STORE_LOCAL); broker_propagation_gate and adapter_atomicity_propagation_gate STILL fail closed for EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE because the broker GovernedRequest and the adapter constructor carry NO idempotency_key (NOT extended in r115 - out of scope), so the missing-key ProtocolError fires; the static effect_declaration_probe stays clean because the pilot passes the class via dynamic kwargs, invisible to the per-callsite literal scan.",alternatives=["Wrap the effect in store.transaction() like the r103 seam: REJECTED - an unrollback-able external act must not be wrapped in a rollback scope; PREPARE / COMMIT / ABORT commit independently at depth 0.","Default every effect failure to ABORT: REJECTED - that falsely asserts non-performance; an ambiguous failure is in-doubt (orphan PREPARE), and ABORT is reserved for PROVEN non-performance signalled by ExternalEffectNotPerformed.","Auto-retry an in-doubt attempt: REJECTED - exactly-once is the external system's property, not the kernel's; the required idempotency_key lets the EXTERNAL system dedup a deliberate, out-of-band MANUAL retry.","Charter-write as the first pilot: REJECTED (locked Q5) - file writes are a temp+rename gray area to classify separately later; the first pilot is a purpose-built conformance-only append-once sink, the safest first stone.","Extend the broker/adapter with an idempotency_key carrier now: NOT TAKEN (out of r115 scope) - EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE via the relays therefore fails closed via the missing-key ProtocolError for now.","Fold the orphan detector only into the gate: NOT TAKEN - it ships as a reusable pure module so a later out-of-band governed reconciliation can consume it.","Formalize a global Invariant E now: DEFERRED - with Path A + this Path B the most E could honestly become is a SCOPED 'atomic OR truthful two-phase outcome trail with detectable in-doubt' claim, which is NOT global atomicity and needs its own design."],consequences="EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE - the one class the r103 seam cannot cover - now has a truthful two-phase outcome trail: a durable decision-before-effect record (PREPARE, NBER-1 preserved); success written AFTER the effect (the success-before-effect ordering flaw fixed for this class by ordering, no rollback scope claimed); a durable classified outcome (COMMIT confirmed-performed / ABORT confirmed-not-performed); detectable in-doubt states (orphan PREPARE) surfaced by a mandatory deterministic detector; a required idempotency_key that makes a manual retry externally safe; and an auditable 'what we attempted and what we know' trail. NOT CLAIMED: NOT rollback (ABORT means confirmed-not-performed, never undone); NOT atomicity (PREPARE + effect + outcome are three independent depth-0 steps, not one atom); NOT exactly-once (no auto-retry; exactly-once remains the external system's property); NOT containment (confess-and-audit: the kernel records, it does not prevent, sandbox, or reverse the act); NOT resolution of in-doubt (an orphan is reported, never silently resolved; the act's status is genuinely unknown until an out-of-band check). FRAME-STATIONARY: all markers in parameters-JSON (NO committed schema column); law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added - the two-phase path realizes the existing receipt/error invariants for a new effect class; wiring precedes any future scoped-E formalization); ADRs through AD-44 (42); gates 98 -> 99 (external_irreversible_pilot_gate is a ugk/conformance gate, because the two-phase path lives in the KERNEL - unlike the r111/r114 GRBSA tool gates). CODEX moves because AD-44 is added. r114 -> r115 BEHAVIORAL continuity link. SCOPE-BOUNDED to the authorized list: NO charter-write; NO production external-effect migration; NO reconciliation op (orphan resolution remains a future governed, out-of-band, separately-authorized operation); NO EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE; NO isolated broker or named-op registry; NO registry defaults; NO global Invariant E law. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the kernel two-phase path, the orphan detector, and the pilot gate are gated conformance semantics for EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE proven via the conformance-only sink; there is NO external production callsite yet (the pilot is the safest first stone); EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE remains DECLARED-BUT-UNIMPLEMENTED and fails closed.",bound_invariants=["PERSIST-S-01","DM-S-03","EH-S-02"])
ADR_45=_adr(id="AD-45",context="r115 (AD-44) implemented the kernel EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE two-phase PREPARE/COMMIT/ABORT path with a REQUIRED, caller-supplied idempotency_key, but DELIBERATELY left both relay carriers (the broker GovernedRequest and the GRBSA ExecutionAdapter constructor) WITHOUT a key field, so EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE via either relay failed closed on the kernel missing-key ProtocolError. The r116 Path B hardening inspection (design-only, accepted) named idempotency_key relay propagation the natural next integration increment -- the THIRD relay joint after effect (r107/AD-40) and class (r111/AD-42) -- with the kernel remaining the SOLE enforcement point; r117 (the narrow kernel-docstring correction, no ADR) was accepted in between. The Governor authorized r118 with a fixed scope: add idempotency_key to GovernedRequest and to the ExecutionAdapter constructor; propagate it verbatim to kernel.execute(); the relays do NOT pre-judge a missing key; the kernel remains the sole EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE key enforcer; extend the focused broker/adapter propagation gates; update stale adapter wording if touched; add this ADR if the interface change enters the governed record; clean-room cert; and an explicit not-authorized list.",decision="r118 makes the CALLER the supplier of the idempotency_key at BOTH relay boundaries and the relays faithful conduits, mirroring the r107/r111 caller-declares / relay-propagates / kernel-enforces principle for the key. (1) INTERFACE CHANGE (called out, not silent): the broker GovernedRequest dataclass gains an idempotency_key field (Optional[str], default None) and ExecutionAdapter.__init__ gains an idempotency_key keyword (Optional[str], default None); each is propagated VERBATIM to kernel.execute() alongside effect_atomicity. Neither relay defaults, invents, alters, or pre-judges the key. (2) KERNEL IS THE SOLE ENFORCER: a missing key for an EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE effect still fails closed in the kernel preflight (ProtocolError, ZERO mutation, before gate_admit -- the AD-44 posture); the relays add NO key pre-check (a pre-check would duplicate the kernel contract in two more places and risk drift). The broker surfaces the ProtocolError as admitted=False with no receipt via its existing protocol-error handling; the adapter surfaces it as a first-class refused envelope (refusal_class ProtocolError, no written receipt). (3) WITH A KEY, EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE NOW PROCEEDS through BOTH relays via the AD-44 two-phase path (PREPARE -> effect -> COMMIT), the key carried VERBATIM into the parameters-JSON markers so it reaches the COMMIT terminal unaltered. (4) THE TWO DISTINCT FAIL-CLOSED REASONS are now explicit in the relays and gates: EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE without a key fails closed (missing-key); EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE fails closed (protocol unimplemented). (5) STALE WORDING UPDATED (no silent semantics): the adapter's former 'external/unimplemented DECLARED class (e.g. EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE)' ProtocolError comment is corrected -- EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE now proceeds with a key, and the ProtocolError refusal is now EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE (unimplemented) OR EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE without a key. (6) GATES EXTENDED (additive, no count change): broker_propagation_gate (ugk/conformance) reworks check (5) to the two distinct fail-closed reasons and adds check (6) -- EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE WITH a key admitted, exactly one COMMIT, the key carried verbatim into the COMMIT; adapter_atomicity_propagation_gate (a GRBSA tool gate) adds a key-capturing spy, reworks (e) to the missing-key fail-closed case (class propagated verbatim, NO key invented), and adds (e2) WITH-key two-phase success with exactly one COMMIT carrying the key and the key propagated verbatim, plus (g) the adapter never defaults/invents/alters the key (verbatim or None). (7) effect_declaration_probe stays clean: the key is a VALUE, not a class literal, so the per-callsite class scan is unaffected; the two effect+class propagation seams are unchanged and still recognized (2 propagated declarations). FRAME-STATIONARY + ADDITIVE: the change lives in ugk/transport/broker.py (GovernedRequest field + verbatim propagation + docstrings), tools/grbsa/grbsa_runtime/execution_adapter.py (constructor kwarg + verbatim propagation + corrected comments), ugk/conformance/broker_propagation_gate.py (extended in place), tools/grbsa/adapter_atomicity_propagation_gate.py (extended), and this ADR; law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; CODEX moves ONLY because this ADR is added; gates stay 99 (broker_propagation_gate is an EXISTING conformance gate extended in place; the adapter gate is a GRBSA tool gate; NO new conformance gate); r117 -> r118 behavioral. SCOPE-BOUNDED: in-process LocalBrokerServer and in-process GRBSA ExecutionAdapter only; NO charter-write; NO production external-effect migration; NO reconciliation op; NO EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE; NO isolated broker; NO named-op registry; NO registry defaults; NO global Invariant E law.",alternatives=["Let the relays pre-check a missing key and refuse before execute(): REJECTED (Governor) - it duplicates the kernel's EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE key contract in two more places (drift risk) for no gain; the kernel preflight is the SOLE enforcer and both relays already surface its ProtocolError as a fail-closed refusal.","Add the key to GovernedRequest only (broker) or the adapter only: REJECTED - both relay joints already carry effect + class (r107/r111); the key is the third element of the same call spec and belongs at both, so EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE works uniformly through either relay or fails closed uniformly without a key.","Make the key a registry default or let a relay synthesize a deterministic key: REJECTED - a synthesized key would be the silent-classification defect reborn for the key; determinism of the key is the caller's audited contract (AD-44), and a missing key must FAIL CLOSED, never be invented.","Migrate a production external-effect callsite through the relays now: REJECTED (Governor) - r118 is the relay key-carrier contract only; no production effect is migrated, and the conformance/tool gates exercise the path. The orphan reconciliation op (the largest r116 production-readiness gap) remains a separate, later, governed increment.","Promote the adapter gate to a ugk/conformance gate or add a new conformance gate (99 -> 100): REJECTED - the adapter is GRBSA tooling (its gate is a tool gate run directly); the broker gate is an existing conformance gate extended in place; no new conformance invariant is introduced, so the count stays 99.","Formalize Invariant E as law now: DEFERRED - the relays now carry the key, but production external effects, the reconciliation path, and EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE remain absent; a global E claim would overclaim; wiring precedes formalization."],consequences="Both relay boundaries are now HONEST about the idempotency_key: the caller supplies it, the relay propagates it verbatim, the kernel enforces it, and neither relay invents, defaults, alters, or pre-judges it -- the THIRD relay joint closed, completing the effect (r107) / class (r111) / key (r118) propagation set. EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE now works end-to-end through BOTH the broker and the GRBSA ExecutionAdapter when the caller supplies a key (PREPARE -> effect -> COMMIT, the key carried verbatim into the COMMIT terminal), and fails closed through both when the key is missing (kernel missing-key ProtocolError, zero mutation), distinct from the EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE unimplemented fail-closed. NOT CLAIMED: that any production external effect was migrated (none was; the path is exercised only by the conformance/tool gates); that the orphan reconciliation op exists (it remains the r116-named production-readiness gap, a separate later governed increment); that an isolated broker, a named-op registry, or a registry default is implemented; that EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE is implemented (it still fails closed); global atomicity; Invariant E as law. The kernel remains the SOLE EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE key enforcement point. FRAME-STATIONARY: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (broker.py is substrate and the adapter is GRBSA tooling, neither is law); genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added - the cutover wires caller-supplied key propagation into the two relays; wiring precedes any future formalization); ADRs through AD-45 (43); gates stay 99 (broker_propagation_gate extended in place; the adapter gate is a GRBSA tool gate; no new conformance gate). r117 -> r118 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link; CODEX moves only because AD-45 is added. VERIFICATION SURFACE: the static effect_declaration_probe stays clean (the key is a value, not a class literal; the two effect+class propagation seams are unchanged -- 2 propagated declarations, 0 unknown classes, 0 undeclared real-effect callsites). STAGED ROADMAP CONTINUES: all three relay elements (effect, class, key) now propagate caller-supplied through both joints; the isolated broker / named-op registry remains design-reserved; the orphan reconciliation op (the largest r116 production-readiness gap) is the natural next Path B increment, design-first and separately authorized; charter-write and EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE remain Path B; a scoped two-phase/class-1-2 atomicity invariant remains a possible future formalization, not global E. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the broker and adapter key-propagation paths and their extended gates are PRODUCTION-GATED (broker via ugk/conformance, adapter via GRBSA tooling); there is still NO production external callsite (the conformance/tool gates exercise the path); EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE remains DECLARED-BUT-UNIMPLEMENTED and fails closed.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-02","EH-S-02","PERSIST-S-01"])
ADR_46=_adr(id="AD-46",context="r115 (AD-44) wrote each EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE terminal (COMMIT/ABORT) as a SINGLE store write; a TRANSIENT failure of that write (a SQLite lock/busy contention, or the AD-36 clean-path commit/RELEASE TransactionCommitError) left NO terminal and an orphan PREPARE -- even though the outcome was ALREADY known (the effect had returned, or had raised ExternalEffectNotPerformed). r119 (read-only) made that record-loss orphan class visible via the enriched orphan descriptor; the r120 design (accepted, design-only) specified a bounded retry of the terminal STORE WRITE ONLY, categorically distinct from the forbidden external-effect retry. The Governor ratified all five r120 section-9 decisions: Option A (record nothing in the chain), MAX=3 with no sleep/backoff, the narrow retryable set, the TerminalWriteExhausted wrapper, and a private helper plus this ADR.",decision="r121 adds a BOUNDED in-process retry of the EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE terminal store write, in a private kernel helper _emit_terminal_durable that wraps ONLY the COMMIT/ABORT _emit_irreversible call. (1) BOUNDARY (the spine): the external effect is NEVER re-invoked -- it lives before the call site, entirely outside the helper; the retry re-attempts only a durable RECORD of an outcome that is already known. (2) BOUNDED: at most MAX_OUTCOME_WRITE_ATTEMPTS (=3, a module CONSTANT, NOT config and NOT a registry default); NO sleep / NO backoff (immediate, synchronous). (3) NARROW RETRYABLE SET: only sqlite3.OperationalError with lock/busy semantics, and TransactionCommitError (AD-36); ANY other exception fails closed IMMEDIATELY (re-raise on the first attempt) -> orphan, so a logic/programming fault is never masked by retrying. (4) FAIL-CLOSED ON EXHAUSTION: after MAX retryable failures NO terminal persists and TerminalWriteExhausted (carrying phase, prepare_ref, attempts) is raised, chaining the last transient error -> the orphan stands. (5) OPTION A -- NOTHING enters the chain: a terminal written on attempt k is byte-identical in PARAMETERS to one written on attempt 1 (only the inherent, already-varying write timestamp differs); no attempt count and no retry marker enter any receipt, so chain-hash determinism is untouched. TerminalWriteExhausted is an EXCEPTION TYPE only, never a receipt field. (6) The ambiguous-effect orphan path is UNCHANGED: a non-designated effect exception still writes no terminal and re-raises, and the retry path is NEVER entered (the outcome is unknown, so there is nothing to persist). (7) The ABORT terminal gets the SAME bounded retry as COMMIT. FRAME: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (NO schema column -- the markers stay parameters-JSON; the helper writes through the existing _emit_irreversible/_store.write); NO new invariant; CODEX moves ONLY because this ADR is added; gates stay 99 (the external_irreversible_pilot_gate is extended IN PLACE). SCOPE-BOUNDED: this shrinks the record-loss orphan SUB-class at its source; orphans REMAIN possible (persistent store failure, a crash between effect-return and the retried write, ambiguous effect failure), so reconciliation is still required and NO fail-closed zero-orphan release gate is added.",alternatives=["Retry the external effect: FORBIDDEN (AD-44) -- it re-performs an unrollback-able act. The r121 retry is the store WRITE only; the effect lives outside the helper and is proven by the gate to run exactly once on every path.","Record an attempt count / retry marker in the terminal receipt: REJECTED (Governor, r120 section-9 Option A) -- compute_h_body binds the parameters, so the same logical outcome would hash differently by storage contention, a determinism wound in a TERMINAL receipt. Contention visibility, if ever wanted, belongs in a read-only probe channel, never the chain.","Unbounded retry or wall-clock backoff: REJECTED -- an unbounded loop or a time.sleep injects a latency/nondeterminism hazard into the kernel; a failure that needs wall-clock time to clear is, for this purpose, persistent and correctly falls through to an orphan. MAX=3, immediate, no sleep.","A broad retryable set (any store exception): REJECTED -- retrying a logic/programming fault would mask it; only the narrow named transient set (lock/busy, TransactionCommitError) is retryable, everything else fails closed immediately.","Synthesize an ABORT or an in-doubt note on write exhaustion: REJECTED -- an exhausted COMMIT is NOT confirmed non-performance (it would falsely classify), and any note is itself a store write that can fail identically (r116 section-4 option 2); the honest residue is the orphan.","A fail-closed zero-orphan release gate now: REJECTED (Governor) -- orphans remain possible after the retry; a zero-orphan gate would wedge releases with no lawful way to clear the state before the reconciliation op exists.","Make MAX configurable or a registry default: REJECTED -- registry defaults remain excluded; the cap is a constant a caller cannot silently override."],consequences="The record-loss orphan SUB-class is shrunk at its source: a TRANSIENT store-write failure of a COMMIT/ABORT is now converted to a clean terminal within MAX attempts, while the external effect runs EXACTLY ONCE (proven by the gate on every path). NOT CLAIMED: that orphans are gone (persistent store failure, a crash between effect-return and the retried write, and ambiguous effect failure still produce orphans); that the external effect is ever retried (it is not -- the helper wraps only the terminal write); that the write-fail and ambiguous orphans are now distinguishable (Option A records nothing; disambiguation remains the reconciliation op's external-check job); that a zero-orphan gate is justified. The kernel still NEVER infers an outcome from an orphan. FRAME-STATIONARY (hashes): law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc; ledger 11; registry 77 (NO invariant added); ADRs through AD-46 (44); gates 99 (the pilot gate extended in place); CODEX moves only for AD-46. DETERMINISM: no receipt field added; the retry is invisible to chain content; TerminalWriteExhausted is an exception type, not a receipt. r120 (design) -> r121 (impl) is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link. STAGED ROADMAP: write-fail bounded store-retry LANDED; the reconciliation op (r116 section-5.1) is next (design-first, separately authorized) -- the lawful external-check resolution of the orphans that are still born; then a first production EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE callsite. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the bounded retry and its gate are PRODUCTION-GATED (conformance); EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE remains declared-but-unimplemented and fails closed; there is still NO production external callsite.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-02","EH-S-02","PERSIST-S-01"])
ADR_47=_adr(id="AD-47",context="AD-44's four-state model leaves an orphan PREPARE (in-doubt: a PREPARE with no terminal) whenever the outcome is genuinely unknown; r121/AD-46 shrank the transient record-loss sub-class but orphans REMAIN possible (persistent store failure, a crash between effect-return and the retried write, and ambiguous effect failure). AD-44 promised such orphans are resolved OUT-OF-BAND; r119 (read-only) made them visible, and the detector's own contract names the cure: a governed out-of-band reconciliation that, after an EXTERNAL check, writes a COMMIT or ABORT for that prepare_ref. The r122 design (accepted, design-only) specified that op. The Governor ratified all six r122 section-10 decisions: a DEDICATED op (not execute()), the provenance marker set, explicit-authority-recorded with the warrant requirement DEFERRED, 'cannot determine' as a first-class refusal, the detector UNCHANGED, and its own ADR.",decision="r123 adds GovernanceKernel.reconcile_external_irreversible(prepare_ref, determination, evidence_ref, authority, ...) -- the governed, out-of-band RESOLUTION of an orphan EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE PREPARE. (1) SPINE: it RECORDS an outcome a governed operator determined by an EXTERNAL check; it runs NO effect (proven: effect-call-count 0) and performs / re-performs / retries / infers NOTHING. (2) CLOSURE VIA THE EXISTING MATCH: it writes ONE terminal for the EXACT (idempotency_key, prepare_ref) of the orphan, so the UNCHANGED strict-match detector then sees it resolved -- the detector is the reader, this is the writer it always assumed; NO detector change. (3) STRICT FAIL-CLOSED CONTRACT (raises ReconciliationRefused, writing NOTHING, leaving the orphan untouched): authority required and recorded (reconciled_by); evidence_ref required and recorded (recorded, NOT verified -- confess-and-audit); determination must be EXACTLY 'performed' or 'not_performed' -- anything else, INCLUDING a 'cannot determine' inconclusive check, is a first-class REFUSAL that leaves the orphan in_doubt (the system NEVER pressures a terminal into existence); prepare_ref must be an OUTSTANDING orphan at write time (re-checked via detect_orphan_prepares) -- unknown ref, non-PREPARE ref, and already-terminal'd ref all refuse, guaranteeing AT MOST ONE terminal per (key, prepare_ref) (the r121 no-duplicate-terminal discipline). (4) PROVENANCE (no laundering): a reconciling terminal carries reconciled=true, reconciled_by, reconciliation_evidence_ref, determination -- durable, deterministic markers so it is NEVER mistaken for an in-band terminal; a reconciling ABORT uses abort_reason='reconciled_not_performed' (DISTINCT from the in-band 'external_effect_not_performed') and NEVER claims the act was undone. (5) STRICT prepare_ref: reconciling one attempt of a key NEVER clears a different attempt (mirrors r119). (6) The terminal write reuses the AD-46 durable path (bounded store-write retry only); on exhaustion no terminal persists and the orphan stands. FRAME: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED (markers are parameters-JSON, NO schema column); NO new invariant; CODEX moves ONLY for this ADR; gates 99 (the external_irreversible_pilot_gate is extended IN PLACE). SCOPE-BOUNDED: this is the lawful RESOLUTION step; it does NOT eliminate orphans (a 'cannot determine' check, or any orphan not yet reconciled, persists), so NO fail-closed zero-orphan release gate is added, and there is NO auto-reconciliation, production migration, charter-write, EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE, registry default, or global Invariant E law.",alternatives=["Auto-reconcile / let the system infer the outcome: FORBIDDEN -- the system NEVER guesses. Reconciliation requires an explicit operator determination plus an external evidence reference; no determination (or a 'cannot determine' check) is a refusal and the orphan stays in_doubt.","Overload execute() for reconciliation: REJECTED (Governor section-10.1) -- reconciliation runs no effect and has a distinct authority/evidence contract; a dedicated op keeps the boundary legible.","Make the reconciling terminal indistinguishable from an in-band one: REJECTED -- that would LAUNDER an in-doubt state into a false clean observation. Reconciled terminals carry permanent provenance markers (reconciled / reconciled_by / reconciliation_evidence_ref / determination, and reconciled_not_performed for ABORT), so an auditor can always distinguish determined-on-evidence from kernel-observed.","Change the detector to special-case reconciliation: REJECTED (Governor section-10.5) -- the strict (key, prepare_ref) match is the law of the trail; reconciliation closes orphans THROUGH it, not around it. Any reconciled-vs-in-band surfacing is a read-only follow-up, not part of this op.","Require a warrant / governor signature now: DEFERRED (Governor section-10.3) -- a production policy call. Authority is recorded per call and the surface is warrant-capable, but no warrant is mandated in this conformance increment.","Reconcile by writing a NEW prepare_ref / a fresh attempt: REJECTED -- that would leave the original orphan unresolved and could spawn duplicate terminals; reconciliation targets the EXACT existing prepare_ref and refuses anything that is not an outstanding orphan.","A fail-closed zero-orphan release gate now that reconciliation exists: REJECTED (Governor) -- a 'cannot determine' check can still leave an orphan; a zero-orphan gate would wedge releases with no lawful way to clear a genuinely undeterminable state."],consequences="The lawful resolution step now exists: a governed operator can, on an external check, RECORD the determined outcome of an orphan PREPARE as a provenance-marked COMMIT/ABORT for its exact (key, prepare_ref), closing it through the unchanged detector. NOT CLAIMED: that the system knows by magic (it records a governed determination, it does not infer); that orphans are eliminated (a 'cannot determine' check, and any orphan not yet reconciled, persists); that a reconciled terminal is epistemically identical to an in-band one (provenance markers keep them distinguishable forever); that the external effect is ever performed or retried (reconciliation runs NO effect -- proven by the gate's effect-call-count 0); that a zero-orphan gate is justified. The kernel still NEVER infers an outcome. FRAME-STATIONARY (hashes): law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc; ledger 11; registry 77 (NO invariant added); ADRs through AD-47 (45); gates 99 (the pilot gate extended in place); CODEX moves only for AD-47. DETERMINISM: the reconciliation markers are explicit operator inputs (deterministic); the only wall-clock value is the receipt's inherent timestamp (already true for every receipt) -- unlike a retry-count, these are durable governance facts the chain SHOULD bind. r122 (design) -> r123 (impl) is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link. STAGED ROADMAP: the orphan-PREPARE reconciliation op is LANDED; the first production EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE callsite is the next frontier (design-first, separately authorized). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the reconciliation op and its gate are CERTIFIED/GATED conformance; EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE remains declared-but-unimplemented and fails closed; there is still NO production external callsite.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-02","EH-S-02","PERSIST-S-01"])

ADR_48=_adr(id="AD-48",context="r123 (AD-47, the orphan reconciliation op) was accepted as canonical. The accepted FGA Roadmap-Exhaustion ordering opened the CGP universal evidence dispatcher as SB-1, on the honest footing established by the accepted CGP additivity grounding and the CGP doc/framing correction (CGP is a constitutionally-integrated layer in the r123 frame, NOT an external overlay; its invariants CGP-S-01/02/03, SCOPE-S-01/02, ESA-S-01, CTR-S-01/07, SRSA-S-01 and CGP-family gates are part of the certified frame). The accepted dispatcher design specified dispatch_capability_evidence as EVIDENCE EXECUTION (not a workflow engine), reusing the EXISTING seven-state EvidenceArtifact verdict vocabulary (PROVEN/FAIL/GAP/WAIVED/BY-CONSTRUCTION/NOT-RUN/ERROR, per the CTR verdict-labeling discipline) rather than inventing a six-state enum, and sealing a content-addressed ledger WITHOUT a chain receipt. The Governor ratified six section-12 decisions (reuse the seven verdicts; content-addressed ledger with NO chain receipt; new ugk/cgp/dispatch.py + CapabilityEvidenceLedger + helpers; the SB-1/SB-2 fold exposing unresolved caps as GAP; CGP-S-04 DEFERRED; selectors core/live/full/custom preserving no-silent-skip), authorized implementation, and after a quick-lane review required five tightenings before canonical lane (content-sensitive registry_version; fail-closed canonicalized waivers; receipt-aggregation explicit deferral; ledger determinism over normalized details proven with real outputs; malformed/unknown handled by rule), all accepted as addressed.",decision="r125 adds the CGP universal evidence dispatcher as ADDITIVE substrate plus one NEW conformance gate, turning capability CLAIMS (the ESA REGISTRY) into a COMPLETE governed evidence LEDGER. (1) NEW MODULE ugk/cgp/dispatch.py: dispatch_capability_evidence(registry, scope, runner, selector, store, gate_runner) -> CapabilityEvidenceLedger, with WaiverRecord, DispatchScope, and the five jobs plan -> resolve-binding -> execute-by-evidence-class -> normalize -> seal. (2) VERDICTS REUSED, NOT INVENTED: the dispatcher imports and reuses the EXISTING seven-state EvidenceArtifact.verdict vocabulary under the CTR verdict-labeling discipline (PROVEN/FAIL/GAP/WAIVED/BY-CONSTRUCTION/NOT-RUN/ERROR), with a self-check (verdict_vocabulary_matches_evidence_artifact) proving the alias is EXACT via typing.get_type_hints; NO six-state enum is coined and the hyphenated NOT-RUN and BY-CONSTRUCTION are preserved. (3) NORMALIZATION TARGET REUSED: every execution outcome is normalized to the EXISTING EvidenceArtifact; Class III interpretive evidence reuses the EXISTING InterpretiveEvidencePack. (4) COMPLETENESS + NO-SILENT-SKIP: every IN-SCOPE capability ends with EXACTLY ONE terminal verdict; every registry capability is either scored or visibly dispositioned (out_of_scope / waivers); planning enumerates the WHOLE registry in canonical sorted-key order. (5) BINDING RESOLUTION BY EVIDENCE CLASS: a UGK realization naming a runnable ugk.conformance gate is EXECUTED (PROVEN/FAIL; a harness/instrument fault -> ERROR, distinct from FAIL); an explicit by-construction marker -> BY-CONSTRUCTION; scenario-sweep / coverage-map / interpretive-pack / receipt-aggregation are RESOLVED and dispositioned NOT-RUN as EXPLICIT deferral (live execution of those classes is a later increment, NOT this one); no UGK-resolvable instrument -> GAP (the SB-2 cap-completion census). (6) CONTENT-ADDRESSED LEDGER, NO CHAIN RECEIPT (ratified decision): seal computes ledger_hash = SHA-256('CGP-LEDGER-v1' || canonical_json(deterministic body)); the ledger is NOT written to the receipt chain and emits NO receipt (deterministic substrate first; chain anchoring is a separate later design and a separate effect-class decision NOT taken here). (7) DETERMINISM: artifact details are NORMALIZED deterministic codes (gate:<name>:ok|fail, gate:<name>:error:<ExcType>, by-construction:<marker>, gap:<reason>, not-run:<reason>, waived:<authority>:<reason>); the raw gate free-text, the scenario timing, and the interpretive layer are RECORDED-but-EXCLUDED from the hash; registry_version is a CONTENT projection over every dispatch-relevant field (class, realizations, evidence_class, gate/binding fields, deterministic_layer, notes, interpretive-template presence) so a changed binding under an unchanged key set changes the version; capabilities iterate in canonical sorted-key order; no wall-clock enters the hashed body. (8) WAIVERS FAIL CLOSED + CANONICAL: a waiver requires authority+reason, forbids a duplicate cap, and requires the cap to exist (otherwise ValueError); waivers are sorted before hashing so equivalent waiver sets are order-independent. (9) MALFORMED BY RULE: a non-dict cap -> ERROR; malformed realizations -> GAP; a missing/unknown evidence_class -> explicit GAP; no malformed entry yields PROVEN; an empty scope/registry yields no artifacts and no PROVEN (anti-vacuity). (10) SELECTORS core/live/full/custom, every selector preserving no-silent-skip (a selected-out in-scope cap is recorded NOT-RUN, never omitted). (11) NEW CONFORMANCE GATE dispatcher_gate (ugk/conformance, registered in run_gates_batch; gates 99 -> 100) proves the seven dispatcher properties (completeness; no-silent-skip; normalization incl. exact verdict aliasing and registry_version content-sensitivity; scope-filtering incl. receipt-aggregation deferral; waiver-handling incl. fail-closed dup/unknown/malformed and order-independence; determinism incl. real-runner reproduction; anti-vacuity incl. empty/malformed and always-ok-runner-proves-only-gate-resolved). (12) CGP-S-04 DEFERRED: the completeness law (every in-scope cap resolves to exactly one governed terminal verdict in a sealed ledger) is NOT formalized as an invariant in this increment; wiring precedes formalization. FRAME: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; NO amendment; registry 77 (NO invariant added); CODEX moves because this ADR is added AND the conformance surface gains a gate; gates 99 -> 100 (dispatcher_gate is a NEW ugk/conformance gate -- the first conformance-count rise since AD-44/r115, because unlike the recent in-place gate extensions this increment adds a distinct gate). SCOPE-BOUNDED: additive substrate + one gate + this ADR ONLY; the dispatcher is EVIDENCE EXECUTION, not a workflow engine; NO chain receipt; NO workflow engine; NO production workflow execution; NO CGP-S-04; NO law/schema/legend move; NO EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE; NO namespace work; NO IEL formalization.",alternatives=["Invent a fresh six-state verdict enum matching the original design sketch: REJECTED (Governor section-12.1; claim<=proof) -- EvidenceArtifact.verdict already governs a seven-state vocabulary under the CTR verdict-labeling discipline including BY-CONSTRUCTION and the hyphenated NOT-RUN; the dispatcher reuses it verbatim rather than coining or shrinking a CTR-governed vocabulary.","Emit a chain receipt when sealing the ledger: DEFERRED (Governor section-12.2) -- the first increment produces a content-addressed ledger WITHOUT a chain receipt; chain anchoring is a separate later design and would be a NEW effect-class decision, not smuggled into this increment.","Formalize CGP-S-04 (the completeness law) now: DEFERRED (Governor section-12.5) -- wire and gate the mechanism first; an invariant (a registry move) would be added only after the mechanism is proven.","Execute scenario-sweep / coverage-map / receipt-aggregation bindings live in this increment: NOT TAKEN -- those classes are RESOLVED and dispositioned NOT-RUN as explicit deferral; live execution is a later increment, kept out so this increment stays additive substrate plus one gate.","Let the dispatcher decide remediation, business-process order, or which capabilities a consumer should hold: REJECTED -- that is consumer workflow; the dispatcher runs EVIDENCE, returns a ledger, and decides nothing about what to DO about a FAIL/GAP/WAIVED.","Hash the raw gate detail text or scenario timing into ledger_hash: REJECTED (Governor quick-lane review) -- real gate detail can carry paths/timing/exception reprs; the hash binds NORMALIZED deterministic codes only, with raw detail and timing recorded outside the hash.","Hash registry_version over sorted keys only: REJECTED (Governor quick-lane review) -- a changed binding under an unchanged key set must change the version, so registry_version is a content projection over the dispatch-relevant fields.","Add seven separate conformance gates (one per property): NOT TAKEN -- a single dispatcher_gate with seven named sub-checks is the minimal-surgical conformance surface for the property set; splitting is a later option (gates 99 -> 100, not 99 -> 106)."],consequences="CGP now turns capability claims into a complete governed evidence ledger: every in-scope capability holds EXACTLY ONE of the seven governed terminal verdicts and every registry capability is scored or visibly dispositioned, with a content-addressed deterministic ledger and NO chain receipt. Over the real 33-cap ESA registry the dispatcher is complete and deterministic (real-runner full distribution PROVEN=8, GAP=20, BY-CONSTRUCTION=1, NOT-RUN=2, ERROR=2; the 20 GAP caps are the SB-2 cap-completion census; the 2 ERROR are real conformance gates that raise when invoked standalone, captured as ERROR distinct from FAIL). NOT CLAIMED: that scenario-sweep/coverage-map/interpretive-pack/receipt-aggregation bindings are executed (they are explicit NOT-RUN deferrals); that the ledger is chain-anchored (it emits NO receipt); that CGP-S-04 is law (deferred); that any production workflow runs (the dispatcher is evidence execution, not a workflow engine); that the GAP caps are closed (closing them is cap-completion work the dispatcher makes visible). FRAME-STATIONARY (hashes): law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added -- CGP-S-04 deferred); ADRs through AD-48 (46); gates 99 -> 100 (dispatcher_gate, a NEW ugk/conformance gate). r123 -> r125 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link; CODEX moves because AD-48 is added and the conformance surface gains a gate. DETERMINISM: ledger_hash binds normalized deterministic codes + a content-projected registry_version + canonical iteration order; raw gate detail, scenario timing, and the interpretive layer are recorded outside the hash; real-runner determinism is gate-proven. STAGED ROADMAP: the CGP universal evidence dispatcher (SB-1) is LANDED; the SB-2 cap-completion (closing the 20 GAP caps with UGK-resolvable bindings), live execution of the deferred evidence classes, the FGA trace-vector layer (SB-3), and a possible future CGP-S-04 formalization are separate, later, separately-authorized increments. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: ugk/cgp/dispatch.py and dispatcher_gate are CERTIFIED/GATED conformance substrate; scenario/coverage/interpretive/receipt-aggregation execution and chain anchoring are DEFERRED (explicit NOT-RUN / no-receipt), not implemented.",bound_invariants=["CGP-S-01","CGP-S-02","CTR-S-01"])

ADR_49=_adr(id="AD-49",context="r125 (AD-48, the CGP universal evidence dispatcher) was accepted as canonical. The FGA Roadmap-Exhaustion ordering then ran three post-r125 quick-lane increments, all accepted: QH-1 (a proof_model_b verifier-consistency correction), SB-2/SB-2a (the CGP GAP-census triage plus a posture-aware conformance gate runner), and the SB-3a FGA trace-vector design -- accepted with a REQUIRED core/candidate split that keeps the capability-evidence surface D_cap OUT of the committed vector until a receipt commitment is separately authorized. SB-3a-core was then implemented and accepted in quick lane under a narrowed, no-overclaim claim: it makes the EXISTING committed receipt axes explicit, NOT a new admissibility regime. The Governor authorized the r126 canonical lane to bundle QH-1 + SB-2a + SB-3a-core, certify the substrate before opening the law-moving LM-2 frontier, and chose Option A -- record SB-3a-core as a governed architectural decision in the ADR/CODEX trail rather than only in release text.",decision="r126 adds the FGA explicit committed-surface trace-vector substrate as ADDITIVE substrate plus one NEW conformance gate, exposing UGK's already-implicit FGA decision-surface/trace-vector structure as a first-class, enumerable, frame-bound object over the EXISTING committed receipt axes. (1) NEW SUBSTRATE PACKAGE ugk/fga/ (trace_vector.py) plus the conformance gate ugk/conformance/trace_vector_gate.py: a CLOSED DecisionSurface registry, a TraceVector builder, a named aggregation operator, and a build-from-receipt correspondence -- reads receipts only, commits nothing new. (2) COMMITTED CORE is EXACTLY D_s / D_c / D_m / D_j, corresponding to the EXISTING committed receipt fields h_s / h_c / h_m / h_j; the registry is CLOSED to those four committed fields (COMMITTED_RECEIPT_FIELDS), so any surface lacking a real committed field is rejected fail-closed. (3) HONEST VERIFICATION MODES, NO OVERCLAIM: D_s is REDERIVED where supported (recomputed via m2.H_s from stored values); D_c / D_m / D_j are COMMITTED-BODY-BOUND -- present, well-formed, and bound by h_r / h_body -- and are NOT claimed as independently replayed (AD-21 rejected H_c/H_m/H_j pipeline replay); the whole-body h_body (IEL-S-01) is the integrity backstop that detects tampering of the non-rederived axes. (4) AGGREGATION OPERATOR IDENTITY is explicitly named and versioned as conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1, bound into every trace vector: ADMIT iff the full canonical committed surface set is displayed AND every surface PASSes AND whole-body integrity AND frame-consistency hold; otherwise REFUSE (fail-closed, monotone toward refusal). (5) NO MONOLITHIC ADMISSIBILITY: an empty, partial, reordered, or operator-mismatched vector cannot ADMIT; admit is the explicit conjunction of the displayed surfaces. (6) TRACE IDENTITY binds the frame/context tuple: law/schema/legend/CODEX frame, surface-registry version, aggregation-operator id, transition/op, and receipt identity (h_r / h_body), hashed into a deterministic trace_vector_hash (within- and cross-process stable). (7) D_cap (capability-evidence, fed by CGP dispatcher ledgers) remains DESIGN-ONLY / CANDIDATE -- intentionally ABSENT from the committed registry and rejected if added -- until a receipt commitment path is separately authorized. (8) WILL/INTENT (WILL-S-06) has NO dedicated committed field, so it remains a documented sub-surface / input concern under D_c and is rejected as a standalone committed surface. (9) NEW CONFORMANCE GATE trace_vector_gate (ugk/conformance, exercising the ugk/fga substrate, registered in run_gates_batch; gates 100 -> 101) proves enumerability, deterministic canonical order, explicit+versioned aggregation, trace-hash stability, frame/context binding, surface-to-committed-field correspondence, h_body binding, no-uncommitted-surface, the honesty modes, the seven required negative tests (D_cap rejected, standalone will/intent rejected, missing committed field fails correspondence, reorder changes identity and cannot admit, operator-id change changes identity, frame change changes identity, monolithic/empty vector refuses), monotone refusal, and a REAL store-issued receipt/body fixture probe over the four committed fields in addition to the synthetic negatives. FRAME: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; NO amendment; registry 77 (NO invariant added); ledger 11; CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added AND the conformance surface gains a gate; gates 100 -> 101. SCOPE-BOUNDED: additive substrate + one gate + this ADR ONLY; NO new constitutional surface; NO D_cap committed surface; NO standalone will/intent committed surface; NO law/schema/legend move; NO new receipt field; NO new invariant; NO terminal-outcome expansion; NO LM-2; NO CGP-S-04; NO dispatcher modification beyond the already-accepted SB-2a posture fix.",alternatives=["Ship SB-3a-core with NO ADR (Option B): NOT TAKEN (Governor) -- a named substrate layer with a closed committed-surface registry, a named aggregation operator, and a core/candidate boundary is a governed architectural decision audits must find in the ADR/CODEX trail, not buried in release text.","Promote D_cap (CGP capability evidence) into the committed trace vector now: REJECTED -- D_cap has no receipt commitment; admitting it would be a shadow/uncommitted admissibility surface (evidence-exists-elsewhere laundering). D_cap stays design-only/candidate until a commitment path is separately authorized.","Promote will/intent to a standalone committed surface: REJECTED -- no dedicated committed receipt field exists; it remains a sub-surface/input concern under D_c.","Claim D_c / D_m / D_j are independently re-derived: REJECTED (proof discipline) -- AD-21 rejected H_c/H_m/H_j pipeline replay; they are committed-body-bound and the gate says so honestly via verification_mode; only h_s and h_body are recomputed.","Formalize an FGA committed-surface invariant (an admissibility-conjunction law or CGP-S-04) now: NOT TAKEN -- wiring precedes formalization; r126 is descriptive/architectural and adds NO invariant."],consequences="UGK's previously-implicit FGA decision-surface/trace-vector structure is now a first-class, enumerable, frame-bound, conjunctively-aggregated substrate over the EXISTING four committed receipt axes, with a closed registry and a named operator. NOT CLAIMED: that a new constitutional surface or admissibility regime is created (it is an explicit committed-surface trace-vector substrate over existing axes); that D_c/D_m/D_j are independently replayed (committed-body-bound only); that CGP capability evidence is a constitutional surface (D_cap is candidate/design-only); that will/intent is a committed surface; that any law/schema/invariant moved. FRAME-STATIONARY (hashes): law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added); ADRs through AD-49 (47); gates 100 -> 101 (trace_vector_gate, a NEW ugk/conformance gate). r125 -> r126 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link; CODEX moves because AD-49 is added and the conformance surface gains a gate. ACCOMPANYING CORRECTIONS recorded in release text and continuity rationale (NOT separate ADRs): QH-1 (tools/grbsa/proof_model_b.py content-hash chain fallback, a verifier-consistency correction) and SB-2a (ugk/cgp/dispatch.py posture-aware conformance gate invocation under an isolated temporary conformance-fixture founding equivalent to the release verification posture -- published dev/test authority, NOT production founding -- moving the dispatcher ledger ERROR 2 -> 0 and PROVEN 8 -> 10). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: ugk/fga/ and trace_vector_gate are CERTIFIED/GATED conformance substrate; D_cap and any will/intent committed surface are DEFERRED (candidate/design-only), not implemented. STAGED ROADMAP: SB-3a-core (the explicit committed-surface trace-vector substrate) is LANDED; D_cap receipt-commitment, the LM-2 terminal-outcome model, and any FGA invariant formalization are separate, later, separately-authorized increments.",bound_invariants=["IEL-S-01","CTR-S-01"])

ADR_50=_adr(id="AD-50",context="r126 (AD-49, the FGA explicit committed-surface trace-vector substrate) was accepted as canonical. The accepted FGA/LM ordering then ran LM-2 -- the terminal-outcome model -- as design, corrected design, implementation plan, and quick-lane implementation, all accepted. The design was tightened so a partial/pending evaluation can NEVER collapse into REFUSE: REFUSE is constitutional negative evaluation over a COMPLETE TraceVector, while STRUCTURAL_ERROR is the inability to honestly evaluate. Two guardrails were ratified: defer_policy must be an EXPLICIT per-call object with no ambient default, and STRUCTURAL_ERROR must PRESERVE the original protocol/preflight diagnostic reason. The Governor authorized the r127 canonical lane to bundle the LM-2 additive classifier plus its gate with the two queued r126 errata, and authorized this descriptive ADR up front.",decision="r127 adds the LM-2 terminal-outcome classifier as ADDITIVE, READ-ONLY, DERIVATIONAL substrate plus one NEW conformance gate, labeling exactly one terminal outcome from existing signals WITHOUT replacing the kernel decision path, committing any receipt field, or moving schema/law. (1) NEW SUBSTRATE MODULE ugk/fga/terminal_outcome.py: a PURE classifier classify(root_conflict, trace, partial, structural_reason, defer_policy) -> TerminalOutcomeResult, model id terminal_outcome_model_v1 bound into every result identity. (2) CLOSED OUTCOME SET: ADMIT / REFUSE / DEFER / STRUCTURAL_ERROR / CRISIS -- exactly five, exhaustive, mutually exclusive. (3) DERIVED, NOT AUTHORITATIVE: the classifier PROJECTS what the kernel already decides (gate_admit -> ADMIT, gate_refuse -> REFUSE, ProtocolError -> STRUCTURAL_ERROR); gate_admit / gate_refuse / ProtocolError remain the authority; the classifier replaces nothing and commits nothing. (4) ADMIT/REFUSE require a COMPLETE SB-3a-core TraceVector decided by conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1 (ADMIT iff all committed surfaces PASS + integrity + frame; else REFUSE). (5) PartialEvaluationTrace is a TYPE-DISTINCT diagnostic/continuation record that can drive NEITHER ADMIT NOR REFUSE; passing it as a complete trace is rejected. (6) DEFER is EXPLICIT-POLICY-GATED: a defer outcome requires an explicit per-call DeferPolicy (reason + authority boundary + continuation condition) that authorizes the specific unresolved condition; there is NO ambient/global/default policy; DEFER emits no admit, runs no effect, and is never a soft admit; with no authorized policy an incomplete evaluation resolves to STRUCTURAL_ERROR, never DEFER and never REFUSE. (7) STRUCTURAL_ERROR PRESERVES the original protocol/preflight/non-evaluable reason (not-founded / undeclared / malformed-input / gate-exception / kernel-internal / non-evaluable) in the result reason and basis -- it is never a fog bank. (8) CRISIS is NARROW root/frame/jurisdiction disambiguation failure and is UNREACHABLE under single-root v0.1.0 (the classifier yields CRISIS only for an explicit root_conflict, which the single-root frame never produces); it is testable as a narrow future condition via a synthetic input. (9) PURE / NO EFFECT: classify performs no mutation and no effect; the result is a derived label whose identity is deterministic for fixed inputs and binds terminal_outcome_model_v1. (10) NO MONOLITHIC TERMINAL: the result basis records the displayed inputs that determined the outcome. (11) NEW CONFORMANCE GATE terminal_outcome_gate (ugk/conformance, exercising the ugk/fga substrate, registered in run_gates_batch; gates 101 -> 102) proves exhaustiveness, refuse/error separation, partial-not-complete, defer-not-admit, explicit-defer-policy, crisis-narrowness and single-root unreachability, trace/outcome correspondence, receipt-commitment honesty, no-monolithic-terminal, classifier purity / zero-effect DEFER, deterministic identity, and preserved STRUCTURAL_ERROR diagnostic specificity, using REAL SB-3a-core TraceVectors for ADMIT/REFUSE and synthetic inputs for DEFER/STRUCTURAL_ERROR/CRISIS. (12) BUNDLED ERRATA: this release also corrects two r126 claim/proof-hygiene errata -- the trace_vector_gate.py header no longer says the gate is unregistered, and AD-49 point (1) now names ugk/fga/ as the substrate package and ugk/conformance/trace_vector_gate.py as the gate location. FRAME: law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; NO amendment; registry 77 (NO invariant added); ledger 11; CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added AND the conformance surface gains a gate; gates 101 -> 102. SCOPE-BOUNDED: additive substrate + one gate + this ADR + two errata ONLY; NO committed terminal-outcome receipt field; NO committed trace_vector_hash; NO general DEFER continuation record; NO CRISIS record; NO law/schema/legend move; NO new invariant; NO D_cap; NO change to kernel authority; NO effect path from DEFER; NO LM-2 law/schema implementation.",alternatives=["Make the classifier the kernel enforced decision authority (replace gate_admit/gate_refuse): NOT TAKEN -- LM-2 is a derived labeling layer; the kernel remains the authority and the classifier projects, it does not replace. Enforcement would be a law move, separately authorized.","Commit the terminal outcome (a five-valued receipt field) or the trace_vector_hash now: DEFERRED -- both are schema moves; wiring precedes commitment. The outcome is a derived label in this increment.","Allow an ambient/default defer policy or let a partial/pending evaluation default to REFUSE: REJECTED (Governor guardrail) -- defer_policy is explicit and per-call; with no authorized policy an incomplete evaluation is STRUCTURAL_ERROR, never DEFER and never REFUSE; partial evaluation never collapses into constitutional refusal.","Collapse ProtocolError into a single opaque STRUCTURAL_ERROR: REJECTED (Governor guardrail) -- STRUCTURAL_ERROR preserves the original diagnostic reason/category; it is never a fog bank.","Treat CRISIS as a generic error bucket: REJECTED -- CRISIS is narrow root/frame/jurisdiction disambiguation failure, unreachable under single-root v0.1.0, never a catch-all.","Add a terminal-outcome invariant (a registry move) now: NOT TAKEN -- descriptive ADR only; wiring precedes formalization; no invariant added."],consequences="UGK now has a derived, read-only terminal-outcome labeling substrate over the r126 trace-vector substrate: it frames ADMIT/REFUSE/DEFER/STRUCTURAL_ERROR/CRISIS from existing signals without turning uncertainty into authority or partial evidence into constitutional refusal. NOT CLAIMED: that the classifier is the enforced kernel decision path (it is derived/read-only); that any terminal outcome is committed to a receipt (no field added); that trace_vector_hash is committed (no field added); that DEFER or CRISIS is reachable by default (DEFER requires an explicit policy; CRISIS requires a root conflict the single-root frame never produces); that any law/schema/invariant moved. FRAME-STATIONARY (hashes): law a3992e45 / schema a49e520e / legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 (no amendment); registry 77 (NO invariant added); ADRs through AD-50 (48); gates 101 -> 102 (terminal_outcome_gate, a NEW ugk/conformance gate). r126 -> r127 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link; CODEX moves because AD-50 is added and the conformance surface gains a gate. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: ugk/fga/terminal_outcome.py and terminal_outcome_gate are CERTIFIED/GATED conformance substrate; the committed terminal-outcome field, committed trace_vector_hash, general DEFER continuation record, CRISIS record, D_cap, and any enforced-authority or law/schema movement are DEFERRED (design/identified-only), not implemented. STAGED ROADMAP: the LM-2 additive classifier is LANDED; committing/enforcing the terminal-outcome model and D_cap are separate, later, separately-authorized increments.",bound_invariants=["IEL-S-01","CTR-S-01"])
ADR_51=_adr(id="AD-51",context="r127 (AD-50, the LM-2 additive read-only terminal-outcome classifier) was accepted as canonical. The Governor then authorized LM-2 Increment A -- COMMITTING the terminal-outcome projection in the receipt body. Two fail-closed halts were raised during implementation and ratified as correct. HALT 1 (circularity): the r127 FGA-TRACE-v1 trace-vector hash binds receipt.h_body, so committing trace_vector_hash INSIDE h_body would be circular (tvh = f(h_body) and h_body = g(tvh)); the Governor authorized the LAYERED Option B model instead. HALT 2 (amendment): adding committed receipt columns moves schema_hash, and AD-28 plus the continuity machinery require a schema-leg move to be carried by an admitted amendment record -- treating it as a recordless frame-stationary change would be silent semantics and would fail continuity; the Governor authorized a law-stationary, legend-stationary schema-leg amendment.",decision="r128 commits the LM-2 terminal-outcome projection inside UGK-BODY-v2 under the layered Option B model, carried by a schema-leg amendment. (1) VERSION DISPATCH: the existing committed version field is the body-schema key -- version=1 -> UGK-BODY-v1 (byte-unchanged), version=2 -> UGK-BODY-v2; there is no body_version. (2) BODY-COMMITTED (inside h_body, v2): terminal_outcome, terminal_outcome_model_id, terminal_outcome_reason. (3) SCHEMA-PERSISTED POST-BODY (a receipt column, NOT a member of h_body): trace_vector_hash, computed AFTER h_body via the UNCHANGED r127 FGA-TRACE-v1 and verified by recomputation -- present for ADMIT/REFUSE, null for STRUCTURAL_ERROR. There is NO FGA-TRACE-v2, NO body-excluded trace hash, and NO fixpoint. (4) CLOSED TYPE, NARROW EMISSION: terminal_outcome is typed over the closed five-set ADMIT / REFUSE / DEFER / STRUCTURAL_ERROR / CRISIS, but Increment A EMITS only ADMIT / REFUSE / STRUCTURAL_ERROR; DEFER and CRISIS are RESERVED and fail closed (ReservedOutcomeError) if emitted without their later support records. (5) DERIVED == COMMITTED: the committed label equals the r127 classifier projection -- gate_admit -> ADMIT, gate_refuse -> REFUSE, protocol_error -> STRUCTURAL_ERROR. (6) EFFECT-ABORT-NOT-REFUSE: a post-admit effect abort (failed=True on a normal op) commits ADMIT as the decision outcome with reason admitted-effect-aborted, never REFUSE. (7) SCHEMA MOVE VIA AMENDMENT: the four added nullable columns move schema_hash a49e520e -> 20c78e18, carried by an admitted law-stationary, legend-stationary schema-leg AmendmentRecord (amendment_hash 59d12806, ordinary, moved-leg = schema, prior_schema a49e520e -> successor_schema 20c78e18); ledger 11 -> 12; law a3992e45 + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 77 UNMOVED; no new invariant. (8) NEW CONFORMANCE GATE terminal_outcome_commit_gate (registered in run_gates_batch; gates 102 -> 103) proves derived == committed, trace_vector_hash recomputes from the final receipt INCLUDING h_body, trace_vector_hash is NOT in h_body, the terminal-outcome fields ARE in h_body, v1 and v2 receipts verify, DEFER/CRISIS are reserved-but-not-emittable, STRUCTURAL_ERROR preserves its reason, effect-abort-not-refuse, no D_cap dependency, and tamper/downgrade attempts fail closed. FRAME: schema a49e520e -> 20c78e18 MOVED (carried by the amendment); law a3992e45 + legend db3c177d UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 -> 12; registry 77 (no invariant); CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added AND the conformance surface gains a gate. SCOPE: this is a SCHEMA COMMITMENT of the terminal-outcome projection, NOT enforcement -- the kernel decision path (gate_admit / gate_refuse / protocol_error) remains authoritative until a later law/enforcement increment. SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO FGA-TRACE-v2; NO body-excluded trace hash; NO fixpoint; NO law move; NO legend move; NO new invariant; NO general DEFER continuation record; NO CRISIS root-conflict record; NO D_cap; NO kernel authority replacement; NO Increment B/C/D work.",alternatives=["Commit trace_vector_hash INSIDE h_body (body v2): REJECTED (fail-closed HALT 1) -- r127 FGA-TRACE-v1 binds h_body, so a body-committed trace hash is circular; the layered model commits the outcome fields in h_body and persists trace_vector_hash as a post-body schema column verified by recomputation.","Treat the committed-column schema move as a recordless frame-stationary change (no amendment): REJECTED (fail-closed HALT 2) -- AD-28 and the continuity machinery require a schema-leg move to be carried by an admitted amendment; skipping it is silent semantics and returns AMEND_NO (continuity failure).","Move law or legend, or add a terminal-outcome invariant, for the commitment: NOT TAKEN -- Increment A is a schema-leg move ONLY; enforcement and any law/registry move are later, separately-authorized increments.","Emit DEFER or CRISIS in Increment A: NOT TAKEN -- both are reserved values requiring their later support records; an attempt to commit them fails closed (ReservedOutcomeError).","Introduce FGA-TRACE-v2 or a body-excluded trace hash to avoid the circularity: REJECTED -- the r127 trace semantics are preserved exactly; the layering (post-body persistence) resolves the circularity without changing FGA-TRACE-v1."],consequences="UGK now BODY-COMMITS the LM-2 terminal-outcome projection (verification-grade, inside h_body v2) with a schema-persisted post-body trace_vector_hash recomputable from the final receipt. NOT CLAIMED: that the classifier is the enforced kernel decision authority (it remains derived/projective); that DEFER or CRISIS is emittable (both are reserved and fail closed); that trace_vector_hash is body-committed (it is a post-body schema column); that law, legend, or the invariant registry moved. FRAME: schema a49e520e -> 20c78e18 MOVED via amendment record 59d12806 (law-stationary, legend-stationary); law a3992e45 + legend db3c177d + registry 77 UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 11 -> 12; ADRs through AD-51 (49); gates 102 -> 103 (terminal_outcome_commit_gate). r127 -> r128 is an AMENDMENT continuity link (amendment_link = True, moved-leg = schema). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the body-v2 terminal-outcome commitment, the post-body trace_vector_hash, and terminal_outcome_commit_gate are CERTIFIED/GATED conformance substrate; enforcement of the terminal outcome, the general DEFER continuation record, the CRISIS root-conflict record, and D_cap remain DEFERRED (design/identified-only), not implemented. STAGED ROADMAP: LM-2 commitment is LANDED; enforcement (a later law increment), Increment B (DEFER record), Increment C (CRISIS), and Increment D (enforcement invariant) are separate, later, separately-authorized increments.",bound_invariants=["IEL-S-01","CTR-S-01"])
ADR_52=_adr(id="AD-52",context="r128 (AD-51, LM-2 Increment A body-v2 terminal-outcome commitment) was accepted as canonical. A Roadmap Exhaustion checkpoint then selected D_cap as the next risk class (lower risk than LM-2 enforcement, continuing the wiring -> commitment -> enforcement spine). The Lane 4a D_cap design pass was accepted with one wording correction: in this increment D_cap is NOT a full aggregating FGA decision surface; it is a COMMITTED CAPABILITY-EVIDENCE surface (a candidate decision surface) that is committed and verified but does NOT participate in conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1 and does NOT affect ADMIT/REFUSE. The design passed every halt check: no law move, no new invariant, no contradiction with the four-surface committed registry (it extends via a sibling registry), no circular hash dependency, CGP evidence stable enough to bind by ledger_hash, and no laundering of WAIVED/GAP/ERROR/NOT-RUN/BY-CONSTRUCTION into authority. The Governor authorized Lane 4b implementation under the corrected terminology.",decision="r129 commits CGP capability evidence as D_cap, a COMMITTED CAPABILITY-EVIDENCE / CANDIDATE decision surface that is NON-AGGREGATING, carried by a law-stationary schema-leg amendment. (1) VERSION LADDER: version is the body-schema key and is monotonic -- version=1 -> UGK-BODY-v1, version=2 -> UGK-BODY-v2, version=3 -> UGK-BODY-v3 with v3 a superset of v2 (a capability-evidence receipt also commits the terminal outcome); v1 and v2 bodies are byte-identical. (2) BODY-COMMITTED (inside h_body, v3): h_cap, capability_evidence_model_id, the bound ledger_hash, registry_version, and scope_id. (3) BINDING: h_cap is produced by a PURE helper over the r125 CGP CapabilityEvidenceLedger that is NON-LAUNDERING -- it fails closed on a ledger that does not self-verify, records the closed seven-verdict census (PROVEN / FAIL / GAP / WAIVED / BY-CONSTRUCTION / NOT-RUN / ERROR) FAITHFULLY with no collapse and no upgrade, keeps WAIVED AUTHORITY-MARKED and separate from the verdict census, and NEVER synthesizes PROVEN (external / Navigator-realized evidence cannot become UGK PROVEN by mere existence). (4) NON-AGGREGATING: D_cap lives in a SIBLING registry (CAPABILITY_SURFACES), NOT in COMMITTED_SURFACES; conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1 / aggregate() is UNCHANGED and consumes EXACTLY the four surfaces D_s/D_c/D_m/D_j; D_cap does NOT enter the conjunction and does NOT affect ADMIT/REFUSE; the closed four-surface committed guard is NOT loosened (a sibling guard admits h_cap). (5) trace_vector_hash remains the r127/r128 FGA-TRACE-v1 post-body hash over the FOUR aggregating surfaces (h_cap is NOT in it; h_cap is external-ledger-derived so there is no circularity with h_body, trace_vector_hash, or FGA-TRACE-v1). (6) NO RETROACTIVE REINTERPRETATION: v1/v2 receipts keep their bodies, hashes, and outcomes; verify_receipt_bodies and the trace re-derivation are made v3-aware while v1/v2 stay byte-identical. (7) SCHEMA MOVE VIA AMENDMENT: five added nullable columns move schema_hash 20c78e18 -> 0d05dc56, carried by an admitted law-stationary, legend-stationary schema-leg AmendmentRecord (amendment_hash bd3dfe14, ordinary, moved-leg = schema, prior_schema 20c78e18 -> successor_schema 0d05dc56); ledger 12 -> 13; law a3992e45 + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 77 UNMOVED; no new invariant. (8) NEW CONFORMANCE GATE capability_evidence_commit_gate (registered; gates 103 -> 104) proves h_cap recomputes from the exact ledger, ledger_hash self-verifies (and corrupt ledgers fail closed), the verdict census is faithful and the seven verdicts stay distinct, WAIVED stays authority-marked, no PROVEN synthesis, D_cap is absent from aggregate(), terminal_outcome is unchanged by D_cap, trace_vector_hash stays FGA-TRACE-v1 over four surfaces, v1/v2 are not reinterpreted, v3 verifies, and h_cap tamper / v3 downgrade fail closed. FRAME: schema 20c78e18 -> 0d05dc56 MOVED (via the amendment); law a3992e45 + legend db3c177d + registry 77 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; ledger 12 -> 13; CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added AND the conformance surface gains a gate. SCOPE: this is a SCHEMA COMMITMENT of capability evidence, NOT enforcement, and D_cap is NON-AGGREGATING -- the kernel decision path and the four-surface aggregation remain authoritative until a later, separately-authorized enforcement/law increment may decide whether and how D_cap becomes decision-authoritative. This release also FOLDS IN the five held doc/tool hygiene edits (two conformance docstrings, two doc notes, make_release.sh retirement), declared SEPARATELY from the D_cap semantic payload. SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law move; NO legend move; NO new invariant; NO change to aggregation; NO FGA-TRACE-v2; NO body-excluded capability hash; NO fixpoint; NO LM-2 Increment D enforcement; NO general DEFER record; NO CRISIS record; NO Invariant E lane; NO EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE lane; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=["Add D_cap to COMMITTED_SURFACES (make it aggregating) now: REJECTED -- aggregate() requires the displayed vector to BE exactly the four-surface set in canonical order, so adding D_cap would retroactively force every v1/v2 receipt to REFUSE (incomplete-or-reordered-surface-vector) and would make capability evidence decision-authoritative without authorization. D_cap is committed but NON-aggregating.","Loosen the closed four-surface committed guard to admit h_cap: REJECTED -- the aggregating guard stays closed over h_s/h_c/h_m/h_j; D_cap is admitted via a SIBLING capability registry and guard, never by weakening the four-surface invariant.","Launder WAIVED/GAP/ERROR/NOT-RUN/BY-CONSTRUCTION into PASS or PROVEN: REJECTED -- the binding records each verdict faithfully, keeps WAIVED authority-marked, and never synthesizes PROVEN; and because D_cap is non-aggregating it cannot turn any capability state into ADMIT authority at all this increment.","Introduce FGA-TRACE-v2, a body-excluded capability hash, or a fixpoint to carry h_cap: NOT TAKEN -- h_cap is body-committed in UGK-BODY-v3 and external-ledger-derived, so there is no circularity; FGA-TRACE-v1 and the post-body trace_vector_hash are preserved exactly.","Move law or add a capability invariant for D_cap now: NOT TAKEN -- the commitment is a schema-leg move only; making D_cap decision-authoritative (enforcement) is a later, separately-authorized increment that may require an invariant and a law move."],consequences="UGK now BODY-COMMITS CGP capability evidence as D_cap (verification-grade, inside h_body v3), bound to an exact CapabilityEvidenceLedger by ledger_hash, WITHOUT making it decision authority. NOT CLAIMED: that D_cap participates in ADMIT/REFUSE (it is NON-aggregating); that any capability state (WAIVED/GAP/ERROR/NOT-RUN/BY-CONSTRUCTION) is laundered into authority or PROVEN; that trace_vector_hash or the four-surface aggregation changed; that law, legend, or the invariant registry moved. FRAME: schema 20c78e18 -> 0d05dc56 MOVED via amendment record bd3dfe14 (law-stationary, legend-stationary); law a3992e45 + legend db3c177d + registry 77 UNMOVED; genesis 5fe68bbc preserved; ledger 12 -> 13; ADRs through AD-52 (50); gates 103 -> 104 (capability_evidence_commit_gate). r128 -> r129 is an AMENDMENT continuity link (amendment_link = True, moved-leg = schema). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the v3 capability-evidence commitment, the pure non-laundering binding helper, and capability_evidence_commit_gate are CERTIFIED/GATED conformance substrate; D_cap ENFORCEMENT (entering conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1) and any enforcement invariant / law move remain DEFERRED (design/identified-only), not implemented. This release also folds in the five held doc/tool hygiene edits (terminal_outcome_gate + trace_vector_gate docstrings, the architecture and release-closure doc notes, and the make_release.sh retirement), declared SEPARATELY in change-confinement so they are not the release semantic payload. STAGED ROADMAP: the D_cap capability-evidence commitment is LANDED; D_cap enforcement, LM-2 Increment D, the DEFER/CRISIS records, Invariant E, and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program remain separate, later, separately-authorized work.",bound_invariants=["IEL-S-01","CTR-S-01"])
ADR_53=_adr(id="AD-53",context="r129 (AD-52, the D_cap committed capability-evidence surface) was accepted as canonical. The shared committed-projection -> decision-authority enforcement-pattern design pass was then accepted, establishing the wiring-precedes-formalization -> law-leg-formalization pattern and recommending namespace 2b/2c constitutionalization as the SAFEST FIRST LAW MOVE of this era (narrow, precedent-backed by the r70 2a constitutionalization, and NOT a central-path refusal change). The namespace 2b/2c law-promotion design pass was accepted with one wording clarification ratified into NS-S-04: delegation is SCOPED NON-OWNERSHIP authority and does NOT itself confer lifecycle authority. The Governor ratified the exact three-invariant text and authorized the r130 implementation lane. Before the law move, the IR was verified to MATCH the ratified text 26/26 (owner-only lifecycle; delegate confers no lifecycle authority; supersession transfers and drops delegations; revoke/invalidate permanent across allocate, supersede, and adjudicate; non-Governor adjudication refused; no wall-clock) -- the no-mismatch halt check.",decision="r130 CONSTITUTIONALIZES the namespace 2b/2c ownership-lifecycle authority via a LAW-LEG amendment -- the FIRST law move of this era. Three invariants are added to invariants.py (the law-bearing surface; law_hash = SHA-256(invariants.py bytes)). (1) NS-S-04 (owner-authority for lifecycle ops): delegation, revocation, invalidation, and supersession take effect ONLY when the receipt authority is the current owner; a non-owner lifecycle op is fail-closed (REFUSED, never folded, ownership unchanged); delegation grants SCOPED authority without transferring ownership and confers NO lifecycle authority; supersession transfers ownership to a named new owner; delegation and supersession must not be collapsed. (2) NS-S-05 (permanence + no-clock determinism): revocation and invalidation PERMANENTLY remove a name (WILL-S-04 pattern) -- never re-granted by later allocation, supersession, or adjudication; expiration is NOT a separate primitive (only a removal reason folded onto revoke/invalidate, the E4 ruling); the ownership projection reads NO wall-clock and admits no TTL/expiry/expires_at. (3) NS-S-06 (Governor-only adjudication): adjudication of a contested name is constitutional-Governor-only; a non-Governor adjudication is fail-closed; adjudication cannot resurrect a revoked/invalidated name (NS-S-05 absolute). RATIFICATION, NOT BEHAVIOR CHANGE: the namespace_governance._project fold is UNCHANGED; the 2b/2c IR (realized r74) already enforced these rules; constitutionalization NAMES them as law without altering the projection, so no prior namespace receipt is reinterpreted (forward-only ratification). CARRIAGE: law-leg AmendmentRecord 14 (ordinary, amendment_hash f3a54942), invariants_added = NS-S-04/NS-S-05/NS-S-06, law a3992e45 -> 499ec390 MOVED; legend db3c177d + schema 0d05dc56 STATIONARY (uncommitted legs, verified unchanged frame-general); ledger 13 -> 14; prior_amendment = record 13; registry 77 -> 80. namespace_governance_gate is EXTENDED IN PLACE (no new gate) to prove NS-S-04/05/06: owner-only lifecycle, the delegate-confers-no-lifecycle clarification, permanence across allocate+supersede+adjudicate, no-clock determinism, Governor-only adjudication, and no resurrection; the three invariants bind gate=namespace_governance_gate. FRAME: LAW MOVED a3992e45 -> 499ec390 (via the amendment); legend db3c177d + schema 0d05dc56 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 77 -> 80; ledger 13 -> 14; CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added AND the conformance surface changes. SCOPE: this constitutionalizes an ISOLATED, already-enforced ownership subsystem; it makes NO central-path change, adds NO new refusal cause (every refusal it names already happened in the IR), moves NO schema or legend, and the no-clock determinism property becomes LAW. The membership namespace NAMESPACE_PHI_0 is a separate constitutional concern and is untouched. SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO D_cap enforcement; NO terminal-outcome enforcement; NO Invariant E; NO EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE; NO DEFER record; NO CRISIS record; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=["Promote 2b/2c as ONE combined invariant: REJECTED -- three legible invariants mirror the 2a NS-S-01/02/03 granularity and are separately refusable; one omnibus invariant would fuse authority, permanence, and adjudication.","Split no-clock determinism into a fourth standalone invariant: NOT TAKEN -- the no-clock clause rides in NS-S-05 where expiration-as-removal-reason already lives; a four-way split was offered as an option and the Governor ratified three.","Change the _project fold during constitutionalization: REJECTED -- this is RATIFICATION of existing IR; altering the fold would be a behavior change and a retroactivity risk. The fold is unchanged.","Treat delegation as conferring lifecycle authority: REJECTED (Governor clarification) -- delegation is scoped non-ownership authority; lifecycle ops are owner-only and adjudication is Governor-only, proven by the gate (a delegate cannot revoke/invalidate/supersede).","Reintroduce clock/TTL expiry as a primitive: REJECTED -- the E4 ruling collapses expiration onto revoke/invalidate as a removal reason; determinism is sacred; NS-S-05 forbids any wall-clock/TTL in the projection."],consequences="Namespace 2b/2c ownership-lifecycle authority is now CONSTITUTIONAL (NS-S-04/05/06), and the no-clock determinism property is now LAW. NOT CLAIMED: that any prior namespace receipt is reinterpreted (the fold is unchanged; forward-only ratification); that the central kernel decision path or aggregate() changed (untouched); that schema or legend moved; that any NEW refusal cause was added (the IR already refused non-owner/non-Governor/re-grant-of-removed). FRAME: LAW MOVED a3992e45 -> 499ec390 via amendment record 14 (f3a54942; ordinary; law-leg; legend + schema stationary); legend db3c177d + schema 0d05dc56 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 77 -> 80; ledger 13 -> 14; ADRs through AD-53 (51); gates stay 104 (namespace_governance_gate extended in place, no new gate). r129 -> r130 is the FIRST LAW-LEG continuity link of this era (amendment_link = True, moved_legs = [law]) -- prior r12x links were schema-leg; the only earlier law moves are the founding-era records (record 2 was the 2a precedent). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: NS-S-04/05/06 are CONSTITUTIONAL/CERTIFIED and the no-clock property is law; D_cap enforcement, terminal-outcome enforcement, Invariant E, the DEFER/CRISIS records, EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE, and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program remain deferred, each separately authorized.",bound_invariants=["NS-S-04","NS-S-05","NS-S-06"])
ADR_54=_adr(id="AD-54",context="r130 (AD-53, the FIRST modern law move -- namespace 2b/2c constitutionalization) was accepted. A post-r130 roadmap checkpoint classified the remaining frontiers and selected terminal-outcome correspondence enforcement as the next lane: a central-path RATIFICATION law (the committed terminal-outcome projection already equals the kernel decision on the derived path) rather than a new refusal surface. The design pass was accepted with one required tightening ratified into TO-S-01: the invariant binds the whole committed projection TUPLE (terminal_outcome, terminal_outcome_model_id, terminal_outcome_reason), not only the outcome enum, so a receipt with the right outcome but a false/corrupted reason or model id cannot satisfy the correspondence law (diagnostic specificity is part of the integrity claim). Before the law move the tuple correspondence was verified provable 11/11 against the current substrate (ADMIT/REFUSE/STRUCTURAL_ERROR/effect-abort correspond; override-outcome, wrong-reason, wrong-model-id, and non-protocol-op STRUCTURAL_ERROR mismatches fail closed; DEFER/CRISIS reserved; v1 out of scope).",decision="r131 CONSTITUTIONALIZES terminal-outcome correspondence as TO-S-01 via an ORDINARY LAW-LEG amendment -- the SECOND modern law move. One invariant is added to invariants.py (law_hash = SHA-256(invariants.py bytes)). TO-S-01: where a receipt commits a terminal-outcome projection under UGK-BODY version >= 2, the committed TUPLE (terminal_outcome / terminal_outcome_model_id / terminal_outcome_reason) MUST correspond to the kernel decision signal recomputed from stored fields under the declared model -- op==gate_refuse -> REFUSE, op==protocol_error -> STRUCTURAL_ERROR (preserved reason), otherwise ADMIT. A divergence in ANY tuple element is a constitutional INTEGRITY violation (a corrupt, non-conformant receipt that fails closed at verification, the IEL species), NOT a re-decision of the op. RATIFICATION, NOT BEHAVIOR CHANGE: the kernel decision path (gate_admit / gate_refuse / protocol_error) remains the deciding authority; TO-S-01 adds NO new refusal cause. A post-admit effect abort (failed=True after admission) remains ADMIT (admitted-effect-aborted), never REFUSE -- correspondence binds the admissibility decision, not effect success. DEFER and CRISIS remain RESERVED (ReservedOutcomeError). v1 receipts (no committed tuple) are NOT reinterpreted (version >= 2 scope). CARRIAGE: law-leg AmendmentRecord 15 (ordinary, amendment_hash 8d695639), invariants_added = TO-S-01, law 499ec390 -> 80d7b8f0 MOVED; legend db3c177d + schema 0d05dc56 STATIONARY (uncommitted legs, verified unchanged frame-general); ledger 14 -> 15; prior_amendment = record 14; registry 80 -> 81. terminal_outcome_commit_gate is EXTENDED IN PLACE (no new gate; gates stay 104; check 13) to prove the tuple correspondence on real-shape ADMIT/REFUSE/STRUCTURAL_ERROR/effect-abort receipts and to fail closed on override-outcome, wrong-reason, wrong-model-id, and non-protocol-op STRUCTURAL_ERROR mismatches; TO-S-01 binds gate=terminal_outcome_commit_gate. FRAME: LAW MOVED 499ec390 -> 80d7b8f0; legend db3c177d + schema 0d05dc56 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 80 -> 81; ledger 14 -> 15; CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added and the conformance surface changes. SCOPE: NO schema move; NO legend move; NO change to aggregate() or FGA-TRACE-v1; NO new refusal cause. SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO D_cap enforcement; NO D_cap sufficiency policy; NO Invariant E; NO EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE; NO DEFER record; NO CRISIS record; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=["Bind TO-S-01 to the outcome enum only: REJECTED (Governor tightening) -- a receipt with the correct outcome but a false/corrupted reason or model id would satisfy a weaker law and puncture diagnostic specificity; the tuple (outcome, model_id, reason) is bound.","Treat correspondence as a new admissibility refusal cause: REJECTED -- a mismatch is a CORRUPT receipt (fail-closed at verification, the IEL integrity species), not a re-decision; the kernel decision path remains authority and no op outcome changes.","Wire commitment into the live kernel decision path in this lane: NOT TAKEN -- TO-S-01 enforces correspondence wherever the tuple is committed; wiring the kernel to commit terminal_outcome on the live path is separate and not in scope.","Recompute correspondence from live/derived state: REJECTED -- like IEL-S-01, the recompute is a pure deterministic function of stored fields (op, failed, intent), so clean receipts never false-positive.","Move schema to carry enforcement: NOT TAKEN -- terminal_outcome was already committed in v2 (r128); enforcement is law-only, schema stationary."],consequences="Terminal-outcome correspondence is now CONSTITUTIONAL (TO-S-01): a committed projection tuple that diverges from the recomputed kernel signal fails closed at verification. NOT CLAIMED: that the kernel decision path changed (it remains authority); that any op outcome changed or any new refusal cause was added; that the live kernel now commits terminal_outcome on every receipt (commitment remains opt-in; TO-S-01 governs it wherever used); that schema, legend, or aggregate()/FGA-TRACE-v1 moved; that v1 receipts are reinterpreted. FRAME: LAW MOVED 499ec390 -> 80d7b8f0 via amendment record 15 (8d695639; ordinary; law-leg; legend + schema stationary); legend db3c177d + schema 0d05dc56 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 80 -> 81; ledger 14 -> 15; ADRs through AD-54 (52); gates stay 104 (terminal_outcome_commit_gate extended in place). r130 -> r131 is an AMENDMENT continuity link (amendment_link = True, moved_legs = [law]) -- the SECOND law-leg link of this era, reusing the r130-proven law-leg template. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: TO-S-01 is CONSTITUTIONAL/CERTIFIED. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: D_cap enforcement (needs a jurisdiction-bound sufficiency policy), Invariant E / scoped effect-law (co-design with EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE), EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE IR, the DEFER continuation record, the CRISIS / multi-root prerequisite, and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program.",bound_invariants=["TO-S-01"])
ADR_55=_adr(id="AD-55",context="r131 (AD-54, terminal-outcome correspondence TO-S-01 -- the SECOND modern law move) was accepted as canonical. The EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE IR design pass was then accepted with one Governor tightening: the compensation arc must be SEPARATELY GOVERNED and SEPARATELY IDEMPOTENT -- it must not run as a hidden side effect of COMMIT, it must write its own intent receipt BEFORE the compensating action, and it must carry a distinct compensation idempotency scope, never ambiguously reusing the forward effect idempotency_key. Grounding confirmed the lane is frame-stationary IR: EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE is realized entirely at the parameters-JSON level (NO schema column), the orphan-PREPARE detector and governed reconciliation exist, EffectAtomicity.EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE was declared-but-unimplemented and failed closed, and compensation failure is representable at the parameter level WITHOUT new committed fields. All seven halt conditions cleared. The Governor authorized the r132 implementation and certification lane.",decision="r132 IMPLEMENTS EffectAtomicity.EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE (the compensation/saga effect class) as FRAME-STATIONARY IR -- NO law, NO schema, NO legend, NO new invariant -- mirroring the EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE parameter-level model. (1) KERNEL PREFLIGHT: the EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE branch no longer fails closed-as-unimplemented; it now REQUIRES a non-empty caller-supplied idempotency_key for the FORWARD effect (missing/empty -> ProtocolError, ZERO mutation, before gate_admit -- the AD-37 posture, mirroring AD-44). (2) FORWARD TRAIL (_execute_external_reversible + _emit_reversible): PREPARE (intent-to-act, depth 0, BEFORE the effect; NBER-1; carries idempotency_key + gate_admit_ref) -> effect() -> COMMIT (confirmed performed, AFTER the effect) | ABORT (ExternalEffectNotPerformed -> confirmed NOT performed, failed=True) | no-terminal+re-raise (any other exception -> orphan PREPARE, in-doubt). Identical in shape to the AD-44 trail; NOT inside store.transaction() (an external act is not store-rollback-able); an uncertain forward failure stays the ADMIT decision (gate_admit durable), NEVER a REFUSE. (3) COMPENSATION ARC (compensate_external_reversible) -- the Governor tightening, enforced: a committed forward effect MAY be OFFSET by a NEW FORWARD compensating action, but ONLY via this SEPARATE governed call -- NEVER a hidden side effect of COMMIT. It writes its OWN COMPENSATE intent receipt at depth 0 BEFORE the compensating action (receipt-before-effect all the way down) and carries its OWN DISTINCT compensation idempotency scope (a dedicated compensation_idempotency_key, or the deterministic composite compose_compensation_key). COMPENSATE -> compensation_effect() -> COMPENSATED (offset confirmed; the forward COMMIT STILL STANDS) | COMPENSATION_FAILED (failed=True, UNRESOLVED execution status -- forward performed, offset failed; NEVER a REFUSE, NEVER a false success). (4) FAIL-CLOSED COMPENSATION CONTRACT (CompensationRefused, writing NOTHING, running no action): authority required; compensation_idempotency_key required and non-empty (missing fails closed); the compensation key MUST be DISTINCT from the forward effect idempotency_key (ambiguous reuse fails closed); prepare_ref must name a COMMITTED, not-yet-compensated forward EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE effect (aborted, in-doubt, unknown, or already-compensated all fail closed -- at most one compensation arc per forward COMMIT). (5) DETECTOR ugk/integrity/external_reversible.py (mirrors external_irreversible.py): PURE, DETERMINISTIC, CLOCK-FREE scans -- detect_orphan_prepares (forward PREPARE with no commit/abort terminal sharing key+prepare_ref) and detect_orphan_compensates (COMPENSATE with no compensated/compensation_failed terminal sharing compensate_ref+compensation key) -- plus find_committed_forward (the compensation guard). The detectors NEVER auto-resolve and NEVER infer an outcome; outstanding in-doubts fail closed at any verifier requiring a clean terminal. (6) NO PHYSICAL UNDO: compensation is a forward OFFSET; the forward COMMIT is NEVER erased (COMPENSATED is an additional receipt; the COMMIT h_r persists unchanged); the kernel NEVER claims the forward act was physically undone (mirroring the AD-44 never-claims-undone discipline). (7) ALL MARKERS PARAMETER-LEVEL: phase, effect_atomicity, idempotency_key, prepare_ref, compensate_ref, compensation_idempotency_key, abort_reason, gate_admit_ref live in parameters-JSON in the EXISTING receipt shape -- NO schema column. (8) NEW CONFORMANCE GATE external_reversible_gate (registered in run_gates_batch; gates 104 -> 105) proves the 16-point required-evidence set: forward + compensation receipt-before-effect; success->COMMIT key-verbatim; confirmed-not-performed->ABORT; uncertain->orphan PREPARE with ADMIT preserved and NO gate_refuse; COMMIT historically true after COMPENSATED (offset not erasure); COMPENSATION_FAILED unresolved-not-REFUSE; orphan PREPARE and orphan COMPENSATE detected; detectors never auto-resolve; missing original key, missing/ambiguous/reused compensation key, and non-compensable forward refs all fail closed; no physical-undo claim; anti-vacuity. (9) RELAY PROPAGATION: broker_propagation_gate (extended in place, new check 7) and the GRBSA adapter_atomicity_propagation_gate (extended, new check e3) prove EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE WITH a key now PROCEEDS through both relays (class + key propagated verbatim into the reversible COMMIT) and WITHOUT a key fails closed (missing-key); effect_atomicity_declaration_gate (b) updated -- EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE without a key fails closed (missing-key), no longer unimplemented. FRAME: law 80d7b8f0 + schema 0d05dc56 + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 81 + amendment ledger 15 + genesis 5fe68bbc ALL UNMOVED; NO amendment; gates 104 -> 105 (external_reversible_gate); CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added AND the conformance surface gains a gate. SCOPE: this WIRES the reversible effect class; it does NOT formalize Invariant E. SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law move; NO schema move; NO legend move; NO new invariant; NO Invariant E formalization; NO terminal-outcome semantic change; NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER record; NO CRISIS record; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=["Run compensation as an automatic side effect of COMMIT: REJECTED (Governor tightening) -- compensation must be SEPARATELY GOVERNED with its own intent receipt before the compensating action; an automatic offset would break receipt-before-effect for the compensation step and hide a forward external action behind a COMMIT.","Reuse the forward effect idempotency_key for the compensation: REJECTED (Governor tightening) -- the compensation arc carries a DISTINCT compensation idempotency scope; an ambiguous reuse fails closed, so a forward effect and its offset are never deduplicated against each other.","Represent compensation or compensation-failure with new committed schema columns: NOT TAKEN -- all phases live in parameters-JSON in the existing receipt shape (mirroring _emit_irreversible), so the schema is stationary; a committed/verification-grade saga surface would be a later schema move.","Write a structural abort receipt on an uncertain forward failure: NOT TAKEN -- mirroring AD-44, an uncertain forward failure leaves a bare orphan PREPARE (the honest in-doubt residue); the kernel infers no outcome, the detector reports it, and the admission decision stays ADMIT.","Claim COMPENSATED physically undoes the forward act, or erase the forward COMMIT: REJECTED -- compensation is a forward OFFSET; the COMMIT persists unchanged; the kernel never claims physical reversal (the substrate cannot prove it).","Add bounded terminal-write retry (AD-46) to the reversible terminals now: NOT TAKEN -- the minimal-surgical first implementation mirrors the pre-r121 AD-44 posture (a transient terminal-write failure leaves an orphan, detector-reported); bounded retry is a later hardening if desired.","Formalize Invariant E now that all five classes are wired: DEFERRED -- E is a scoped effect-law co-design, separately authorized; wiring precedes formalization."],consequences="EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE (compensation/saga) is now IMPLEMENTED as frame-stationary IR: a forward PREPARE/COMMIT/ABORT/orphan trail plus a SEPARATELY-GOVERNED, SEPARATELY-IDEMPOTENT compensation arc (COMPENSATE/COMPENSATED/COMPENSATION_FAILED/orphan), all at the parameter level, with a pure clock-free in-doubt detector that never auto-resolves. NOT CLAIMED: that compensation physically undoes the forward act (it is a forward OFFSET; the COMMIT stays historically true); that an uncertain forward or compensation failure is a REFUSE (both are execution status under a preserved ADMIT decision); that any committed field, schema, law, legend, or invariant moved; that Invariant E is formalized (it is not -- the reversible wiring is its precondition, not its formalization). FRAME: law 80d7b8f0 + schema 0d05dc56 + legend db3c177d + registry 81 + ledger 15 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; NO amendment; ADRs through AD-55 (53); gates 104 -> 105 (external_reversible_gate). r131 -> r132 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []); CODEX moves because AD-55 is added and the conformance surface gains a gate. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE forward trail, the separately-governed compensation arc, the in-doubt detector, external_reversible_gate, and the extended relay gates are CERTIFIED/GATED substrate; a committed/verification-grade saga surface, bounded terminal-write retry for the reversible terminals, a governed compensation-reconciliation op, and Invariant E formalization remain DEFERRED (design/identified-only), each separately authorized. STAGED ROADMAP: with EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE landed, ALL FIVE EffectAtomicity classes (PURE/STORE_LOCAL/EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE/EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE plus the NON_ATOMIC bridge) are wired -- the precondition for a scoped Invariant E co-design; D_cap enforcement, the DEFER/CRISIS records, and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program remain separate, later, separately-authorized work.",bound_invariants=["GK-S-02","EH-S-02","PERSIST-S-01"])
ADR_56=_adr(id="AD-56",context="r132 (AD-55, EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE compensation/saga implemented as frame-stationary IR) was accepted as canonical. The post-r132 Invariant E / scoped effect-law DESIGN pass was then run and accepted as Option A (smallest safe invariant) with TWO Governor wording corrections: (1) the invariant is EFFECT-TRAIL INTEGRITY, a class-relative claim that the recorded trail honestly conforms to the declared effect class -- NOT a strong claim that every effect is atomic; (2) the accepted D_cap enforcement pattern is a SIBLING refusal precondition OUTSIDE aggregation, so D_cap enforcement is higher-risk for introducing a new refusal cause and requiring a sufficiency policy, NOT for altering conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1 / aggregate(). The Governor ratified the exact EFFECT-S-01 text and authorized the r133 law lane.",decision="r133 CONSTITUTIONALIZES effect-trail integrity as EFFECT-S-01 via an ORDINARY LAW-LEG amendment -- the THIRD modern law move. One invariant is added to invariants.py (law_hash = SHA-256(invariants.py bytes)). EFFECT-S-01 is a CLASS-RELATIVE trail-integrity invariant (the IEL integrity species), explicitly NOT a claim that every effect is atomic: where a receipt declares an effect atomicity class or phase, the recorded trail must conform to that class realized protocol. PURE/STORE_LOCAL may assert rollback-backed atomicity via the AD-34/36 store-local seam (no two-phase phase markers); EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE follows PREPARE/COMMIT/ABORT/in-doubt (AD-44); EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE follows the forward PREPARE/COMMIT/ABORT plus the SEPARATELY-GOVERNED COMPENSATE/COMPENSATED/COMPENSATION_FAILED arc (AD-55); COMMIT/ABORT/COMPENSATED/COMPENSATION_FAILED terminals must be anchored to their prior intent records; a successful terminal must not be recorded when the effect/compensation did not perform; orphan PREPARE/COMPENSATE are honest in-doubt residue (detector-reported, never auto-resolved, NOT corruption); COMPENSATED is an OFFSET not erasure (the forward COMMIT stays historically true); COMPENSATION_FAILED is unresolved execution status, NOT a constitutional REFUSE; NON_ATOMIC remains an explicit bridge claiming no two-phase compliance. A class-mismatched trail, a terminal with no anchoring intent record, or a false success is a constitutional INTEGRITY violation (corrupt receipt, fail-closed at verification), NOT a re-decision. RATIFICATION, NOT BEHAVIOR CHANGE: EFFECT-S-01 ratifies the realized effect-class wiring; it adds NO new refusal cause and does NOT mutate terminal-outcome semantics -- a post-admit effect abort remains ADMIT (admitted-effect-aborted), never REFUSE (TO-S-01 preserved). CARRIAGE: law-leg AmendmentRecord 16 (ordinary, amendment_hash 54ac06d5), invariants_added = EFFECT-S-01, law 80d7b8f0 -> 7f28d368 MOVED; legend db3c177d + schema 0d05dc56 STATIONARY (uncommitted legs, verified unchanged); ledger 15 -> 16; prior_amendment = record 15; registry 81 -> 82. NEW conformance gate effect_trail_integrity_gate hosts the PURE cross-class recompute verifier verify_effect_trail_integrity and binds EFFECT-S-01 (gates 105 -> 106); a dedicated gate is STRUCTURALLY NECESSARY because EFFECT-S-01 is a CROSS-CLASS integrity recompute that no single-class exercise gate (class12 / irreversible / reversible / declaration) can host without distortion -- the extend-vs-new judgment the Governor delegated. It proves no-false-success, terminal-implies-anchor, class-relative conformance, PURE/STORE_LOCAL rollback-backed behavior, EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE and EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE trail discipline, COMPENSATED-not-erasure, COMPENSATION_FAILED-not-REFUSE, orphan exemption, NON_ATOMIC-claims-no-compliance, and TO-S-01 effect-abort separation, over real kernel trails (conformant) and synthetic corrupt trails (flagged). EFFECT-S-01 is added to SCI typing (category IR, mirroring TO-S-01). This release ALSO folds the queued r132 claim/proof-hygiene erratum: the kernel.py execute() docstring line and the EffectAtomicity enum docstring line that still called EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE unimplemented / later are corrected to AD-55; declared SEPARATELY in change-confinement, not the release semantic payload. FRAME: LAW MOVED 80d7b8f0 -> 7f28d368; legend db3c177d + schema 0d05dc56 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 81 -> 82; ledger 15 -> 16; CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added, an invariant is added, and the conformance surface gains a gate. SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO schema move; NO legend move; NO D_cap enforcement; NO D_cap sufficiency enactment; NO DEFER record; NO CRISIS record; NO terminal-outcome semantic change; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=["Name EFFECT-S-01 effect-atomicity in the strong sense: REJECTED (Governor wording correction) -- it is effect-TRAIL integrity, class-relative; it does NOT claim every effect is atomic (the external classes are explicitly non-atomic with honest in-doubt residue).","Prove EFFECT-S-01 by extending a single existing effect gate in place: NOT TAKEN -- EFFECT-S-01 is a CROSS-CLASS trail-integrity recompute; no single-class exercise gate can host it without distortion, so a dedicated effect_trail_integrity_gate is structurally necessary. This is the documented extend-vs-new judgment, exercised toward a new gate with justification.","Promote effect_atomicity/phase to closed typed schema columns so EFFECT-S-01 binds a schema-closed surface: NOT TAKEN -- the markers are already IEL-S-01-integrity-protected in the committed body, so EFFECT-S-01 binds them schema-stationary; a schema-typed effect surface is a separate, larger lane.","Treat an orphan PREPARE or orphan COMPENSATE as a trail violation: REJECTED -- an orphan is honest in-doubt residue, detector-reported, never corruption; EFFECT-S-01 flags only malformed terminals and class mismatches.","Describe D_cap enforcement as adding D_cap to conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1 / changing four-surface aggregation: CORRECTED (Governor) -- the accepted D_cap enforcement pattern is a SIBLING refusal precondition OUTSIDE aggregation; it is higher-risk for introducing a new refusal cause and requiring a sufficiency policy, not for altering aggregate()."],consequences="Effect-trail integrity is now CONSTITUTIONAL (EFFECT-S-01): a recorded effect trail that is class-mismatched, carries a terminal with no anchoring intent record, or records a false success fails closed at verification. NOT CLAIMED: that every effect is atomic (the claim is class-relative trail integrity; external classes remain non-atomic); that any new refusal cause was added; that terminal-outcome semantics changed (post-admit effect abort stays ADMIT, TO-S-01 preserved); that compensation physically reverses anything (COMPENSATED is an offset, the forward COMMIT stays historically true); that schema or legend moved. FRAME: LAW MOVED 80d7b8f0 -> 7f28d368 via amendment record 16 (54ac06d5; ordinary; law-leg; legend + schema stationary); legend db3c177d + schema 0d05dc56 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 81 -> 82; ledger 15 -> 16; ADRs through AD-56 (54); gates 105 -> 106 (effect_trail_integrity_gate). r132 -> r133 is an AMENDMENT continuity link (amendment_link = True, moved_legs = [law]) -- the THIRD modern law-leg link, reusing the r130/r131 template. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: EFFECT-S-01 is CONSTITUTIONAL/CERTIFIED; the cross-class verifier and effect_trail_integrity_gate are CERTIFIED/GATED substrate. This release folds the queued kernel.py EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE docstring erratum as separately-declared claim/proof hygiene. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: D_cap enforcement (a sibling refusal precondition outside aggregation, plus a sufficiency policy), the committed/verification-grade saga surface (schema move), bounded terminal-write retry for the reversible terminals, the governed compensation-reconciliation op, the DEFER/CRISIS records, and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program. With EFFECT-S-01 landed, the effect-atomicity spine wiring to commitment to law is closed for trail integrity across all five classes.",bound_invariants=["EFFECT-S-01"])
ADR_57=_adr(id="AD-57",context="r133 (AD-56, effect-trail integrity EFFECT-S-01 -- the THIRD modern law move) was accepted as canonical. The post-r133 5+7 hygiene/tooling lane (a runnable deterministic mint tool plus two claim/proof-hygiene edits) was accepted and HELD (no dedicated release), riding the next substantive release. The schema-typed effect surface design pass was then accepted: the Governor REJECTED the 'proceed only if a concrete consumer' condition (the governance substrate itself -- verifier hardness, schema closure, future law clarity, reduction of convention-over-JSON softness -- is the consumer), ratified that this is a typed-surface HARDENING lane (not a correctness rescue) whose mechanism is already proven by terminal_outcome v2 and D_cap v3, and authorized the schema-leg implementation lane first, with the law-leg binding of the typed surface deferred to a separate later lane.",decision="r134 commits the TYPED EFFECT SURFACE as UGK-BODY-v4, a schema-closed, domain-validated, body-committed MIRROR of the parameters effect markers, carried by a law-stationary, legend-stationary schema-leg amendment. (1) VERSION LADDER EXTENDED: version is the body-schema key and is monotonic -- v1->UGK-BODY-v1, v2->v2 (terminal_outcome, AD-51), v3->v3 (D_cap, AD-52), v4->UGK-BODY-v4 a superset of v3; v1/v2/v3 bodies are byte-identical and NOT reinterpreted. (2) NINE NULLABLE TYPED COLUMNS (body-committed inside h_body, v4): effect_atomicity, effect_atomicity_model_id, effect_phase, effect_prepare_ref, effect_compensate_ref, effect_idempotency_key, effect_compensation_idempotency_key, effect_abort_reason, effect_gate_admit_ref. (3) DERIVE-FROM-MARKERS SINGLE SOURCE: the typed columns are derived at the store.write() boundary FROM the existing parameters effect markers (the kernel emission is UNCHANGED -- it keeps stamping the markers), so the typed column EQUALS its marker BY CONSTRUCTION at write; an effect-bearing receipt (parameters carries effect_atomicity) is auto-detected and written at version>=4. The JSON markers remain the COMPATIBILITY MIRROR during the transition. (4) DOMAIN CLOSURE, FAIL CLOSED AT WRITE: effect_atomicity is typed over the closed five-set {pure, store_local, external_reversible, external_irreversible, non_atomic}; effect_phase over the closed six-set {prepare, commit, abort, compensate, compensated, compensation_failed} or None; an out-of-domain value raises EffectDomainError with ZERO mutation; effect_atomicity_model_id is the closed-domain anchor effect_atomicity_model_v1. (5) CONSISTENCY + DIVERGENCE FAILS CLOSED: verify_effect_column_marker_consistency proves, at verification, that every typed column equals its parameters marker and the model id is the declared anchor; a column/marker divergence or a wrong model id is a corrupt receipt (fail closed); because h_body commits BOTH the parameters and the typed columns, a tampered typed column ALSO breaks full-body verification (IEL-S-01). (6) ORTHOGONAL TO terminal_outcome AND D_cap: a v4 effect receipt is not a terminal-outcome-committing or capability receipt, so it commits terminal_outcome=None (out of TO-S-01 scope -- the 'no committed projection' principle, the same out-of-scope status v1 has) and carries no trace_vector_hash; terminal-outcome semantics, the kernel decision path, conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1 / aggregate(), FGA-TRACE-v1, and D_cap (non-aggregating) are ALL UNCHANGED. (7) EFFECT-S-01 STILL BINDS THE MARKERS: this is a schema-leg ONLY; EFFECT-S-01 (law) continues to bind the parameters markers schema-stationary; the typed columns are a COMMITTED-BUT-NOT-YET-LAW-BOUND surface (the proven commit-first / law-later pattern of terminal_outcome before TO-S-01 and D_cap before any enforcement). (8) SCHEMA MOVE VIA AMENDMENT: nine added nullable columns move schema_hash 0d05dc56 -> cbe140bf, carried by an admitted law-stationary, legend-stationary schema-leg AmendmentRecord 17 (ordinary, amendment_hash a793076e, moved-leg = schema, prior_schema 0d05dc56 -> successor_schema cbe140bf, prior_amendment = record 16 54ac06d5); ledger 16 -> 17; law 7f28d368 + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 82 UNMOVED; NO new invariant. (9) NEW CONFORMANCE GATE typed_effect_surface_gate (registered in run_gates_batch; gates 106 -> 107) proves v1/v2/v3 verify unchanged and carry no effect columns; v4 effect receipts body-commit the typed columns with the model anchor; effect_atomicity and effect_phase domain closure fail closed at write; column/marker divergence and wrong model id fail closed at verification; a tampered typed column breaks h_body; EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE and EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE v4 trails verify; and terminal_outcome is None with no trace_vector_hash on a plain effect receipt. (10) HELD 5+7 SET FOLDED, DECLARED SEPARATELY (not the release semantic payload): tools/release/mint_release.sh (new runnable deterministic mint tool), make_release.sh (retired stub now pointing to it), and construction/cgproj/phase6_full_validation_gate.py (a stale law-hash description corrected) ride r134 as tooling / claim-proof hygiene with separate change-confinement accounting. FRAME: SCHEMA MOVED 0d05dc56 -> cbe140bf (via the amendment); law 7f28d368 + legend db3c177d + registry 82 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; ledger 16 -> 17; CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added AND the conformance surface gains a gate (sci_typing UNCHANGED -- no invariant added). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law move; NO legend move; NO new invariant; NO terminal-outcome semantic change; NO D_cap aggregation/enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS record; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=["Make the typed columns authoritative and bind EFFECT-S-01 (or a new EFFECT-S-02) to them in this lane: NOT TAKEN -- that is the LAW LEG, deferred to a separate later lane; this lane is schema-only, so the markers remain authoritative under EFFECT-S-01 and the typed columns are a committed mirror. The law-leg readiness assessment rides the r134 report.","Thread the typed columns from each kernel emission site instead of deriving them at the store boundary: NOT TAKEN -- deriving from the markers at store.write() is a SINGLE SOURCE (consistency by construction at write), is minimal-surgical (kernel emission unchanged), and the verify-side cross-check supplies the divergence-fails-closed guarantee; threading from N emission sites would duplicate the marker production and invite drift.","Make UGK-BODY-v4 NOT include the v2/v3 body fields (a non-monotonic version): REJECTED -- the version ladder is monotonic by architecture (v3 is a superset of v2); v4 includes the v2/v3 projections (committed as None on a plain effect receipt, truthfully 'no terminal-outcome / no capability evidence'), which recompute identically and keep the ladder coherent.","Treat the schema move as a recordless frame-stationary change: REJECTED (the AD-51/AD-28 rule) -- adding committed columns moves schema_hash and MUST be carried by an admitted schema-leg amendment; skipping it is silent semantics and fails continuity.","Move law to make the schema leg coherent: NOT TAKEN -- a committed-but-unbound typed surface is coherent without a law move (the proven terminal_outcome-before-TO-S-01 and D_cap-before-enforcement pattern); the law-leg binding is a separate, separately-authorized lane."],consequences="UGK now BODY-COMMITS a schema-closed, domain-validated TYPED EFFECT SURFACE (UGK-BODY-v4) that mirrors the parameters effect markers: the effect surface is now schema-typed, domain-closed, and column-queryable, closing the convention-over-JSON softness EFFECT-S-01 rested on, WITHOUT making the typed columns law-authoritative yet. NOT CLAIMED: that the typed columns are law-authoritative (EFFECT-S-01 still binds the markers; the columns are a committed mirror); that any new refusal cause was added; that terminal_outcome semantics changed (a v4 effect receipt commits terminal_outcome=None, out of TO-S-01 scope, and carries no trace_vector_hash); that D_cap aggregates or is enforced; that v1/v2/v3 receipts are reinterpreted (they verify byte-unchanged and carry no effect columns); that law or legend moved. FRAME: SCHEMA MOVED 0d05dc56 -> cbe140bf via amendment record 17 (a793076e; ordinary; schema-leg; law + legend stationary); law 7f28d368 + legend db3c177d + registry 82 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; ledger 16 -> 17; ADRs through AD-57 (55); gates 106 -> 107 (typed_effect_surface_gate). r133 -> r134 is an AMENDMENT continuity link (amendment_link = True, moved_legs = [schema]) -- reusing the r128/r129 schema-leg template. This release folds the held 5+7 mint-tool / claim-proof-hygiene set, declared SEPARATELY in change-confinement. LAW-LEG READINESS (rides the report, NOT enacted here): the typed surface is now committed and gated, so a later law leg can bind it authoritative either by AMENDING EFFECT-S-01 to bind the typed columns (registry-stationary, the AD-29 statement-amendment precedent) or by ADDING EFFECT-S-02 (registry 82 -> 83) as a typed-surface conformance invariant leaving EFFECT-S-01 as the marker layer; the dual-surface consistency obligation (gated here) is the bridge until that law leg lands, so the schema leg does NOT create an indefinite ambiguous dual-surface state. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the v4 typed effect surface, the derive-from-markers single source, the domain closure, and typed_effect_surface_gate are CERTIFIED/GATED conformance substrate; the law-leg binding of the typed surface, D_cap enforcement, the DEFER/CRISIS records, and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program remain DEFERRED, each separately authorized. With the typed effect surface committed, the effect-atomicity spine is schema-closed for the markers EFFECT-S-01 binds.",bound_invariants=["IEL-S-01","EFFECT-S-01"])

ADR_58=_adr(id='AD-58',context='r134 (AD-57, the typed effect surface UGK-BODY-v4 schema-leg) was accepted as canonical. A governed Coder lane then refactored the GRBSA G6 release-certification verifier from a self-spawning aggregate orchestrator into a checkpoint-aware RECEIPT-BUNDLE verifier, and carried a proven pre-existing certification-tooling erratum. This is a BEHAVIORAL/TOOLING release: it changes only the certification substrate (tools/release/, tools/grbsa/, verify_deep.sh) and adds this descriptive ADR; it moves NO constitutional frame leg (law/schema/legend/invariant).',decision="r135 RESTRUCTURES the release-certification tooling and is recorded as a BEHAVIORAL/TOOLING release. (1) ORCHESTRATOR/CONSUMER SPLIT: tools/release/certify_release.py is the canonical release-cert ORCHESTRATOR -- it owns gate execution, founds EPHEMERALLY in a temporary genesis dir (never the extract, never the repo), runs the live-bound conformance suite (expectations derived from ugk.conformance.run_gates_batch.GATES, not a second hardcoded universe), the 9 GRBSA leaf gates, the 5 MigrationReceipts, registry identity, hygiene/no-drift, and the incremental continuity frontier, then emits a sealed release-cert BUNDLE; a new --phase bundle drives this. (2) G6 IS A BUNDLE VERIFIER: tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py in bounded mode is a PURE bundle CONSUMER plus a read-only genesis-contamination scan -- it does NOT spawn or found the GRBSA/conformance gate forest, does NOT found posture, and creates NO genesis contamination; given neither --bundle nor --full-audit it fails closed (refusal). (3) FULL-AUDIT NON-BLOCKING: the full genesis->head continuity compose is retained ONLY behind an explicit --full-audit and is non-blocking (archival; may RESOURCE_TIMEOUT), never on the bounded certification path. (4) INCREMENTAL FRONTIER: continuity is verified incrementally over a rolling attestation checkpoint, recomputing ONLY the unattested frontier; an unrecomputable frontier is UNFINISHED (never a false PASS) and a behaviourally recomputed clean link is HOLD. New tooling modules tools/grbsa/g6_proof_cache.py (per-link fail-closed cache + frontier verifier), tools/grbsa/g6_bundle.py (sealed bundle schema + pure consumer), and tools/grbsa/g6_incremental_gate.py (focused self-test) support this; tools/grbsa/proof_model_b.py gains a PROOF_MODEL_VERSION, a 4-tuple evaluate_link return, and a --full-audit alias. Legacy callers (verify_deep.sh, tools/grbsa/verifier_gate.py) are rebound off the removed orchestrator onto the 9 GRBSA leaf gates directly. tools/release/mint_release.sh excludes the regenerable g6_proof_cache.json. (5) CARRIED ERRATUM (separately declared in change-confinement, NOT the primary payload): tools/release/certify_release.py check_attestation previously compared composed == 'HOLD' EXACTLY, which FALSE-FAILED the descriptive attestation string '...composed=HOLD' (proven pre-existing against pristine r134). It now DELEGATES to proof_model_b._verify_attestation (every attested link HOLD; contiguous sha chain; current-link content chaining) with a structured composed=HOLD guard, and FAILS CLOSED on missing/malformed/ambiguous/non-HOLD/broken-continuity; semantics are STRENGTHENED, never weakened. FRAME: law 7f28d368 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 82 + genesis 5fe68bbc ALL UNMOVED; ledger 17 UNCHANGED; NO amendment record; gates 107 UNCHANGED (the G6 self-test is certification tooling, NOT a registered conformance gate); CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added (invariants/registry/legend unchanged). r134 -> r135 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law move; NO schema move; NO legend move; NO new invariant; NO governance-semantic change; NO typed-effect law; NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS record; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=('Keep G6 as a self-spawning aggregate orchestrator: NOT TAKEN -- a verifier that founds posture and spawns the gate forest conflates orchestration with verification, risks genesis contamination, and cannot bound the continuity compose; splitting orchestration (certify_release.py) from verification (G6 consumer) removes that conflation.', 'Recompute the full genesis->head continuity compose on the bounded certification path: NOT TAKEN -- it is unbounded (may time out) and redundant given a trusted rolling attestation checkpoint; the bounded path recomputes only the unattested frontier and full compose is retained behind non-blocking --full-audit.', 'Fold the check_attestation fix into the G6 payload: NOT TAKEN -- the fix is a pre-existing certification-tooling erratum independent of the G6 architecture; it is declared SEPARATELY in change-confinement (B4).', 'Treat the check_attestation fix as a frame/governance change: REJECTED -- it is certification-tooling parsing only; it moves no law/schema/legend/invariant and changes no kernel/runtime behavior.', 'Add a conformance gate for the G6 self-test (move gates 107 -> 108): NOT TAKEN -- the G6 self-test is certification tooling exercised directly (like the GRBSA leaf gates and cert_selftest_gate), not a kernel/conformance invariant; the conformance gate count stays 107.'),consequences="UGK release certification now SEPARATES orchestration from verification: certify_release.py orchestrates and emits a sealed receipt bundle; G6 verifies the finished bundle and spawns nothing in bounded mode; continuity is verified incrementally over a rolling attestation checkpoint (HOLD/UNFINISHED/FAIL), with full genesis->head compose retained as non-blocking --full-audit. NOT CLAIMED: that any law/schema/legend/invariant moved; that the ledger moved (it stays 17, NO amendment); that the conformance gate count changed (stays 107); that any kernel/runtime/governance semantic changed. The carried check_attestation erratum strengthens attestation verification (delegation + structured composed=HOLD guard + fail-closed) and is declared separately in change-confinement. FRAME-STATIONARY in the constitutional sense: law 7f28d368 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + registry 82 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; ledger 17; gates 107; ADRs through AD-58 (56); CODEX a67dba41 -> re-pinned because AD-58 is added. 'Frame-stationary' HERE MEANS law/schema/legend/invariant-registry stationary; the ADR count (55 -> 56) and the derived CODEX projection move as RELEASE-RECORD / DOCUMENTATION movement, NOT a constitutional frame-leg move. r134 -> r135 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []), reusing the r131->r132 (AD-55) behavioral-link template. PRIMARY PAYLOAD vs CARRIED ERRATUM are declared SEPARATELY in change-confinement (B4): the G6 receipt-bundle verifier architecture is the primary payload; the check_attestation parser fix is the carried erratum. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: certify_release.py --phase bundle, the G6 bundle consumer, g6_proof_cache.py, g6_bundle.py, and g6_incremental_gate.py are CERTIFIED release-certification tooling. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: the typed-effect law leg, D_cap enforcement, the DEFER/CRISIS records, and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program.",bound_invariants=('IEL-S-01', 'AUDIT-S-01'))

ADR_59=_adr(id='AD-59',context='r135 (AD-58, the G6 checkpoint-aware receipt-bundle verifier behavioral/tooling release) was accepted as canonical. A post-r135 roadmap-exhaustion checkpoint selected the lowest-risk live hardening lane: applying the proven AD-46 (r121) bounded TERMINAL-write retry pattern -- previously implemented for the EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE COMMIT/ABORT terminals -- to the EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE class (AD-55). The r132 EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE implementation wrote each terminal as a SINGLE store write, so a TRANSIENT store failure (a SQLite lock/busy, or the AD-36 clean-path TransactionCommitError) of a terminal write left NO terminal and an orphan PREPARE/COMPENSATE even though the outcome was already known. The Governor authorized this as a frame-stationary IR-hardening lane and explicitly bounded it: terminal-write retry ONLY; the surviving orphan residue after retry exhaustion is the future input to the separate, unopened governed compensation-reconciliation lane, NOT something this lane resolves.',decision="r136 adds a BOUNDED in-process retry of the EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE TERMINAL store write, mirroring r121/AD-46 EXACTLY for the reversible class. A private kernel helper _emit_reversible_terminal_durable wraps ONLY the terminal _emit_reversible call for the four reversible terminals -- the FORWARD trail terminals (phase in {commit, abort}, written AFTER the forward effect has returned / raised ExternalEffectNotPerformed) and the COMPENSATION-arc terminals (phase in {compensated, compensation_failed}, written AFTER the compensation action has returned / raised). (1) BOUNDARY (the spine): the external effect and the compensating action are NEVER re-invoked -- each lives entirely OUTSIDE the helper, BEFORE the call site; the retry re-attempts only a durable RECORD of an outcome that is already known. The PREPARE and COMPENSATE INTENT writes are NOT terminals and remain direct, single, receipt-before-effect writes (not retried). (2) BOUNDED: at most MAX_OUTCOME_WRITE_ATTEMPTS (=3); NO sleep / NO backoff (immediate, synchronous). (3) NARROW RETRYABLE SET: reuses _is_retryable_terminal_write_error -- only sqlite3.OperationalError with lock/busy semantics and TransactionCommitError (AD-36); ANY other exception fails closed IMMEDIATELY (re-raise on the first attempt), so a logic/programming fault is never masked. (4) FAIL-CLOSED ON EXHAUSTION: after MAX retryable failures NO terminal persists and TerminalWriteExhausted (carrying phase, the in-doubt ref, attempts) is raised, chaining the last transient error -> the orphan PREPARE / orphan COMPENSATE STANDS as honest in-doubt residue, still reported by detect_orphan_prepares / detect_orphan_compensates and never auto-resolved. (5) OPTION A -- NOTHING enters the chain: a terminal written on attempt k is byte-identical in PARAMETERS to one written on attempt 1 (only the inherent, already-varying write timestamp differs); no attempt count and no retry marker enter any receipt, so chain-hash determinism is untouched. (6) SEMANTICS UNCHANGED: the retry changes only the DURABILITY of a terminal RECORD whose meaning is unchanged -- it does NOT infer an outcome, does NOT convert an execution failure into REFUSE (TO-S-01 effect-abort separation preserved: a forward ABORT and a COMPENSATION_FAILED stay failed=True execution status, never a gate_refuse; the ADMIT decision is untouched), and does NOT alter the trail's class-relative conformance (EFFECT-S-01 intact); a COMPENSATED still records an OFFSET and the forward COMMIT stays historically true. The certified EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE helper (_emit_terminal_durable) is UNTOUCHED; the reversible helper is an ADDITIVE sibling. external_reversible_gate is EXTENDED IN PLACE (no new gate; gates stay 107) to prove transient->clean-terminal, exhaustion->orphan-stands + TerminalWriteExhausted, effect/action-runs-exactly-once, ambiguous-failure-does-not-enter-retry, confirmed-non-performance->clean-ABORT-never-REFUSE, orphan-detectors-still-report, TO-S-01 and EFFECT-S-01 intact, Option A, and forward-COMMIT-preserved-after-compensation. FRAME: law 7f28d368 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 82 + genesis 5fe68bbc ALL UNMOVED; ledger 17 UNCHANGED; NO amendment record; gates 107 UNCHANGED; CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added (invariants/registry/legend unchanged). r135 -> r136 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law move; NO schema move; NO legend move; NO new invariant; NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS record; NO typed-effect law leg; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM; the governed compensation-reconciliation lane (#4) is NOT opened.",alternatives=('Generalize the certified _emit_terminal_durable (irreversible) to also serve the reversible class: NOT TAKEN -- that re-wires a certified helper and broadens the change; an ADDITIVE sibling _emit_reversible_terminal_durable is minimal-surgical and leaves the irreversible path untouched.', 'Retry the external effect or the compensating action on a transient terminal-write failure: REJECTED -- the act/offset already happened and is not idempotent here; only the durable RECORD of the already-known outcome is re-attempted. The effect/action lives outside the helper and is proven to run exactly once across retries.', 'Also retry the PREPARE / COMPENSATE intent writes: NOT TAKEN -- they are not terminals; a failed intent write fails closed before any effect runs (receipt-before-effect), with nothing to make durable. Bounded retry is for terminals only.', 'Resolve or annotate the surviving orphan after retry exhaustion: REJECTED (Governor scope bound) -- the orphan PREPARE/COMPENSATE that survives exhaustion is honest in-doubt residue and the future input to the separate governed compensation-reconciliation lane (#4); this lane never auto-resolves it.', 'Record the attempt count / a retry marker in the terminal receipt: REJECTED (Option A) -- it would inject retry nondeterminism into the chain; the terminal is byte-identical in parameters regardless of attempt.'),consequences="EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE terminal writes (forward COMMIT/ABORT and compensation COMPENSATED/COMPENSATION_FAILED) now survive a TRANSIENT store failure via a bounded, immediate, named-retryable-only in-process retry -- reducing honest-but-noisy record-loss orphans -- while a PERSISTENT failure still fails closed to an honest in-doubt orphan (TerminalWriteExhausted, no terminal). NOT CLAIMED: that the external effect or the compensating action is retried (it is not -- it runs exactly once, outside the helper); that any orphan is resolved or auto-annotated (the surviving orphan stands for the future reconciliation lane); that an execution failure becomes a REFUSE (TO-S-01 effect-abort separation preserved -- no gate_refuse); that the trail's class-relative integrity changed (EFFECT-S-01 intact); that compensation physically undoes the forward act (COMPENSATED stays an offset; the COMMIT stays historically true); that law, schema, legend, or the invariant registry moved. FRAME: law 7f28d368 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + registry 82 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; ledger 17 (NO amendment); ADRs through AD-59 (57); gates 107 (external_reversible_gate extended in place, NO new gate); CODEX projection moves (71791f7a -> re-pinned) because AD-59 is added. 'Frame-stationary' means law/schema/legend/invariant-registry stationary; the ADR count (56 -> 57) and the derived CODEX projection move as release-record / documentation movement, NOT a constitutional frame-leg move. r135 -> r136 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []), reusing the r131->r132 / r134->r135 behavioral-link template. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: _emit_reversible_terminal_durable and the extended external_reversible_gate are CERTIFIED/GATED runtime substrate. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: the governed compensation-reconciliation op (#4 -- the consumer of the surviving residue), the committed/verification-grade saga surface, the typed-effect law leg, D_cap enforcement, the DEFER/CRISIS records, and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program. With this lane, all five EffectAtomicity classes' terminal writes (irreversible via AD-46, reversible via this lane) carry the same bounded-retry record-durability discipline.",bound_invariants=('GK-S-02', 'EH-S-02', 'PERSIST-S-01'))

ADR_60=_adr(id='AD-60',context="r136 (AD-59) completed the bounded terminal-write retry for the EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE class, so all five EffectAtomicity classes' terminal writes carry the same record-durability discipline. What r136 intentionally left is the honest in-doubt residue that survives retry EXHAUSTION -- an orphan forward PREPARE or an orphan COMPENSATE. The EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE class already had a COMPLETE in-doubt story: bounded retry (AD-46) PLUS governed out-of-band reconciliation (AD-47, reconcile_external_irreversible). The reversible class had only the retry half. The reversible orphan detectors (detect_orphan_prepares, detect_orphan_compensates) already existed as the readers; the missing piece was the lawful writer. A post-r136 checkpoint selected this lane as the natural completion of the reversible substrate, and the Governor authorized it design-first then implement.",decision="r137 adds GovernanceKernel.reconcile_external_reversible_forward(...) and reconcile_external_reversible_compensation(...) -- the EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE analogue of AD-47, one per in-doubt arc. Each RECORDS an outcome a governed operator determined by an EXTERNAL check; it runs NO effect and NO compensating action (proven: action-count 0), performs/re-performs/retries/infers NOTHING, and NEVER auto-resolves. Closure is by writing ONE provenance-marked terminal for the EXACT orphan key/ref, so the UNCHANGED reversible detector then sees it resolved (detector = reader, this = the lawful writer it always assumed; NO detector change). (1) FORWARD ARC (reconcile_external_reversible_forward, target an outstanding orphan PREPARE via detect_orphan_prepares): determination='performed' -> a reconciling COMMIT; 'not_performed' -> a reconciling ABORT with abort_reason='reconciled_not_performed' (DISTINCT from the in-band 'external_effect_not_performed'). (2) COMPENSATION ARC (reconcile_external_reversible_compensation, target an outstanding orphan COMPENSATE via detect_orphan_compensates): determination='performed' -> a reconciling COMPENSATED (the offset is DETERMINED to have run; an OFFSET, NOT an undo -- the forward COMMIT stays historically true; NO erasure marker is ever set, EFFECT-S-01's no-physical-erasure rule holds); 'not_performed' -> a reconciling COMPENSATION_FAILED with abort_reason='reconciled_compensation_not_performed' (DISTINCT from the in-band 'compensation_effect_failed'); the business state is unresolved (the forward effect stands, un-offset). Either compensation terminal CLEARS the orphan via the unchanged detector. (3) STRICT FAIL-CLOSED CONTRACT (reuses ReconciliationRefused, writing NOTHING, leaving the orphan untouched): authority required and recorded (reconciled_by); evidence_ref required and recorded (reconciliation_evidence_ref) -- RECORDED, NOT VERIFIED (confess-and-audit, as in AD-47); determination must be exactly 'performed' or 'not_performed' (anything else -- None, 'cannot determine', any unsupported value -- is a first-class REFUSAL; the orphan stays in_doubt); the target ref must be an OUTSTANDING orphan at write time, so unknown / wrong-arc / already-terminal'd refs all refuse, guaranteeing AT MOST ONE terminal per orphan. (4) PROVENANCE (no laundering): every reconciled terminal carries reconciled=true + reconciled_by + reconciliation_evidence_ref + determination + arc, so it is NEVER mistaken for an in-band terminal. (5) REUSE: the terminal write reuses the AD-59 reversible durable path (_emit_reversible_terminal_durable -- bounded retry of the STORE WRITE only); on exhaustion NO terminal persists and the orphan STANDS. All markers are parameters-JSON (reconciled/reconciled_by/reconciliation_evidence_ref/determination/arc + the existing prepare_ref/compensate_ref/compensation_idempotency_key/abort_reason), so NO schema column is added. external_reversible_gate is EXTENDED IN PLACE (no new gate; gates stay 107). FRAME: law 7f28d368 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 82 + genesis 5fe68bbc ALL UNMOVED; ledger 17 UNCHANGED; NO amendment record; CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added. r136 -> r137 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law move; NO schema move (no committed/typed saga field); NO legend move; NO new invariant; NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS record; NO typed-effect law leg; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM; #4 stays separate from the schema-typed saga surface.",alternatives=('Generalize reconcile_external_irreversible (AD-47) to also serve the reversible class: NOT TAKEN -- the target surfaces and terminal phases differ per arc (prepare_ref -> commit/abort vs compensate_ref -> compensated/compensation_failed); two additive named ops are minimal-surgical and leave AD-47 untouched.', 'A single reconcile_external_reversible op dispatching on arc: NOT TAKEN -- the compensation arc keys on (compensate_ref, compensation_idempotency_key) while the forward arc keys on prepare_ref; two explicit ops keep the authority/evidence audit trail per-arc legible.', 'Run a verifying/offsetting action to confirm the determination: REJECTED -- reconciliation is confess-and-audit; it records an externally-determined outcome and runs NO effect and NO compensating action; evidence_ref is recorded, not verified, unless a later evidence-admission mechanism exists.', "Infer the outcome from the orphan's age / absence of a terminal: REJECTED -- no inference from absence; an inconclusive determination REFUSES and the orphan stays in_doubt.", "Reuse the in-band abort_reasons ('external_effect_not_performed' / 'compensation_effect_failed') for reconciled terminals: REJECTED -- distinct reconciled reasons ('reconciled_not_performed' / 'reconciled_compensation_not_performed') plus reconciled=true prevent any conflation (no laundering).", 'Let a reconciling COMPENSATED imply the forward effect was undone: REJECTED -- COMPENSATED is an OFFSET, never an erasure; the forward COMMIT stays historically true and no erasure marker is set.'),consequences="The EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE class now has a COMPLETE in-doubt story at PARITY with EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE: bounded retry (AD-59) for transient record loss, PLUS governed reconciliation (this ADR) for the honest residue that survives exhaustion -- the reversible mirror of AD-46 + AD-47. NOT CLAIMED: that any external effect or compensating action is run or re-run (action-count 0); that any outcome is inferred or any orphan auto-resolved (a determination is explicit, required, closed-domain; inconclusive REFUSES); that evidence_ref is verified (it is recorded, confess-and-audit); that a reconciling ABORT/COMPENSATED claims the forward act was undone (no physical-undo; COMMIT stays historically true); that an execution failure becomes a REFUSE (TO-S-01 preserved: reconciling ABORT/COMPENSATION_FAILED are failed=True execution status, never a gate_refuse); that the trail's class-relative integrity changed (EFFECT-S-01 stays clean with reconciled terminals present); that law, schema, legend, or the invariant registry moved. FRAME: law 7f28d368 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + registry 82 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; ledger 17 (NO amendment); ADRs through AD-60 (58); gates 107 (external_reversible_gate extended in place); CODEX projection moves (67172747 -> re-pinned) because AD-60 is added. 'Frame-stationary' means law/schema/legend/invariant-registry stationary; the ADR count (57 -> 58) and the derived CODEX projection move as release-record/documentation movement. r136 -> r137 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the two reconcile_external_reversible_* methods and the extended external_reversible_gate are CERTIFIED/GATED runtime substrate. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: the committed/verification-grade saga surface (schema), the typed-effect law leg, D_cap enforcement, the DEFER/CRISIS records, and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program. A future evidence-admission/warrant mechanism could raise reconciliation from recorded-not-verified to verified-grade -- explicitly out of this lane's scope.",bound_invariants=('GK-S-02', 'EH-S-02', 'PERSIST-S-01'))

ADR_61=_adr(id='AD-61',context='r134 (AD-57) added the v4 typed effect surface: nine body-committed effect_* columns derived at write from the parameter markers, domain-validated (closed 5-set atomicity / 6-set phase), with a marker<->column consistency verifier gated by typed_effect_surface_gate. AD-57 was explicitly SCHEMA-LEG ONLY -- it moved schema (to cbe140bf) but left EFFECT-S-01 binding the parameter markers; the typed columns were committed and gated but were NOT the authoritative trail-integrity surface. EFFECT-S-01 (AD-56) therefore still recomputes effect-trail integrity from the markers, while the stronger body-committed typed columns sit beside it unused by the law. A post-r137 roadmap checkpoint identified this as the live effect frontier -- law authority over the already-committed typed surface, not building a new surface -- and the Governor authorized a design pass then this implementation. The chosen shape (Option B) ADDS EFFECT-S-02 rather than mutating EFFECT-S-01 in place, so the historical marker-based invariant keeps its meaning and the new column-based authority is explicit.',decision="r138 adds EFFECT-S-02 (typed-column effect-trail integrity) as the AUTHORITATIVE trail-integrity surface for v>=4 receipts, binding the body-committed v4 typed columns (effect_atomicity, effect_phase, effect_prepare_ref, effect_compensate_ref, effect_idempotency_key, effect_compensation_idempotency_key, effect_abort_reason, effect_gate_admit_ref, under effect_atomicity_model_v1). EFFECT-S-02 recomputes the SAME class-relative discipline as EFFECT-S-01 -- class-relativity, terminal->intent anchoring (forward terminals to the typed PREPARE columns, compensation terminals to the typed COMPENSATE columns), no false success, orphans as honest in-doubt residue, COMPENSATED as offset not erasure, COMPENSATION_FAILED as unresolved execution not REFUSE -- but sourced from the columns instead of the markers. (1) OPTION B (add, not amend): EFFECT-S-01 is UNCHANGED and remains the marker-layer invariant; EFFECT-S-02 is the new column-authoritative invariant. (2) NON-RETROACTIVE: EFFECT-S-02 governs only v>=4 receipts (which carry the typed surface); v<4 receipts carry no columns and stay under EFFECT-S-01 marker semantics -- pre-v4 receipts are never reinterpreted. (3) CONSISTENCY BRIDGE: for v>=4, the typed columns and the parameter markers MUST agree (the r134 verify_effect_column_marker_consistency, gated by typed_effect_surface_gate); a divergence is a corrupt receipt that fails closed. EFFECT-S-02's soundness rests on IEL-S-01 (h_body covers the columns) PLUS that gated bridge. (4) RESIDUAL no-erasure guard: the no-physical-erasure prohibition (a COMPENSATED must not assert undone/reversed/erased/rolled_back) has NO typed column; it is retained as a BOUNDED parameter-hygiene residual read. NO claim of pure column closure is made while that residual remains. (5) effect_trail_integrity_gate is EXTENDED IN PLACE (no new gate; gates stay 107) to prove: column recompute equals marker recompute on conformant v>=4 trails; the typed recompute flags the same structural corruption; the bridge fails closed on divergence; the residual erasure guard remains effective; and v<4 non-retroactivity. FRAME: this is a LAW-LEG AMENDMENT -- law_hash moves (invariants.py gains EFFECT-S-02: 7f28d368 -> 82c565f1), invariant registry 82 -> 83, amendment ledger gains record 18 (ordinary, invariants_added=[EFFECT-S-02], fixture-Governor signed, prior_amendment a793076e). SCHEMA cbe140bf STATIONARY (columns already exist from r134); LEGEND db3c177d STATIONARY (sci_typing is classification metadata, not law, and the legend artifact is unchanged); genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED. r137 -> r138 is an AMENDMENT-class continuity link (amendment_link = True, moved_legs = the law leg). SCOPE-BOUNDED: EFFECT-S-02 ADDS NO NEW REFUSAL CAUSE and does not mutate terminal-outcome semantics (TO-S-01: a post-admit effect abort remains ADMIT, never REFUSE); NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM; NO evidence-admission surface; the markers-as-source-of-truth flip (callsites writing columns directly) is a separate later lane, NOT opened here.",alternatives=('Amend EFFECT-S-01 in place to read the columns (Option A): NOT TAKEN -- it would silently change the meaning of the r133/AD-56 marker-based invariant; Option B keeps the old law visible and makes the new column authority explicit, per the no-silent-semantics discipline.', 'Make the typed columns the SOURCE of truth (kernel/callsites write columns directly; markers derived or dropped): NOT TAKEN -- that is an implementation-heavy write-path change; this lane moves only the VERIFICATION binding, with markers remaining the source and the consistency bridge guaranteeing agreement.', "Add a typed erasure column so the no-erasure check is column-based too: NOT TAKEN -- that is a schema move, out of this law-leg's scope; the v4 phase domain has no erasure representation, so the prohibition is retained as a bounded parameter-hygiene residual instead.", 'Promote verify_effect_column_marker_consistency to its own law invariant: NOT TAKEN this lane -- the bridge stays gated (typed_effect_surface_gate) under IEL-S-01; EFFECT-S-02 depends on it as a co-requirement. Elevation can be a separate amendment if later warranted.', 'Make EFFECT-S-02 retroactive to v<4 receipts: REJECTED -- v<4 receipts carry no typed columns; reinterpreting them would be dishonest. They remain under EFFECT-S-01.', 'Claim pure column closure (drop all marker reads): REJECTED -- the no-erasure residual has no column; claiming pure closure would overclaim. The residual marker read is retained and disclosed.'),consequences='The effect spine is now complete from committed surface to LAW AUTHORITY for v>=4 receipts: r134 committed the typed columns; r138 makes them the authoritative trail-integrity surface via EFFECT-S-02, with EFFECT-S-01 retained as the marker layer (authoritative for v<4, and the consistency-bridge counterpart for v>=4). NOT CLAIMED: that EFFECT-S-01 changed meaning (it did not -- Option B); that pure column closure was achieved (the no-erasure prohibition remains a bounded parameter-hygiene residual); that v<4 receipts were reinterpreted (EFFECT-S-02 is non-retroactive); that any new refusal cause was added or terminal-outcome semantics moved (TO-S-01 intact); that AD-55/59/60 compensation semantics changed (they are re-expressed over columns, not altered); that schema or legend moved. FRAME: law_hash 7f28d368 -> 82c565f1 (EFFECT-S-02 added); registry 82 -> 83; ledger 17 -> 18 (ordinary amendment); schema cbe140bf, legend db3c177d, genesis 5fe68bbc all UNMOVED; gates 107 (effect_trail_integrity_gate extended in place); ADRs through AD-61 (59); CODEX re-pinned (AD-61 + EFFECT-S-02 added). This is an AMENDMENT-class release -- the first amendment after the r135-r137 behavioral run (r133 and r134 were prior law/schema amendments). r137 -> r138 continuity is amendment-class (amendment_link = True, moved_legs = law). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: EFFECT-S-02 and the extended gate are CERTIFIED/GATED law and verification substrate. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: D_cap sufficiency/enforcement (a new refusal cause, sibling precondition outside aggregation); the markers->columns source-of-truth flip; DEFER continuation record; CRISIS/multi-root; the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program; and the parked verification-grade evidence-admission surface.',bound_invariants=('EFFECT-S-02', 'EFFECT-S-01', 'IEL-S-01'))

ADR_62=_adr(id='AD-62',context='r138 (AD-61) made the v4 typed effect columns the AUTHORITATIVE trail-integrity surface for v>=4 receipts via EFFECT-S-02, but explicitly DEFERRED -- in its own scope bound -- the markers-as-source-of-truth flip (callsites writing columns directly): "a separate later lane, NOT opened here". Under AD-57/AD-61 the typed columns were still DERIVED FROM the parameter markers at the store.write() boundary (markers were the write-time source; columns the mirror). A post-r138 checkpoint opened that deferred lane as Lane 1 and the Governor authorized a design pass then a byte-identity-gated behavioral implementation, with a tightening: the typed columns become the PRIMARY write surface for v>=4 STRUCTURAL effect fields, while parameter markers REMAIN a derived mirror, the EFFECT-S-01 marker-layer surface, the residual no-erasure guard substrate, and the v<4 compatibility layer -- markers are NOT retired. Further tightening: the column descriptor is canonical, markers are derived from it (never independently trusted), and a caller-supplied marker that diverges from its typed column must FAIL CLOSED -- no silent precedence where a stale marker overrides the typed columns. The real go/no-go was a byte-identity proof, required EARLY, before any release-record work.',decision="r139 FLIPS the typed-effect source of truth at the WRITE PATH and is recorded as a BEHAVIORAL release with ZERO frame movement. (1) COLUMN-PRIMARY WRITE: the kernel effect-write helpers (the EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE and EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE emit helpers and the execute() admit effect-class tag) now pass a CANONICAL effect_columns descriptor to store.write(); a new store-side resolver _resolve_effect_surface derives the parameter markers FROM the typed columns via _derive_effect_markers (the inverse of the AD-57 _derive_effect_columns), the exact reverse of the r134 derive-from-markers single source. (2) BYTE-IDENTITY (the go/no-go gate, proven early): a v>=4 column-primary write is BYTE-IDENTICAL to the pre-flip marker-primary write -- full committed body, h_body, h_r, committed parameters, the nine typed columns, and version all identical; the r134 marker<->column bridge holds on both. This holds because compute_h_body commits BOTH the parameters markers AND the typed columns and canonicalizes via sorted-key _canonical_json, so deriving markers from columns (instead of columns from markers) leaves the committed bytes unchanged; the marker mirror is reproduced with the same truthy-conditional discipline the legacy callsites used. The flip is therefore FRAME-NEUTRAL: NO law, NO schema, NO legend, NO body-version, NO invariant move. (3) DIVERGENCE FAILS CLOSED / NO SILENT PRECEDENCE: when columns are supplied, any effect marker left in parameters is STRIPPED and re-derived from the columns (columns always win by construction); a caller marker that DIVERGES from its canonical column raises EffectDomainError (fail closed). A stale marker can never silently override the typed columns. (4) MARKERS NOT RETIRED: the parameter markers remain the committed derived mirror, the EFFECT-S-01 marker-layer surface (authoritative for v<4 and the v>=4 consistency-bridge counterpart), the residual no-erasure guard read, and the v<4 compatibility layer. (5) NON-RETROACTIVE: only v>=4 effect-bearing writes take the column-primary path; v<4 writes remain marker-only with no typed columns; pre-existing receipts are immutable and byte-identical under re-derivation, so nothing is reinterpreted. (6) LEGACY PATH RETAINED: store.write(effect_columns=None) preserves the exact pre-flip marker-primary derivation for non-effect / not-yet-flipped writers (back-compat). (7) VERIFICATION-SURFACE UPDATE (declared separately in change-confinement): external_irreversible_pilot_gate's outcome-write-failure fault-injection probe identified the COMMIT store.write() by reading parameters['phase']; since the canonical write-boundary value moved to effect_columns['effect_phase'] (the marker is now derived INSIDE store.write, downstream of the probe), the probe is updated to detect the COMMIT via the descriptor first with the legacy parameters-marker fallback retained. This is a probe following the new source-of-truth boundary, NOT a kernel behavior change and NOT a mask: the AD-46 outcome-write-failure -> orphan-PREPARE behavior is proven intact (failure propagates, exactly one durable PREPARE, no durable COMMIT, orphan detector flags exactly the in-doubt key). FRAME: law 82c565f1 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 83 + amendment ledger 18 + genesis 5fe68bbc ALL UNMOVED; NO amendment record; gates 107 UNCHANGED (the probe is updated in place; no gate added or removed); CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added (invariants/registry/legend unchanged). r138 -> r139 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law move; NO schema move; NO legend move; NO body-version move; NO new invariant; NO marker retirement; NO terminal-outcome semantic change (TO-S-01 intact); NO effect execution / retry / reconciliation / terminal-outcome behavior change (AD-46/47, AD-55/59/60 intact); NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS record; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=('Retire the parameter markers now that columns are primary: NOT TAKEN (Governor tightening) -- markers remain a derived mirror, the EFFECT-S-01 marker layer, the residual no-erasure guard substrate, and the v<4 compatibility layer; retirement would change the committed body (breaking byte-identity and EFFECT-S-01) and is a separate later lane if ever warranted.', 'Resolve a caller marker/column divergence by silently letting the columns win (overwrite without erroring): NOT TAKEN (Governor tightening) -- columns are stripped-and-re-derived so they always win by construction, AND a divergent caller marker FAILS CLOSED, surfacing the caller bug rather than masking it; there is no silent precedence rule.', 'Make the divergence guard reject ANY effect marker present in parameters alongside a descriptor: NOT TAKEN -- execute() inherits effect_atomicity through base_params into the emit helpers, so a strict presence-rejection would false-fail; the strip-and-re-derive resolver tolerates a MATCHING inherited marker (byte-identical) and fails closed only on a true divergence.', 'Convert every effect-bearing write (incl. the post-admit effect-abort and PURE/STORE_LOCAL class tags) to column-primary in this lane: NOT TAKEN -- the lane targets the v>=4 STRUCTURAL effect-trail writes (the emit helpers + the admit class tag); the legacy marker-primary path is retained and remains byte-identical, so partial coverage is coherent and minimal-surgical. Remaining class-tag-only writes can flip in a later lane.', 'Prove byte-identity only at the resolver core, not at a full store.write: NOT TAKEN -- byte-identity was proven at BOTH the resolver core (identical columns/parameters/h_body) and a full controlled store.write (identical h_body/h_r/version/parameters/columns, bridge holding), isolating session/timestamp nondeterminism from the flip.', 'Do a provisional validation mint to exercise hygiene/clean-room/G6 before the release record: NOT TAKEN (Governor) -- a throwaway archive without the r139 release record cannot honestly exercise the continuity/G6 frontier; the pre-release proof pack (byte-identity, divergence, regressions, bridge, v<4 non-retroactivity, residual guard, verify_release) gated entry to the release-record phase, and the archive-dependent proofs run once on the real artifact.'),consequences="The typed effect columns are now the PRIMARY write surface for v>=4 structural effect fields: the kernel writes columns and the store derives the parameter markers from them, the exact reverse of the AD-57 derive-from-markers single source, while the committed receipt remains BYTE-IDENTICAL to the pre-flip write (h_body/h_r/parameters/columns/version), so EFFECT-S-02 (column-authoritative) and EFFECT-S-01 (marker layer) both verify unchanged and the r134 bridge holds. NOT CLAIMED: that the parameter markers are retired (they remain a derived mirror, the EFFECT-S-01 surface, the residual no-erasure guard read, and the v<4 compatibility layer); that any frame leg moved (law/schema/legend/body-version/invariant all stationary; the flip is byte-identity-gated and frame-neutral); that v<4 receipts are reinterpreted (the column-primary path is v>=4-only and old receipts are byte-identical under re-derivation); that any kernel effect behavior changed (the conformance-probe update tracks the new write boundary; the AD-46 outcome-write-failure->orphan behavior is proven intact); that a caller marker can override a typed column (divergence fails closed; columns always win); that a new refusal cause or terminal-outcome change was introduced (TO-S-01, AD-46/47, AD-55/59/60 intact). FRAME: law 82c565f1 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + registry 83 + ledger 18 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; NO amendment record; ADRs through AD-62 (60); gates 107 (probe updated in place, none added). 'Frame-stationary' means law/schema/legend/invariant-registry stationary; the ADR count (59 -> 60) and the derived CODEX projection move as release-record / documentation movement, NOT a constitutional frame-leg move. r138 -> r139 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []), reusing the r131->r132 / r134->r135 / r135->r136 / r136->r137 behavioral-link template. CHANGE-CONFINEMENT (declared separately): primary payload = the typed-column source-of-truth write-path flip (ugk/storage/store.py resolver + ugk/kernel.py callsite conversions); verification payload = the external_irreversible_pilot_gate fault-injection probe update; release-record payload = AD-62, CODEX, RELEASE.txt, continuity/attestation. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the column-primary resolver, the kernel column-primary callsites, and the updated probe are CERTIFIED/GATED runtime + verification substrate. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: retirement of the parameter markers; flipping the remaining class-tag-only effect writes; D_cap sufficiency/enforcement; the DEFER/CRISIS records; the committed/verification-grade saga surface; and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program. With this lane the typed effect surface is authoritative for verification (AD-61) AND primary at the write path (this ADR) for v>=4 structural effect fields, with the parameter markers retained as a derived compatibility mirror.",bound_invariants=('EFFECT-S-01', 'EFFECT-S-02', 'IEL-S-01'))

ADR_63=_adr(id='AD-63',context="r139 (AD-62) flipped the typed-effect source of truth at the WRITE PATH for the v>=4 STRUCTURAL effect-trail writes (the EXTERNAL_IRREVERSIBLE + EXTERNAL_REVERSIBLE emit helpers and the execute() admit class tag): those callsites pass a canonical effect_columns descriptor and the store derives the parameter markers from the columns, byte-identically. AD-62 explicitly scoped the flip to the structural-trail writes and left two CLASS-TAG-ONLY effect writes on the legacy marker-primary path: the post-admit PURE/STORE_LOCAL STRUCTURAL ABORT (_emit_effect_abort, which stamps abort_reason/effect_atomicity/gate_admit_ref markers) and the in-band effect-CLASS tag on the PURE/STORE_LOCAL success receipt and the NON_ATOMIC / no-effect op receipt (execute() stamping _params['effect_atomicity']). A post-r139 roadmap checkpoint classified the six remaining frontiers and selected this -- the remaining class-tag-only write flip -- as the lowest-risk next behavioral lane and the structural completion of the r139 flip (and a prerequisite for any future marker retirement, which was NOT opened). The Governor authorized it design-first, byte-identity-gated, with the same r139 discipline: preserve TO-S-01 effect-abort semantics, preserve v<4 non-retroactivity, preserve the EFFECT-S-01/EFFECT-S-02/typed-surface bridge, keep it behavioral unless byte-identity fails.",decision="r140 COMPLETES the typed-effect source-of-truth flip by converting the two remaining class-tag-only effect writes to column-primary, and is recorded as a BEHAVIORAL release with ZERO frame movement. (1) STRUCTURAL ABORT (_emit_effect_abort): when the abort is effect-bearing it now passes a canonical effect_columns descriptor {effect_atomicity, effect_abort_reason, effect_gate_admit_ref} and the store derives the abort_reason / effect_atomicity / gate_admit_ref markers from it; when NOT effect-bearing (effect_atomicity is None) it keeps the legacy marker path (abort_reason plain, gate_admit_ref if truthy). The receipt stays failed=True with terminal outcome ADMIT -- TO-S-01 effect-abort separation is intact (a post-admit effect abort is NEVER a REFUSE). (2) CLASS TAG (execute()): instead of stamping _params['effect_atomicity'] the dispatch computes a canonical _effect_columns = {effect_atomicity} (when effect-bearing) and passes it as effect_columns on the PURE/STORE_LOCAL success-receipt write and on the NON_ATOMIC / no-effect op write; the store derives the marker mirror. The EXTERNAL_* helpers already build their own descriptor (AD-62), so _params no longer needs to carry the class tag for them -- the redundant inherited marker is removed and the resolver no longer strips it. (3) BYTE-IDENTITY (the go/no-go gate, proven early before any release-record work): a cross-baseline comparison (r139 head vs r140) over a PURE effect success, a PURE effect ABORT, and a NON_ATOMIC effect op -- under a controlled session and fixed write timestamp -- shows the committed receipts are BYTE-IDENTICAL (op, version=4, failed flag, h_body, committed parameters, all nine typed columns), so the flip is FRAME-NEUTRAL. (Independent-kernel session divergence -- different gate_admit h_r feeding gate_admit_ref / prior_h_r -- was isolated and excluded by fixing the session id; it is not the conversion.) (4) MARKERS NOT RETIRED: the parameter markers remain the committed derived mirror, the EFFECT-S-01 marker-layer surface, the residual no-erasure guard read, and the v<4 compatibility layer. (5) NON-RETROACTIVE: only v>=4 effect-bearing writes take the column-primary path; v<4 / non-effect writes are unaffected; the NON_ATOMIC effect FAILURE receipt (which carried no class tag before) is unchanged; pre-existing receipts are immutable and byte-identical under re-derivation. (6) NO VERIFICATION-SURFACE CHANGE THIS LANE: no conformance probe keys on these write boundaries (the r139 external_irreversible_pilot_gate probe is already descriptor-aware), so NO gate or probe is touched -- the ugk/ change is purely the two kernel callsite conversions plus the release record. FRAME: law 82c565f1 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 83 + amendment ledger 18 + amendment_pin 4bd87514 + genesis 5fe68bbc ALL UNMOVED; NO amendment record; gates 107 UNCHANGED (no probe touched); CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added. r139 -> r140 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law/schema/legend/invariant/body-version move; NO marker retirement; NO terminal-outcome semantic change (TO-S-01 intact); NO effect execution/retry/reconciliation behavior change (AD-46/47, AD-55/59/60 intact); NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS record; NO evidence-admission surface; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=('Leave the class-tag-only writes on the legacy marker path indefinitely: NOT TAKEN -- they are v>=4 effect-bearing writes; completing the flip makes the typed columns uniformly primary at the write path and is the structural prerequisite for any future marker retirement, while the legacy marker-primary store path remains available (effect_columns=None) for non-effect / not-yet-flipped writers.', 'Retire the parameter markers now that every effect write is column-primary: NOT TAKEN (out of scope; separate frontier) -- markers remain a derived mirror, the EFFECT-S-01 surface, the residual no-erasure guard read, and the v<4 compatibility layer; retirement would move body-version/schema/law and is a separate, separately-authorized lane.', 'Convert the structural abort unconditionally (drop the effect_atomicity-is-None legacy branch): NOT TAKEN -- a non-effect-bearing abort has no class to commit; preserving the legacy branch keeps the not-effect-bearing case byte-identical and avoids fabricating an effect surface.', 'Also stamp the NON_ATOMIC effect FAILURE receipt with the class tag while here: NOT TAKEN -- that receipt used the original parameters (no class tag) before; adding one would change committed content and break byte-identity / non-retroactivity. It is left unchanged.', 'Update a conformance probe to the new boundary as in r139: NOT NEEDED -- no probe keys on the abort or class-tag write boundary (the r139 pilot probe is already descriptor-aware), so this lane touches no verification surface.'),consequences="The typed-effect source-of-truth flip is now COMPLETE: every v>=4 effect-bearing write -- the structural PREPARE/COMMIT/ABORT and compensation trail (AD-62), the post-admit structural abort, and the PURE/STORE_LOCAL/NON_ATOMIC effect-class tag (this ADR) -- is COLUMN-PRIMARY, with the store deriving the parameter-marker mirror from the canonical typed columns. The committed receipts remain BYTE-IDENTICAL to the pre-flip writes (proven across PURE success, PURE abort, and NON_ATOMIC), so EFFECT-S-02 (column-authoritative) and EFFECT-S-01 (marker layer) both verify unchanged and the r134 bridge holds. NOT CLAIMED: that the parameter markers are retired (they remain a derived mirror, the EFFECT-S-01 surface, the residual no-erasure guard read, and the v<4 compatibility layer); that any frame leg moved (law/schema/legend/body-version/invariant all stationary; byte-identity-gated, frame-neutral); that v<4 / non-effect receipts are reinterpreted (the NON_ATOMIC failure receipt is unchanged; old receipts are byte-identical under re-derivation); that any kernel effect behavior changed (TO-S-01 effect-abort stays ADMIT; AD-46/47 and AD-55/59/60 intact); that any verification surface changed (no probe touched). FRAME: law 82c565f1 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + registry 83 + ledger 18 + amendment_pin 4bd87514 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; NO amendment record; ADRs through AD-63 (61); gates 107 (no probe touched). 'Frame-stationary' means law/schema/legend/invariant-registry stationary; the ADR count (60 -> 61) and the derived CODEX projection move as release-record / documentation movement, NOT a constitutional frame-leg move. r139 -> r140 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []), reusing the r138->r139 (AD-62) behavioral-link template. CHANGE-CONFINEMENT (declared separately): primary payload = the two class-tag-only effect-write conversions in ugk/kernel.py (_emit_effect_abort + the execute() PURE/STORE_LOCAL/NON_ATOMIC class tag); verification payload = NONE (no probe touched); release-record payload = AD-63, CODEX, RELEASE.txt, continuity/attestation. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the converted callsites are CERTIFIED/GATED runtime substrate. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: retirement of the parameter markers (now structurally reachable -- every effect write is column-primary); D_cap sufficiency/enforcement; DEFER/CRISIS (CRISIS blocked on multi-root); evidence-admission / verification-grade reconciliation; and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program. With this lane the typed effect surface is authoritative for verification (AD-61) AND uniformly primary at the write path (AD-62 + this ADR) for all v>=4 effect-bearing writes, with the parameter markers retained as a derived compatibility mirror.",bound_invariants=('EFFECT-S-01', 'EFFECT-S-02', 'IEL-S-01'))

ADR_64=_adr(id='AD-64',context="The three governed out-of-band reconciliation ops -- reconcile_external_irreversible (AD-47) and reconcile_external_reversible_forward / reconcile_external_reversible_compensation (AD-60) -- close an orphan PREPARE/COMPENSATE by RECORDING an operator-determined outcome with a required evidence_ref that is RECORDED, NOT VERIFIED (confess-and-audit). AD-47 section-10.3 explicitly DEFERRED a warrant requirement as 'a production policy call': each op already accepts a warrant_id (a committed receipt field) but treats it as a NOT-NULL sentinel ('warrant requirement deferred, §10.3'). A post-r140 roadmap re-triage selected Frontier 5 (evidence-admission / verification-grade reconciliation) as the lowest-frame-risk substantive next lane, and a design pass established that the existing warrant_id seam + the content-addressed DecisionWarrant / WarrantStore primitive (already wired into the kernel via set_warrant_store) permit a first verified-grade increment WITHOUT any new committed/typed evidence surface. The Governor authorized increment 1 as a single batched FRAME-STATIONARY behavioral lane, opt-in, with the explicit scope nuance that 'verified-grade' means WARRANT-BACKED admissible-basis verification (content-addressed integrity, resolvability, current-frame binding, non-empty basis), NOT independent proof of the external-world event.",decision="r141 adds OPT-IN WARRANT-BACKED VERIFIED-GRADE reconciliation across all three reconcile_* ops and is recorded as a BEHAVIORAL release with ZERO frame movement. (1) OPT-IN: each op gains verified=False (default). When verified=False the path is UNCHANGED -- recorded-grade confess-and-audit, byte-identical to r140 (PROVEN: a recorded reconciling terminal under a fixed session is byte-identical to the r140 baseline; it carries NO reconciliation_grade marker and the warrant_id sentinel stays ''). (2) VERIFIED MODE: when verified=True the kernel calls a shared _verify_reconciliation_warrant(warrant_id) that FAILS CLOSED (raises ReconciliationRefused, writing NOTHING, orphan untouched) unless the cited DecisionWarrant (a) is reachable -- a WarrantStore is wired (else 'verified-requires-warrant-store') and warrant_id is non-empty (else 'verified-requires-warrant-id'); (b) RESOLVES in the store (else 'warrant-not-found'); (c) is content-addressed-INTACT -- verify_hash() passes (else 'warrant-hash-invalid'); (d) binds the CURRENT FRAME -- warrant.law_hash == kernel law_hash and warrant.legend_hash == kernel legend_hash (else 'warrant-stale-frame'); (e) carries a NON-EMPTY constitutional basis (else 'warrant-basis-invalid'). On success the reconciling terminal is tagged reconciliation_grade='verified' (a kernel-set parameters-JSON marker) and commits the warrant_id. (3) WARRANT-BACKED, NOT TRUTH-VERIFIED (scope nuance, explicit): this verifies the ADMISSIBLE BASIS -- the warrant's hash, resolvability, frame binding, and non-empty basis -- it does NOT and cannot prove the external act occurred; the kernel still RECORDS, never witnesses. It upgrades the basis from free-string confession to admissible, hash-verifiable, frame-bound warrant material. (4) NO LAUNDERING (proven): the reconciliation markers are KERNEL-BUILT (the ops take no caller parameters dict), so a caller cannot inject reconciliation_grade; a recorded terminal NEVER carries the grade marker or a warrant_id, a verified terminal ALWAYS carries both -- the two grades are structurally distinguishable and cannot launder into each other. (5) NO NEW REFUSAL CAUSE ON THE EXISTING PATH: verified-grade is opt-in; the recorded path's refusal taxonomy (authority/evidence/determination/orphan) is unchanged. The verified-mode refusals are intrinsic to the opt-in mode. (6) VERIFICATION-SURFACE UPDATE (declared separately in change-confinement): the two reconciliation gates are EXTENDED IN PLACE -- external_irreversible_pilot_gate proves the verified COMMIT (grade + committed warrant_id, orphan cleared, no effect), the recorded-unchanged/no-laundering guard, and all five fail-closed conditions; external_reversible_gate proves the same for the forward and compensation arcs (verified terminal, recorded-unchanged, stale-frame and empty-basis fail-closed with the orphan intact). NO gate is added or removed. FRAME: law 82c565f1 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + invariant registry 83 + amendment ledger 18 + amendment_pin 4bd87514 + genesis 5fe68bbc ALL UNMOVED; NO amendment record; gates 107 UNCHANGED (both reconciliation gates extended in place); CODEX moves because THIS ADR is added. r140 -> r141 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law/schema/legend/body-version/invariant move; NO committed/typed evidence surface (the warrant_id + the grade marker are existing/parameters-JSON, NOT a schema column); NO law formalization of the verified requirement (DEFERRED -- wiring precedes formalization); NO CGP evidence-artifact binding; NO mandated verified-grade (opt-in only); NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS; NO marker retirement; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=('Jump straight to a committed/typed evidence surface (a schema column for verified evidence): NOT TAKEN -- the warrant_id seam is already committed and the DecisionWarrant is content-addressed + hash-verifiable, so verified-grade is achievable as a read-side check with NO schema/body-version move. A typed evidence surface is a strictly later, heavier increment.', 'Formalize a law invariant now (that a verified-grade reconciliation MUST cite a hash-verified warrant): DEFERRED -- wiring precedes formalization (the established pattern: D_cap committed before enforcement, terminal_outcome before TO-S-01, typed columns before EFFECT-S-02). The mechanism is proven first; the law leg is a separate, separately-authorized amendment.', 'Mandate verified-grade as the only reconciliation path: NOT TAKEN -- that introduces a NEW REFUSAL CAUSE on the existing path. Increment 1 is opt-in and additive; mandating is a later policy/law leg.', 'Mark BOTH grades (reconciliation_grade=\"recorded\" on the recorded path too): NOT TAKEN -- that would change the recorded terminal body, breaking byte-identity with r140. Only verified terminals are marked; recorded terminals are unchanged and the absence of the marker is itself the (kernel-controlled, un-injectable) recorded signal.', 'Bind reconciliation to a CGP EvidenceArtifact / sealed CapabilityEvidenceLedger (AD-48) for verdict-grade evidence: NOT TAKEN (heavier, later) -- warrant-backed admissible-basis verification is the minimal first increment; CGP-evidence binding is a separate increment if warrant-grade proves insufficient.', 'Verify the external-world event itself: IMPOSSIBLE / NOT CLAIMED -- the kernel records a governed determination on an external check; it never witnesses the act. Verified-grade verifies the BASIS, not the event.'),consequences="Reconciliation evidence can now be raised, per call and opt-in, from recorded-confession to WARRANT-BACKED verified-grade: a verified reconciling terminal cites a content-addressed, hash-intact, current-frame-bound DecisionWarrant with a non-empty constitutional basis, and is tagged reconciliation_grade='verified' with the warrant_id committed; any failure of that basis fails closed and leaves the orphan in_doubt. NOT CLAIMED: that the external event is independently proven (verified-grade verifies the admissible BASIS, not the act -- the kernel still records, never witnesses); that the recorded path changed (it is byte-identical to r140 -- no grade marker, sentinel warrant_id); that a new refusal cause exists on the recorded path (verified-grade is opt-in); that verified and recorded can launder (markers are kernel-built; the grades are structurally distinguishable); that any frame leg moved (law/schema/legend/body-version/invariant all stationary; frame-stationary behavioral); that the verified requirement is formalized as law (deferred) or mandated (opt-in only); that a committed/typed evidence surface was added (none). FRAME: law 82c565f1 + schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + registry 83 + ledger 18 + amendment_pin 4bd87514 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; NO amendment record; ADRs through AD-64 (62); gates 107 (both reconciliation gates extended in place). 'Frame-stationary' means law/schema/legend/invariant-registry stationary; the ADR count (61 -> 62) and the derived CODEX projection move as release-record / documentation movement, NOT a constitutional frame-leg move. r140 -> r141 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link = False, moved_legs = []). CHANGE-CONFINEMENT (declared separately): primary payload = the verified-grade reconciliation path (ugk/kernel.py: the _verify_reconciliation_warrant helper + the opt-in verified branch and grade marker in all three reconcile_* ops); verification payload = the two reconciliation gates extended in place (external_irreversible_pilot_gate + external_reversible_gate); release-record payload = AD-64, CODEX, RELEASE.txt, continuity/attestation. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the verified-grade path and the gate extensions are CERTIFIED/GATED runtime + verification substrate; the recorded path is unchanged production. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: law formalization of the verified-grade requirement; mandating verified-grade (a new refusal cause); CGP evidence-artifact / sealed-ledger binding; a committed/typed evidence surface; marker retirement; D_cap enforcement; DEFER/CRISIS; GCNL/GCML/CPVM. With this lane reconciliation moves from recorded-confession toward admissible warrant-backed proof material, opt-in and frame-stationary, with the recorded path intact.",bound_invariants=('GK-S-02', 'EH-S-02', 'PERSIST-S-01'))
ADR_65=_adr(id="AD-65",context="r138-r141 completed the typed-effect spine: EFFECT-S-02 made the v4 typed columns the AUTHORITATIVE trail-integrity surface for v>=4 (AD-61), the write path became uniformly column-primary for all v>=4 effect-bearing writes (AD-62/AD-63), and reconciliation gained opt-in warrant-backed verified-grade (AD-64). Throughout, the eight STRUCTURAL effect markers (effect_atomicity, phase, prepare_ref, compensate_ref, idempotency_key, compensation_idempotency_key, abort_reason, gate_admit_ref) were RETAINED as a derived parameters mirror -- the EFFECT-S-01 marker-layer surface, the v<4 compatibility layer, and substrate the no-erasure guard and runtime detectors read. AD-62/AD-63 named marker retirement as the structurally-reachable next frontier and explicitly DEFERRED it. Under the pre-v0.1.0 closure posture (exhaust the transitional mirror before the first release, while there are NO external compatibility obligations), the Governor authorized marker retirement. A design pass established feasibility as a scoped law amendment plus a body-version transition with schema STATIONARY (no columns added) and the no-erasure guard surviving as a bounded parameter-hygiene residual. An early-implementation halt surfaced that the verification-surface blast radius (gates identifying effect receipts by reading retired markers) and a runtime-substrate blast radius (kernel trail navigation reading retired markers) were larger than the design pass scoped; the Governor accepted both as in-scope for the authorized lane (Option A) -- correctness requirements of completing retirement, not expansion -- and authorized uniform v5 plus the full verification-surface migration.",decision="r142 RETIRES the eight structural effect markers from committed parameters for new receipts via UNIFORM UGK-BODY-v5, recorded as a LAW-LEG AMENDMENT. (1) UNIFORM v5: every new receipt is UGK-BODY-v5 -- one clean post-retirement body regime, not only effect-bearing receipts (pre-v0.1.0, no compatibility obligations). v5 commits the same field blocks as v4 (the typed effect columns remain committed and are the SOLE committed structural effect surface), but the eight structural effect markers are NO LONGER mirrored into committed parameters; any caller/legacy marker is STRIPPED at the resolver and never re-injected. parameters is RETAINED for caller payload, reconciliation provenance (reconciled/reconciled_by/reconciliation_evidence_ref/determination/reconciliation_grade), and the residual no-erasure hygiene region. (2) EFFECT-S-01 RE-SCOPED to marker-era / body-schema version < 5 -- THE LAW LEG (law = SHA-256(invariants.py)). The statement is EXPLICITLY scoped, NOT vacuous: v>=5 receipts are out of scope by construction, with EFFECT-S-02 the authoritative effect-trail-integrity surface for them. EFFECT-S-02 is UNCHANGED and remains authoritative for v>=4 INCLUDING v5. (3) CONSISTENCY BRIDGE re-scoped to v==4 (the dual-surface version): v5 (column-only) and v<4 (marker-only) are out of scope and never false-fail for the correct absence of the other surface. (4) v<5 BYTE-IDENTICAL / NON-RETROACTIVE: pre-existing v<5 receipts recompute byte-identically under r142 (proven: a v4 body recomputes identically r141==r142 at 44c11de7); v4 and v5 are DISTINCT commitment domains (distinct UGK-BODY tag), so neither is recomputed under the other regime. (5) RUNTIME TRAIL NAVIGATION MIGRATED -- PRIMARY SUBSTRATE, not verification scaffolding: the kernel runtime detectors (detect_orphan_prepares, detect_orphan_compensates, find_committed_forward in ugk/integrity/external_reversible.py and external_irreversible.py) and the reconcile-compensation comp_rec/fwd_key lookup in ugk/kernel.py now read the typed effect COLUMNS column-first with marker FALLBACK. Without this, uniform v5 would break runtime compensation, reconciliation, and orphan detection; v<4 navigation is preserved by the marker fallback. (6) RESIDUAL NO-ERASURE GUARD retained PARAMETER-BASED over the DISJOINT adversarial erasure keys {undone, reversed, erased, rolled_back} -- these are NOT structural effect markers; the no-physical-undo boundary is preserved, NO typed erasure column is added, and NO claim of pure column closure is made. (7) VERIFICATION-SURFACE MIGRATION: eleven conformance gates are migrated from marker-read identification to typed-column identification for live v5 receipts (effect_trail_integrity_gate, external_irreversible_pilot_gate, external_reversible_gate, broker_propagation_gate, effect_atomicity_class12_gate, effect_atomicity_declaration_gate, pure_migration_r105_gate, pure_migration_r108_gate, terminal_outcome_commit_gate, capability_evidence_commit_gate, typed_effect_surface_gate), with marker fallback retained ONLY for deliberate v<5 fixtures. The v4 dual-surface marker-equals-typed equivalence and the bridge divergence-catch are preserved on explicit SYNTHETIC v4 fixtures; version-ladder assumptions are updated so live writes are v5 while legacy v1/v2/v3/v4 verifier coverage is exercised through SYNTHETIC lower-version fixtures (uniform v5 forbids live lower-version writes). No proof is weakened -- each migrated gate still proves its property against the typed-column surface. (8) AMENDMENT BOOKKEEPING (declared separately): a1_conservativity_gate advances its current-law conservativity baseline 82c565f1 -> 7d34ef9d (the single IN-ugk current-law expectation pin); the OUT-OF-ugk GRBSA / current-law pin cascade advances the current-law expectation pins (tools/b1_conformance.py, b2_conformance.py, b3_conformance.py, b4a_conformance.py, b5a_conformance.py, tools/grbsa/verifier.py, tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py, tools/release/certify_release.py, tools/schema_hash_conformance.py, construction/cgproj/phase6_full_validation_gate.py); historical ADR prose, ledger lineage, and transition rationales are UNTOUCHED; no bulk replacement. FRAME: this is a LAW-LEG AMENDMENT -- LAW MOVES 82c565f1 -> 7d34ef9d (EFFECT-S-01 re-scoped in ugk/invariants.py); SCHEMA cbe140bf STATIONARY (no columns added -- retirement removes a parameters mirror, not a column); LEGEND db3c177d STATIONARY (no legend artifact changed); invariant REGISTRY 83 UNCHANGED (EFFECT-S-01 re-scoped, neither added nor removed); amendment ledger 18 -> 19 (record 19: ordinary, invariants_added=[], law leg, prior_law 82c565f1 -> successor_law 7d34ef9d, prior_amendment 4bd87514, fixture-Governor signed, amendment_hash bd0a1808); amendment_pin 4bd87514 -> bd0a1808; genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; BODY REGIME uniform UGK-BODY-v5. r141 -> r142 is an AMENDMENT-class continuity link (amendment_link = True, moved_legs = [law]). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO schema move; NO legend move; NO new/removed invariant; NO new refusal cause; NO terminal-outcome semantic change (TO-S-01 intact); NO weakening of the no-physical-undo boundary; NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS record; NO evidence-admission increment 2; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM; NO marker-retirement spillover beyond this lane.",alternatives=("Effect-bearing-only v5 (only effect receipts move to v5; non-effect receipts keep their versions): NOT TAKEN (Governor) -- uniform v5 is one clean post-retirement body regime before v0.1.0; effect-bearing-only would leave a mixed v4/v5 forward surface. The larger blast radius of uniform v5 (version-assertion gates) is the expected cost of exhausting the mirror cleanly.","Retain the marker mirror indefinitely (do not retire): NOT TAKEN -- the transitional mirror is exactly what the pre-v0.1.0 closure posture exists to burn down while there are no compatibility obligations; AD-62/AD-63 named retirement as the reachable frontier.","Add a typed erasure column so the no-erasure guard is column-based too: NOT TAKEN -- that is a schema move out of this law leg; the v5 phase domain has no erasure representation. The four erasure keys are disjoint adversarial parameter keys and the guard is retained as a bounded parameter-hygiene residual (halt-and-reclassify if a column is ever proven required).","File the runtime-detector migration under gate migration: REJECTED -- the detectors and the kernel reconcile lookup are RUNTIME substrate (compensation / reconciliation / orphan detection); they are declared as PRIMARY SUBSTRATE, not verification scaffolding.","Keep lower-version verifier coverage by writing live v1/v2/v3/v4 receipts: IMPOSSIBLE under uniform v5 -- the live store emits only v5; legacy-version coverage is therefore exercised through explicit synthetic lower-version fixtures, deliberately rather than assumed from a new write.","Reinterpret pre-existing v<5 receipts under the v5 regime: REJECTED -- v<5 receipts recompute byte-identically and stay under EFFECT-S-01 marker semantics; reinterpreting them would be dishonest and is forbidden (non-retroactive)."),consequences="The eight structural effect markers are RETIRED from committed parameters for all new receipts: under uniform UGK-BODY-v5 the typed effect columns are the SOLE committed structural effect surface, the parameters effect-marker mirror is gone, and the transitional dual-surface state opened at r134 is closed before v0.1.0. NOT CLAIMED: that pre-existing v<5 receipts changed (they recompute byte-identically and remain under EFFECT-S-01 marker semantics -- non-retroactive); that EFFECT-S-02 changed (unchanged; authoritative for v>=4 including v5); that the no-physical-undo boundary weakened (the no-erasure guard remains a bounded parameter-hygiene residual over {undone,reversed,erased,rolled_back}); that pure column closure was achieved (the erasure residual remains and is disclosed); that schema, legend, the invariant registry, or genesis moved; that any new refusal cause or terminal-outcome change was introduced (TO-S-01 intact). FRAME: LAW MOVED 82c565f1 -> 7d34ef9d via amendment record 19 (bd0a1808; ordinary; law leg; legend + schema stationary; invariants_added=[]); schema cbe140bf + legend db3c177d + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 83 UNCHANGED; ledger 18 -> 19; amendment_pin 4bd87514 -> bd0a1808; ADRs through AD-65 (63); gates 107 (all migrated in place; none added or removed); CODEX re-pinned (AD-65 added; invariants re-scoped; registry/legend unchanged). r141 -> r142 is an AMENDMENT-class continuity link (amendment_link = True, moved_legs = [law]) -- the first amendment after the r139-r141 behavioral run. B4 DECLARED-SURFACES (== ugk/ diff vs r141): MARKER-RETIREMENT SUBSTRATE ugk/storage/store.py + ugk/invariants.py + ugk/integrity/external_reversible.py + ugk/integrity/external_irreversible.py + ugk/kernel.py; MARKER-RETIREMENT VERIFICATION the eleven migrated gates; AMENDMENT BOOKKEEPING ugk/conformance/a1_conservativity_gate.py (in-ugk current-law expectation pin); RELEASE-RECORD ugk/amendment_ledger.json (the amendment record; classified substrate) + ugk/adr.py + ugk/codex/CODEX.md + ugk/codex/CODEX_HASH.txt. SEPARATELY-DECLARED OUT-OF-ugk GRBSA CURRENT-LAW PIN CASCADE (current-law expectation pins only; historical/synthetic refs untouched): tools/grbsa/verifier.py, tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py, tools/release/certify_release.py, tools/b1_conformance.py, tools/b2_conformance.py, tools/b3_conformance.py, tools/b4a_conformance.py, tools/b5a_conformance.py, tools/schema_hash_conformance.py, construction/cgproj/phase6_full_validation_gate.py. OUT-OF-ugk (declared, not B4-confined): RELEASE.txt, tools/grbsa/continuity_surfaces.json, and tools/grbsa/CONTINUITY_ATTESTATION.json (regen). 'Frame-stationary' does NOT apply here -- this is a frame-MOVING law-leg amendment (law leg only). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the v5 body regime, the markerless resolver, the re-scoped EFFECT-S-01 and bridge, the column-first runtime detectors and reconcile lookup, and the eleven migrated gates are CERTIFIED/GATED runtime + verification substrate. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: D_cap sufficiency/enforcement; the DEFER/CRISIS records; evidence-admission increment 2 (committed/typed evidence surface, law formalization of verified-grade); and the GCNL/GCML/CPVM program.",bound_invariants=("EFFECT-S-01","EFFECT-S-02","IEL-S-01"))
ADR_66=_adr(id="AD-66",context="AD-64 (r141) wired OPT-IN warrant-backed verified-grade reconciliation: the kernel verifies a cited DecisionWarrant's content-addressed integrity, resolvability, current-frame binding (law/legend), and non-empty constitutional basis, then records reconciliation_grade='verified'. The verified-grade design review (post-r142) found the claim was NOT yet self-contained: warrant_id was already a committed typed column, but the warrant BODY lived in the external WarrantStore and reconciliation_grade was a parameters-JSON marker -- re-verification required re-resolving a mutable external store, and (the marker softness r142 had just retired for effects) the grade itself was an un-typed parameters field. The Governor authorized Evidence-admission increment 2 schema-first/staged: Stage 1 a schema leg committing a typed, self-verifying surface; Stage 2 (DEFERRED) a law formalization over it. Fork A (uniform v6) was ruled over verified-only-v6 to keep one clean forward body regime after r142.",decision="r143 commits the TYPED VERIFIED-GRADE RECONCILIATION SURFACE as a SCHEMA-LEG amendment, UGK-BODY-v6 uniform forward. (1) TWO nullable columns: reconciliation_grade (TEXT; 'verified' on a verified terminal, NULL on recorded) and reconciliation_warrant_snapshot (TEXT; the verbatim canonical warrant body whose SHA-256 == the committed warrant_id). (2) UNIFORM v6 (fork A): every new receipt is UGK-BODY-v6 -- v6 commits the v5 field blocks (via version>=N) PLUS the typed reconciliation surface (version>=6 block); recorded terminals commit NULL grade/snapshot. (3) SELF-VERIFYING FROM RECEIPT ALONE: for grade=='verified' a verifier recomputes (i) snapshot present, (ii) SHA-256(snapshot)==warrant_id [integrity + correspondence], (iii) snapshot.law_hash/legend_hash == receipt frame [frame-binding], (iv) snapshot.constitutional_basis non-empty -- with NO WarrantStore resolution. The FULL canonical warrant body is committed (not a digest) precisely so the hash recompute binds the snapshot to the cited warrant_id; a partial digest could not and would secretly depend on the store. (4) PARAMETERS STRIPPED: grade+snapshot travel via markers into write(), which promotes them to the typed columns and STRIPS them from committed parameters (the typed columns are the sole committed surface -- the r142 resolver discipline). (5) NON-RETROACTIVE: the version-gated body blocks mean pre-existing v<6 receipts recompute BYTE-IDENTICALLY (the version>=6 block never fires for them; their tag is unchanged); v5 and v6 are distinct commitment domains. (6) RUNTIME UNCHANGED: no detector, aggregation, terminal-outcome, D_cap, or effect surface changes; the reconciliation columns are NON-AGGREGATING and orthogonal. (7) VERIFICATION SURFACE: external_irreversible_pilot_gate and external_reversible_gate migrated to read the TYPED grade and to PROVE the snapshot self-verifies (sha256==warrant_id, frame-bound, non-empty basis, NO store) and that recorded terminals carry NULL grade/snapshot; effect_trail_integrity_gate and typed_effect_surface_gate version assertions advanced v5->v6. (8) AMENDMENT BOOKKEEPING: amendment record 20 (ordinary, SCHEMA leg, law spine stationary 7d34ef9d, legend stationary, prior_schema cbe140bf -> successor_schema f343b870, prior_amendment bd0a1808); out-of-ugk current-SCHEMA expectation pins advanced (tools/release/certify_release.py, tools/b2_conformance.py, tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py); historical refs, ledger lineage, and synthetic frame placeholders (trace_vector_gate, terminal_outcome_gate) untouched. FRAME: SCHEMA-LEG amendment -- SCHEMA MOVES cbe140bf -> f343b870 (two nullable columns added); LAW 7d34ef9d STATIONARY; LEGEND db3c177d STATIONARY; invariant REGISTRY 83 UNCHANGED (NO law invariant in this lane -- Stage 2 deferred); ledger 19 -> 20; amendment_pin bd0a1808 -> 52f150fe; genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; BODY uniform UGK-BODY-v6. STAGE 1 ONLY -- schema surface; NO law invariant binding grade==verified to snapshot self-verification (that is Stage 2). NO MANDATE (verified remains opt-in); NO new refusal cause; recorded path semantically unchanged (NULL typed fields). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law/legend move; NO new/removed invariant; NO terminal-outcome change (TO-S-01 intact); verified-grade proves the ADMISSIBLE BASIS, NOT the external event (the kernel records, never witnesses); reconciliation_evidence_ref stays a RECORDED parameters string (AD-47/AD-60 confess-and-audit intact); NO D_cap enforcement; NO DEFER/CRISIS; NO evidence-admission Stage 2 law; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=("Law-first (formalize the verified-grade requirement before the typed surface): NOT TAKEN -- it would bind law to the soft parameters grade marker, the exact softness r142 retired for effects; schema-first lets Stage 2 bind a typed, self-contained surface (the proven AD-57->AD-61 sequence).","Verified-only v6 (only verified terminals move to v6): NOT TAKEN (fork A) -- preserves byte-identity for new recorded terminals but reintroduces forward-version heterogeneity immediately after r142 established uniform v5; pre-v0.1.0 prefers one clean forward regime.","Commit a basis digest / partial snapshot instead of the full warrant body: REJECTED -- only the full body lets the verifier recompute warrant_hash and bind the snapshot to the committed warrant_id; a digest only APPEARS self-contained while still implicitly depending on the store for correspondence.","Add a redundant reconciliation_warrant_hash column: REJECTED -- warrant_id already IS the warrant_hash; a second copy is redundant and a divergence risk; correspondence is proven by recompute.","Mandate verified-grade (forbid recorded): REJECTED for this lane -- a NEW refusal cause on the existing reconcile path; explicitly a separate, separately-authorized fork, not smuggled into Stage 1.","Promote reconciliation_evidence_ref into the verified/typed surface: REJECTED -- it would imply the recorded evidence_ref was verified, weakening AD-47/AD-60 confess-and-audit honesty; evidence_ref stays recorded."),consequences="Verified-grade reconciliation is now SELF-CONTAINED: a verifier confirms the admissible basis (warrant integrity + frame-binding + non-empty basis) from committed receipt state ALONE, with no WarrantStore dependence, because the receipt commits the full canonical warrant body whose SHA-256 is the already-committed warrant_id. The grade is a typed column, not a parameters marker. NOT CLAIMED: that verified-grade proves the external-world event (it proves the admissible basis; the kernel records, never witnesses); that pre-existing v<6 receipts changed (byte-identical, non-retroactive); that any law moved (law + legend stationary; NO new invariant; Stage 2 law formalization DEFERRED); that recorded reconciliation changed semantically (it gains NULL typed fields under the uniform v6 bump, no new refusal cause); that verified-grade became mandatory (still opt-in). FRAME: SCHEMA MOVED cbe140bf -> f343b870 via amendment record 20 (52f150fe; ordinary; schema leg; law+legend stationary; invariants_added=[]); law 7d34ef9d + legend db3c177d + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 83 UNCHANGED; ledger 19 -> 20; amendment_pin bd0a1808 -> 52f150fe; ADRs through AD-66 (64); gates 107 (4 migrated in place; none added/removed); CODEX re-pinned (AD-66 added; schema columns added). r142 -> r143 is a SCHEMA-class continuity link (amendment_link=True, moved_legs=[schema]). B4 declared-surface (== ugk/ diff vs r142): SUBSTRATE ugk/storage/store.py + ugk/kernel.py; VERIFICATION ugk/conformance/{external_irreversible_pilot_gate, external_reversible_gate, effect_trail_integrity_gate, typed_effect_surface_gate}.py; RELEASE-RECORD ugk/amendment_ledger.json + ugk/adr.py + ugk/codex/CODEX.md + ugk/codex/CODEX_HASH.txt. OUT-OF-ugk current-schema pin cascade (declared, not B4-confined): tools/release/certify_release.py, tools/b2_conformance.py, tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py; plus RELEASE.txt + continuity_surfaces.json + CONTINUITY_ATTESTATION.json (regen). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the v6 typed surface, the markerless promotion+strip, and the self-verifying snapshot are CERTIFIED runtime + verification substrate. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: Stage 2 law formalization (bind grade==verified to snapshot self-verification; optionally bind result==ADMIT); the mandate fork; D_cap sufficiency/enforcement; DEFER/CRISIS; GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",bound_invariants=("IEL-S-01","EFFECT-S-02"))
ADR_67=_adr(id="AD-67",context="r143 (AD-66) committed the typed verified-grade reconciliation surface (UGK-BODY-v6): reconciliation_grade and reconciliation_warrant_snapshot are typed committed columns, and a verified terminal is self-verifying from receipt state alone (sha256(snapshot)==warrant_id, frame-bound, non-empty basis) with NO WarrantStore resolution. AD-66 deliberately deferred the LAW formalization to Stage 2. The Evidence-admission increment 2 Stage 2 design pass (post-r143) confirmed schema-first/staged was correct and that the surface is now ready for a law leg over the typed, self-contained surface -- binding self-verification, opt-in, with NO new refusal cause and NO mandate. Grounding showed DecisionWarrant.create defaults result=RESULT_ADMIT (9001) and every existing verified-grade fixture cites an admit-verdict warrant, so requiring snapshot.result==ADMIT does NOT conflict with existing warrant semantics.",decision="r144 adds RECON-S-01, the law-bound verified-grade reconciliation self-containment invariant -- a LAW-LEG amendment ratifying the r143 typed surface. (1) RECON-S-01 binds: for a reconciling terminal committing reconciliation_grade=='verified', the receipt MUST self-verify from committed state ALONE (no WarrantStore) -- snapshot present; SHA-256(snapshot)==warrant_id; snapshot law_hash/legend_hash == receipt frame; constitutional_basis non-empty; and snapshot.result==ADMIT (9001). (2) RECEIPT-LOCAL ONLY: it re-derives nothing from the WarrantStore and does NOT re-evaluate the warrant's constitutional reasoning; it proves the ADMISSIBLE BASIS is committed, hash-intact, frame-bound, non-empty, and admit-verdicted -- NOT that the external event occurred (the kernel records, never witnesses). (3) result==ADMIT bound (design axis resolved): a verified reconciliation must cite an admit-verdict warrant; a refuse-verdict warrant is incoherent. Grounding confirmed no conflict (create() defaults ADMIT; all fixtures ADMIT), so the invariant was NOT weakened. (4) OPT-IN / NON-RETROACTIVE: RECON-S-01 governs ONLY receipts that commit reconciliation_grade=='verified' (v6+); recorded-grade reconciliation (verified=False) is OUT OF SCOPE and stays the AD-47/AD-60 confess-and-audit path with reconciliation_evidence_ref a recorded string. (5) NO NEW REFUSAL CAUSE / NO MANDATE: a committed verified-grade surface that does not self-verify is a corrupt receipt that fails closed at VERIFICATION (like EFFECT-S-02/TO-S-01), not a re-decision and not a decision-path refusal; verified-grade is NOT mandated (the mandate fork stays separate). (6) GATE: bound to external_irreversible_pilot_gate (extended at r143 with the self-verification checks; r144 adds the result==ADMIT clause), with external_reversible_gate proving the same for the reversible forward/compensation arcs. No new gate was structurally necessary. (7) AMENDMENT BOOKKEEPING: amendment record 21 (ordinary, LAW leg, invariants_added=['RECON-S-01'], prior_law 7d34ef9d -> successor_law 1e906a9c, legend+schema stationary, prior_amendment 52f150fe); the out-of-ugk current-law pin cascade advanced (a1_conservativity_gate [in-ugk], b1/b2/b3/b4a/b5a, grbsa/verifier, grbsa/g6, certify_release, schema_hash_conformance, cgproj/phase6); historical refs, ledger lineage untouched. FRAME: LAW-LEG amendment -- LAW MOVES 7d34ef9d -> 1e906a9c (RECON-S-01 added); SCHEMA f343b870 STATIONARY (the v6 surface already exists -- this lane adds NO column); LEGEND db3c177d STATIONARY; invariant REGISTRY 83 -> 84 (RECON-S-01 added); ledger 20 -> 21; amendment_pin 52f150fe -> ff74fbf1; genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; BODY regime UGK-BODY-v6 UNCHANGED. SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO schema/legend move; NO new column; NO new refusal cause; NO mandate; NO terminal-outcome change (TO-S-01 intact); recorded/confess-and-audit path unchanged; verified-grade proves admissible basis NOT the external event; NO D_cap work; NO DEFER/CRISIS; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=("Self-verification only, WITHOUT result==ADMIT: NOT TAKEN -- grounding showed no conflict (all warrants default ADMIT), and a verified reconciliation citing a refuse-verdict warrant is incoherent; binding result==ADMIT is a cheap, receipt-local integrity strengthening. (Had it conflicted, the lane was to HALT and report rather than weaken; it did not conflict.)","Bind basis SEMANTICS (re-derive the warrant's constitutional reasoning from the receipt): REJECTED -- exceeds what the snapshot proves and would invite WarrantStore/legend re-resolution; RECON-S-01 binds self-verification + admit-verdict ONLY.","Mandate verified-grade (forbid recorded): REJECTED for this lane -- a NEW refusal cause on the reconcile path; a separate, separately-authorized fork.","Add a schema column for the verified determination: UNNECESSARY -- the r143 v6 surface already commits grade+snapshot; Stage 2 is law-only.","A dedicated new RECON gate: UNNECESSARY -- the existing pilot/reversible gates already prove the property; RECON-S-01 binds the pilot gate (reversible corroborates)."),consequences="Verified-grade reconciliation is now LAW-BOUND: RECON-S-01 makes the r143 self-verifying surface a constitutional requirement -- a verified terminal that does not self-verify (missing/mismatched/stale-frame/empty-basis/non-admit snapshot) is a corrupt receipt that fails closed at verification. The increment-2 arc (typed surface at r143 -> law authority at r144) is complete, mirroring AD-57->AD-61 (typed effect columns -> EFFECT-S-02). NOT CLAIMED: that verified-grade proves the external event (admissible basis only; kernel records, never witnesses); that recorded reconciliation changed (out of scope; confess-and-audit intact; reconciliation_evidence_ref stays recorded); that verified-grade became mandatory (opt-in; mandate fork separate); that any new refusal cause was added (verification-time integrity, like EFFECT-S-02); that schema/legend moved or any column was added. FRAME: LAW MOVED 7d34ef9d -> 1e906a9c via amendment record 21 (ff74fbf1; ordinary; law leg; invariants_added=['RECON-S-01']); schema f343b870 + legend db3c177d + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 83 -> 84; ledger 20 -> 21; amendment_pin 52f150fe -> ff74fbf1; ADRs through AD-67 (65); gates 107 (pilot + reversible extended in place; none added/removed); CODEX re-pinned (AD-67 added; RECON-S-01 typed in sci_typing.json; invariants re-hashed). r143 -> r144 is a LAW-class continuity link (amendment_link=True, moved_legs=[law]). B4 declared-surface (== ugk/ diff vs r143): SUBSTRATE ugk/invariants.py; VERIFICATION ugk/conformance/external_irreversible_pilot_gate.py + ugk/conformance/external_reversible_gate.py + ugk/conformance/a1_conservativity_gate.py (in-ugk current-law expectation pin, amendment bookkeeping); RELEASE-RECORD ugk/amendment_ledger.json + ugk/adr.py + ugk/codex/CODEX.md + ugk/codex/CODEX_HASH.txt + ugk/codex/sci_typing.json. SEPARATELY-DECLARED OUT-OF-ugk current-law pin cascade: tools/b1_conformance.py, b2, b3, b4a, b5a, tools/grbsa/verifier.py, tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py, tools/release/certify_release.py, tools/schema_hash_conformance.py, construction/cgproj/phase6_full_validation_gate.py. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: RECON-S-01 is a CERTIFIED law invariant over the production v6 surface. Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: the mandate fork; D_cap sufficiency-policy (Lane 2a) then enforcement (Lane 2b, new refusal cause); DEFER continuation record (Lane 3, schema-first then TO-S-01 law); CRISIS/multi-root; GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",bound_invariants=("RECON-S-01","IEL-S-01","EFFECT-S-02"))
ADR_68=_adr(id="AD-68",context="D_cap (the CGP capability-evidence commitment, AD-52) is recorded + verified but explicitly NON-AGGREGATING: h_cap does NOT enter conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1 and does NOT affect ADMIT/REFUSE -- decision-authority was always declared 'a later, separately-authorized enforcement increment'. The CGP dispatcher already emits exactly one terminal verdict per in-scope capability from the EXISTING closed seven-state EvidenceArtifact vocabulary (PROVEN/FAIL/GAP/WAIVED/BY-CONSTRUCTION/NOT-RUN/ERROR; CTR-S-03 vocabulary), already keeps WAIVED authority-marked off the verdict census, already refuses to synthesize PROVEN from external/Navigator evidence, and already keeps BY-CONSTRUCTION distinct. The accepted Lane 2 architecture (design pass, then readiness pass against r144) split the work: 2a a frame-stationary sufficiency-POLICY artifact (this ADR); 2b a SEPARATE enforcement law lane (sibling refusal precondition + the insufficient-capability refusal cause). The readiness pass confirmed the policy is precise enough to encode directly over the existing vocabulary with no design gap.",decision="r145 adds the D_cap SUFFICIENCY-POLICY ARTIFACT (ugk/cgp/capability_sufficiency.py) -- a PURE, TOTAL, DECLARATIVE policy over the closed seven-verdict vocabulary, consumed by NO decision path. (1) is_evidence_sufficient(verdict): PROVEN is the ONLY evidence-sufficient verdict; every other verdict (and any unknown/out-of-vocabulary value) is False -- total + deterministic + default-deny. (2) classify(verdict, policy_entry): PROVEN -> SUFFICIENT; WAIVED -> WAIVER_DISPOSITION (an AUTHORITY disposition, NEVER evidence, reported distinctly so it can never read as PROVEN); BY-CONSTRUCTION -> BY_CONSTRUCTION_ADMITTED only if the policy entry names a backing internal proof, else BY_CONSTRUCTION_UNBACKED (it can NEVER launder into PROVEN/SUFFICIENT); FAIL/GAP/ERROR/NOT-RUN and any unknown -> FAIL_CLOSED. (3) CAPABILITY_SUFFICIENCY_POLICY declares the rules + external_evidence_sufficient=False (external/Navigator evidence remains non-sufficient absent a future evidence-admission path) + enforced_scopes=[] (EMPTY in 2a) + default_posture='fail-closed' + non_aggregating=True. (4) FRAME-STATIONARY / NO ENFORCEMENT: the artifact is consumed by NO decision path (no kernel/governance import), opens NO refusal path, adds NO new refusal cause; D_cap stays recorded+verified and OUTSIDE aggregate()/conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1/COMMITTED_SURFACES, exactly as before. (5) PROVING GATE: capability_sufficiency_policy_gate (registered; gates 107 -> 108) proves PROVEN-only sufficiency, WAIVED-not-evidence, BY-CONSTRUCTION-non-laundering (named-proof only, never PROVEN), GAP/ERROR/NOT-RUN/FAIL fail closed, unknown fails closed, external non-sufficient, D_cap non-aggregating, and that NO decision-path module consumes the policy. FRAME: BEHAVIORAL / FRAME-STATIONARY -- law 1e906a9c, schema f343b870, legend db3c177d, invariant REGISTRY 84, amendment ledger 21, amendment_pin ff74fbf1, genesis 5fe68bbc ALL UNMOVED; NO amendment record; gates 107 -> 108 (one proving gate added); ADRs 65 -> 66 (AD-68); CODEX re-pinned because AD-68 is added. 'Frame-stationary' means law/schema/legend/invariant-registry stationary; the ADR count and the derived CODEX projection move as release-record/documentation movement, NOT a constitutional frame-leg move; the gate-count move is a verification-surface census change (the live gate count is dynamic, not a pinned constant). r144 -> r145 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link=False, moved_legs=[]). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law/schema/legend/invariant move; NO new refusal cause; NO decision-path consumption; NO enforcement; NO D_cap aggregation; NO DEFER/CRISIS; NO marker retirement; NO evidence-admission increment 3; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM. Lane 2b (enforcement) is the SEPARATE next increment.",alternatives=("Encode the policy AND wire enforcement in one lane: REJECTED -- conflates the frame-stationary policy artifact with the new-refusal-cause law leg; the staged split keeps 2a free of any decision-path change and reserves the refusal cause for an explicitly authorized 2b.","Put the policy inside dispatch.py rather than a dedicated module: NOT TAKEN -- a dedicated capability_sufficiency module keeps the sufficiency criterion legible and separately gated without touching the dispatcher substrate.","Add a law invariant binding sufficiency now: REJECTED for 2a -- that IS enforcement (Lane 2b, DCAP-S-01); 2a binds nothing in law (frame-stationary).","Populate enforced_scopes now: REJECTED -- enumerated scopes are only meaningful once a decision path enforces them; in 2a they would be inert data that risks reading as ambient policy. enforced_scopes stays empty until 2b."),consequences="The D_cap sufficiency criterion is now an explicit, governed, proven artifact: PROVEN-only evidence sufficiency over the closed vocabulary, with WAIVED an authority disposition, BY-CONSTRUCTION non-laundering, and external evidence non-sufficient -- all total and deterministic and fail-closed. NOT CLAIMED: that any operation now refuses on insufficiency (the policy is consumed by NO decision path; no new refusal cause; ADMIT/REFUSE unchanged); that D_cap aggregates (it stays outside aggregate()/conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1/COMMITTED_SURFACES); that any frame leg moved (law/schema/legend/registry stationary). FRAME: BEHAVIORAL/FRAME-STATIONARY -- law 1e906a9c + schema f343b870 + legend db3c177d + registry 84 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; NO amendment; gates 107 -> 108; ADRs 65 -> 66 (AD-68); CODEX re-pinned. r144 -> r145 BEHAVIORAL link (amendment_link=False, moved_legs=[]). B4 declared-surface (== ugk/ diff vs r144): SUBSTRATE ugk/cgp/capability_sufficiency.py; VERIFICATION ugk/conformance/capability_sufficiency_policy_gate.py + ugk/conformance/run_gates_batch.py (roster registration) + ugk/adr.py; CODEX ugk/codex/CODEX.md + ugk/codex/CODEX_HASH.txt. OUT-OF-ugk (declared, not B4-confined): RELEASE.txt + continuity_surfaces.json + CONTINUITY_ATTESTATION.json (regen). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the policy artifact + gate are CERTIFIED; the policy is PRODUCTION sufficiency semantics but NON-ENFORCED (no decision path reads it). Lane 2b (enforcement: DCAP-S-01 + sibling precondition + insufficient-capability refusal cause + law leg) is the SEPARATE next increment, gated on its own authority decisions.",bound_invariants=("CGP-S-01","CGP-S-02","CGP-S-03"))
ADR_69=_adr(id="AD-69",context="r145 (AD-68, Lane 2a) shipped the D_cap sufficiency-POLICY artifact -- a pure/total/declarative policy over the closed seven-verdict vocabulary, consumed by NO decision path (frame-stationary, no enforcement, no refusal cause). The accepted Lane 2 architecture reserved ENFORCEMENT for a separate authorized increment with explicit authority decisions: a new refusal cause, sibling placement outside aggregate(), the aggregation boundary, a law-only determination model, jurisdiction fail-closed scoping, and the WAIVED/BY-CONSTRUCTION/external rules under enforcement. The Governor authorized Lane 2b with those eight decisions fixed.",decision="r146 wires D_cap ENFORCEMENT and binds it in law as DCAP-S-01 -- a LAW-LEG amendment over the r145 policy artifact. (1) SIBLING PRECONDITION OUTSIDE aggregate(): kernel.execute() gains a precondition (Step 4a) that runs AFTER gate()/aggregation admits and BEFORE the admit receipt; it consults ONLY the policy artifact + a supplied capability verdict census (the same census the committed h_cap binds) -- it does NOT read or modify aggregate()/conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1, and h_cap is NOT added to conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1 or COMMITTED_SURFACES (proven: a gate()=False op still refuses via the normal path, orthogonal to D_cap; the four-surface model is byte-unchanged). (2) ENUMERATED-ONLY, FAIL-CLOSED-WITHIN-SCOPE: enforcement fires ONLY for an explicitly enumerated (jurisdiction, op/capability-class) policy entry; UNENUMERATED scopes are a NO-OP (existing ADMIT/REFUSE unchanged); with the shipped empty enforced_scopes the invariant enforces NOTHING live (zero production behavior change). There is NO ambient permit and NO global default allow. (3) PROVEN-ONLY SUFFICIENCY + DISPOSITIONS: within an enumerated scope, admit requires PROVEN, OR a named-proof BY-CONSTRUCTION, OR a WAIVED verdict under an entry that permits a waiver (an AUTHORITY disposition kept DISTINCT from evidence sufficiency, never PROVEN); FAIL/GAP/ERROR/NOT-RUN, unbacked BY-CONSTRUCTION, unpermitted WAIVED, external/Navigator evidence, a missing verdict, and any unknown verdict all FAIL CLOSED -> REFUSE. (4) NEW REFUSAL CAUSE: insufficient-capability -- explicit and ATTRIBUTABLE (recorded in the gate_refuse receipt parameters with the capability_class + enforced jurisdiction). This is the ONE new refusal cause; no other decision semantics change. (5) LAW-ONLY DETERMINATION: the sufficiency decision is recomputable from the committed evidence census + the policy artifact; NO committed sufficiency-determination schema surface is added (schema STATIONARY) -- the determination is deterministic + auditable (h_cap binds the census), so the halt-on-non-determinism / halt-on-schema-need conditions did NOT fire. (6) GATE: capability_sufficiency_policy_gate EXTENDED IN PLACE (no new gate) with the enforce_decision pure matrix + a kernel round-trip proving enumerated+PROVEN admits, enumerated+insufficient refuses with insufficient-capability, unenumerated/live unchanged, aggregate() intact, and schema stationary. (7) AMENDMENT BOOKKEEPING: amendment record 22 (ordinary, LAW leg, invariants_added=['DCAP-S-01'], prior_law 1e906a9c -> successor_law 30befd23, legend+schema stationary, prior_amendment ff74fbf1); current-law pin cascade advanced (a1_conservativity_gate [in-ugk], b1/b2/b3/b4a/b5a, grbsa/verifier, grbsa/g6, certify_release, schema_hash_conformance, cgproj/phase6). FRAME: LAW-LEG amendment -- LAW MOVES 1e906a9c -> 30befd23 (DCAP-S-01 added); SCHEMA f343b870 STATIONARY (law-only determination; NO committed column); LEGEND db3c177d STATIONARY; invariant REGISTRY 84 -> 85; ledger 21 -> 22; amendment_pin ff74fbf1 -> a72419ec; genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; gates 108 UNCHANGED (gate extended in place); BODY regime UGK-BODY-v6 UNCHANGED. SCOPE-BOUNDED: ONE new refusal cause (insufficient-capability); NO schema/legend move; NO D_cap aggregation (outside aggregate()/conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1/COMMITTED_SURFACES); NO ambient default; existing behavior unchanged outside enumerated scopes; NO DEFER/CRISIS; NO evidence-admission increment 3; NO marker retirement; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",alternatives=("Fold D_cap into aggregate()/conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1: REJECTED (explicit authority decision) -- D_cap must stay a non-aggregating sibling; folding it would silently re-weight the four-surface conjunctive decision.","Commit a sufficiency-determination schema column: NOT TAKEN -- the determination is recomputable law-only from the committed census + policy (deterministic + auditable via h_cap); a column was the authorized fallback ONLY if recomputation proved non-deterministic/non-auditable, which it did not.","Enforce by a global/default-allow or ambient policy: REJECTED -- fail-closed, enumerated-only; no ambient permit; unenumerated scopes untouched.","Populate live enforced_scopes in this lane: NOT TAKEN -- the mechanism + law + refusal cause ship proven (via fixtures) with empty live scopes (zero behavior change); enumerating real scopes is a later declarative step needing no code change.","Mandate verified capability for all ops: REJECTED -- enforcement is opt-in per enumerated entry, not a blanket mandate.","Exempt _UNIVERSAL_OPS from enforceability: NOT TAKEN -- the explicit enumeration IS the scope control (default-empty enforces nothing); only _KERNEL_OPS (externally unreachable) are exempt."),consequences="D_cap sufficiency is now ENFORCEABLE as a law-bound, attributable, non-aggregating sibling precondition: for an enumerated scope, an aggregation-admitted operation refuses with insufficient-capability unless capability sufficiency (PROVEN, or a named-proof BY-CONSTRUCTION, or a permitted WAIVER kept distinct from evidence) holds. NOT CLAIMED: that any operation refuses today (shipped enforced_scopes is empty -> zero live enforcement; behavior unchanged); that D_cap aggregates (it stays outside aggregate()/conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1/COMMITTED_SURFACES); that a schema moved (law-only determination; schema/legend stationary); that external evidence can satisfy it (never PROVEN); that verified capability is mandated (opt-in, enumerated). FRAME: LAW MOVED 1e906a9c -> 30befd23 via amendment record 22 (a72419ec; ordinary; law leg; invariants_added=['DCAP-S-01']); schema f343b870 + legend db3c177d + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; registry 84 -> 85; ledger 21 -> 22; amendment_pin ff74fbf1 -> a72419ec; ADRs through AD-69 (67); gates 108 (capability_sufficiency_policy_gate extended in place); CODEX re-pinned (AD-69 added; DCAP-S-01 typed in sci_typing.json; invariants re-hashed). r145 -> r146 is a LAW-class continuity link (amendment_link=True, moved_legs=[law]). B4 declared-surface (== ugk/ diff vs r145): SUBSTRATE ugk/invariants.py + ugk/kernel.py + ugk/cgp/capability_sufficiency.py; VERIFICATION ugk/conformance/capability_sufficiency_policy_gate.py + ugk/conformance/a1_conservativity_gate.py (in-ugk current-law expectation pin); RELEASE-RECORD ugk/amendment_ledger.json + ugk/adr.py + ugk/codex/CODEX.md + ugk/codex/CODEX_HASH.txt + ugk/codex/sci_typing.json. SEPARATELY-DECLARED OUT-OF-ugk current-law pin cascade: tools/b1_conformance.py, b2, b3, b4a, b5a, tools/grbsa/verifier.py, tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py, tools/release/certify_release.py, tools/schema_hash_conformance.py, construction/cgproj/phase6_full_validation_gate.py. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: DCAP-S-01 + the enforcement precondition are CERTIFIED, PRODUCTION-grade but DORMANT (empty live enforced_scopes). Still DEFERRED, each separately authorized: populating live enforced_scopes; evidence-admission increment 3 (admitting external evidence); DEFER continuation record (Lane 3); CRISIS/multi-root; GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",bound_invariants=("DCAP-S-01","CGP-S-01","CGP-S-03"))
ADR_70=_adr(id="AD-70",context="r146 (AD-69, DCAP-S-01) landed D_cap ENFORCEMENT as a law-bound sibling precondition, but shipped DORMANT: the policy artifact's enforced_scopes was EMPTY, so the invariant enforced nothing live (the mechanism was proven only via gate fixtures). The Governor directed that enforcement be made NON-VACUOUS before v0.1.0 while preserving the r146 architecture, with a bounded first activation (no global ambient enforcement; explicit (jurisdiction/scope, op/capability-class) entries). Grounding established: the corpus has NO pre-existing op->required-capability map; the real governed execute()-ops are the namespace-mutation family + authority_model_set (the reconcile/compensate/external arcs are kernel METHODS, not execute ops, and effect-bearing is keyed by effect_atomicity not op name); capability classes are named by compound_capabilities (ATLAS-S-02); and -- decisively -- NO existing decision path supplies capability_verdicts to execute() yet, so enumerating any (jurisdiction, op) pair that the existing suite already drives would flip those calls to insufficient-capability and break conformance.",decision="r147 makes D_cap enforcement NON-VACUOUS by populating the policy artifact's enforced_scopes with the smallest principled activation table -- a FRAME-STATIONARY, policy-data + gate + ADR change (the enforcement MECHANISM and DCAP-S-01 are already law-bound at r146; activation moves no frame leg). (1) ACTIVATION TABLE: four explicit entries, each a real governed op + a real compound capability class, all scoped to the externally-consequential governance scope -- (external-consequential, authority_model_set, fail_closed_governance), (external-consequential, namespace_allocate, fail_closed_governance), (external-consequential, namespace_delegate, fail_closed_governance), (external-consequential, namespace_revoke, fail_closed_governance). These are governance-consequential AUTHORITY-mutating operations. (2) NON-BREAKING BY EXPLICIT SCOPE: the entries are scoped to the external-consequential jurisdiction, which NO existing decision path drives (existing traffic uses session/namespace/production/kernel); the SAME ops in any other scope are UNENUMERATED and UNCHANGED. There is NO global ambient enforcement and NO default allow. (3) NON-VACUOUS, PROVEN AT THE KERNEL: capability_sufficiency_policy_gate is EXTENDED IN PLACE with a LIVE-policy founded-kernel round-trip -- a real enumerated op (authority_model_set @ external-consequential) REFUSES with insufficient-capability when capability is insufficient or absent, ADMITS on PROVEN, and the same op in the unenumerated session scope ADMITS unchanged; WAIVED (entry does not permit) refuses and is never read as PROVEN; unbacked BY-CONSTRUCTION refuses (no laundering); external/non-PROVEN refuses. (4) PRESERVED r146 BOUNDARIES: D_cap stays a sibling precondition OUTSIDE aggregate(); NOT added to conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1 or COMMITTED_SURFACES; the refusal cause remains insufficient-capability; WAIVED stays authority (not evidence); BY-CONSTRUCTION requires a named proof; external evidence stays non-sufficient; unknown verdicts fail closed. (5) DETERMINATION unchanged: law-only recompute from the supplied verdict census + the policy table; NO schema move (the table is policy DATA in ugk/cgp/capability_sufficiency.py, not a committed surface). FRAME: BEHAVIORAL / FRAME-STATIONARY -- law 30befd23, schema f343b870, legend db3c177d, invariant REGISTRY 85, amendment ledger 22, amendment_pin a72419ec, genesis 5fe68bbc ALL UNMOVED; NO amendment record; gates 108 UNCHANGED (gate extended in place); ADRs 67 -> 68 (AD-70); CODEX re-pinned because AD-70 is added. 'Frame-stationary' means law/schema/legend/invariant-registry stationary; the ADR count + derived CODEX projection move as release-record/documentation movement. r146 -> r147 is a BEHAVIORAL continuity link (amendment_link=False, moved_legs=[]). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law/schema/legend/invariant move; NO global ambient default; NO new refusal cause; NO aggregation contact; NO schema surface; existing behavior unchanged outside the enumerated table; NO DEFER/CRISIS; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM; NO evidence-admission increment 3.",alternatives=("Enumerate ops under a jurisdiction the existing suite already drives (e.g. session/namespace): REJECTED -- no decision path supplies capability_verdicts yet, so this would flip live conformance calls to insufficient-capability and create unexplained refusals; it trips the halt condition. The external-consequential scope is the bounded, non-breaking activation.","Declare 'all operations require D_cap' / a global default: REJECTED (explicit Governor constraint) -- enforcement must be explicitly scoped; no ambient permit.","Activate read-only/diagnostic ops: NOT TAKEN -- only governance-consequential authority-mutating ops are activated; the corpus does not mark read-only ops as capability-requiring.","Commit a sufficiency-determination schema surface to bite real traffic now: REJECTED -- determination stays law-only; biting real traffic requires a separate verdict-source wiring (an evidence-admission-class increment), which is OUT OF SCOPE for this lane.","Author a brand-new op taxonomy: UNNECESSARY -- the existing governed-op set + compound_capabilities supply a defensible taxonomy."),consequences="D_cap enforcement is now NON-VACUOUS: the live policy enumerates four real governance-consequential scopes, and the kernel demonstrably refuses a real governed op (authority_model_set / namespace_*) under the external-consequential scope when capability is insufficient, while admitting on PROVEN. NOT CLAIMED: that existing traffic is now gated (the enumerated scope is one no existing path drives -- biting current session/namespace/production traffic awaits a separate capability-verdict-source wiring, deliberately out of scope); that D_cap aggregates (it stays outside aggregate()/conjunctive_refusal_monotone_v1/COMMITTED_SURFACES); that any frame leg moved (law/schema/legend/registry stationary); that WAIVED or BY-CONSTRUCTION can satisfy as evidence. FRAME: BEHAVIORAL/FRAME-STATIONARY -- law 30befd23 + schema f343b870 + legend db3c177d + registry 85 + ledger 22 + amendment_pin a72419ec + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; NO amendment; gates 108; ADRs 67 -> 68 (AD-70); CODEX re-pinned. r146 -> r147 BEHAVIORAL link (amendment_link=False, moved_legs=[]). B4 declared-surface (== ugk/ diff vs r146): SUBSTRATE ugk/cgp/capability_sufficiency.py (enforced_scopes data); VERIFICATION ugk/conformance/capability_sufficiency_policy_gate.py (live-activation round-trip) + ugk/adr.py; CODEX ugk/codex/CODEX.md + ugk/codex/CODEX_HASH.txt. OUT-OF-ugk (declared, not B4-confined): RELEASE.txt + continuity_surfaces.json + CONTINUITY_ATTESTATION.json (regen). SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the activation table is PRODUCTION policy data; enforcement is LIVE + non-vacuous for the enumerated scopes. Still DEFERRED (each separately authorized): wiring a capability-verdict SOURCE so enforcement bites existing-jurisdiction traffic; evidence-admission increment 3; DEFER/CRISIS; GCNL/GCML/CPVM.",bound_invariants=("DCAP-S-01","CGP-S-01","CGP-S-03"))
ADR_71=_adr(id="AD-71",context="TO-S-01 reserves DEFER and CRISIS as terminal outcomes that 'remain reserved and fail closed until their support records exist'. The accepted roadmap sequence reaches Lane 3 (DEFER continuation record) after evidence-admission Stage 2 (r144) and D_cap policy/enforcement/scope activation (r145-r147). Lane 3 is staged: a continuation-record SCHEMA surface first (this ADR), then the TO-S-01 extension / DEFER law semantics + emit/hold/resume/resolve/expire/refuse lifecycle (the SEPARATE r149 law leg). This mirrors the proven r134->r138 pattern (commit a typed surface schema-first, bind it in law second). The Governor accepted the column shape with tightenings: deterministic recomputable continuation_id; expiry as bounded {kind,value} committed-evidence JSON (no wall-clock); continuation_state as an append-only lifecycle marker over a closed domain; uniform UGK-BODY-v7 forward; schema-only (no DEFER emittability, no lifecycle execution beyond schema fixtures).",decision="r148 adds the continuation-record SURFACE as eight nullable, body-committed UGK-BODY-v7 columns on the receipt -- the support record TO-S-01 requires before DEFER can become a live outcome. (1) COLUMNS: continuation_id (deterministic SHA-256 over the deferred op payload {op,authority,parameters,jurisdiction} PLUS the creating-receipt anchor -- stable + recomputable, validated by recomputation at write), continuation_op, continuation_authority, continuation_parameters (canonical JSON), continuation_jurisdiction, continuation_expiry_basis (canonical {kind,value} JSON; kind in the CLOSED committed-evidence-only domain {receipt_height, explicit_trigger}; NO wall-clock), continuation_state (CLOSED append-only lifecycle marker domain {HELD,RESUMED,RESOLVED,EXPIRED,REFUSED}), continuation_model_id (continuation_record_model_v1). (2) UNIFORM v7 FORWARD: the live write body version moves 6 -> 7; v7 commits the v6 field blocks (by version>=N) PLUS the continuation surface under a distinct UGK-BODY-v7 tag. NON-RETROACTIVE: pre-existing v<7 receipts skip the v7 block + keep their tag, so they are BYTE-IDENTICAL (proven against the r147 code directly for v1/v2/v3/v4/v6). (3) NULL ON ORDINARY RECEIPTS: DEFER is NOT emittable in r148, so nothing populates the columns in live operation; they are NULL on every ordinary receipt and the surface is committed-but-unbound. The shape is proven via schema FIXTURES (a continuation record persists, verifies under h_body, and round-trips through the DB read path). (4) FAIL-CLOSED VALIDATION: _validate_continuation rejects (ValueError) any out-of-domain state, any non-{kind,value} or wall-clock or non-int-height expiry basis, any wrong model_id, and any non-recomputable continuation_id -- no silent coercion. (5) APPEND-ONLY: continuation_state is a phase MARKER, not mutable state; lifecycle transitions are LATER receipts (the r149 concern), never mutations of the creating record. (6) SCHEMA-ONLY: DEFER and CRISIS remain RESERVED / non-emittable (EMITTABLE_OUTCOMES unchanged = {ADMIT,REFUSE,STRUCTURAL_ERROR}); TO-S-01 is NOT extended; no resume/resolve/expire SEMANTICS are implemented (resume is NOT wired as a bypass -- it is not wired at all here); the law leg is the SEPARATE r149 increment. (7) GATE: continuation_record_surface_gate (gates 108 -> 109) proves non-retroactivity, uniform-v7 commit+verify, fixture persist/verify/round-trip, deterministic id, closed-domain fail-closed validation, and DEFER/CRISIS still reserved. BODY-VERSION CASCADE: the two uniform-body-version gates (effect_trail_integrity_gate, typed_effect_surface_gate) advance their v6 assertion to v7 (the r142 v5 / r143 v6 cascade analogue). FRAME: SCHEMA-LEG AMENDMENT -- schema MOVES f343b870 -> 8255332f via amendment record 23 (0f113982; ordinary; schema leg; prior_schema f343b870 -> successor_schema 8255332f); LAW 30befd23 STATIONARY (the law spine is the always-committed prior==successor anchor); LEGEND db3c177d STATIONARY; invariant REGISTRY 85 UNMOVED (no invariant added -- the surface is committed-but-unbound, the EFFECT-S-02-before / D_cap-before pattern); ledger 22 -> 23; amendment_pin a72419ec -> 0f113982; genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; gates 108 -> 109; ADRs 70 -> 71 (AD-71); CODEX re-pinned. SCHEMA-PIN CASCADE (out-of-ugk): store.py EXPECTED_SCHEMA_HASH (source, in-ugk) plus certify_release.py, tools/b2_conformance.py, tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py. r146 -> r147 was behavioral; r147 -> r148 is a SCHEMA-class continuity link (amendment_link=True, moved_legs=[schema]). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO law/legend move; NO invariant; NO DEFER emittability; NO TO-S-01 extension; NO lifecycle execution; NO resume/expire semantics; NO CRISIS; NO multi-root; NO D_cap verdict-source wiring; NO evidence-admission increment 3; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM. The continuation_ref / continuation_parent_ref question (distinguishing the creating DEFER receipt from later lifecycle receipts) did NOT require a new column in r148 (the anchor is folded into continuation_id); if r149 proves it necessary, that is a separate halt-and-report.",alternatives=("Add DEFER to EMITTABLE_OUTCOMES + extend TO-S-01 in r148: REJECTED -- that is the r149 law leg; r148 commits the support surface only, exactly as r134 committed the typed-effect columns before r138 bound them.","Store the continuation record in a new TABLE rather than receipt columns: NOT TAKEN -- body-committed receipt columns make the surface verification-grade (h_body) and append-only by construction, matching the corpus's effect-trail precedent; a side table would not be body-committed.","Allow a wall-clock or duration expiry basis: REJECTED -- expiry MUST be deterministic committed evidence; the closed kind domain is {receipt_height, explicit_trigger} only.","Make continuation_state mutable in place: REJECTED -- the record is append-only; lifecycle transitions are later receipts (r149).","Add a separate continuation_ref/parent_ref column now: NOT TAKEN -- the creating-receipt anchor is folded into the deterministic continuation_id; a distinct ref is deferred to r149 IF proven necessary (halt-and-report, per the accepted constraint).","Per-receipt mixed body versions: REJECTED -- uniform v7 forward, consistent with the r142/r143 uniform-body discipline; v<7 non-retroactive."),consequences="The support record TO-S-01 requires for DEFER now EXISTS and is committed + verification-grade: a deterministic, recomputable, closed-domain, append-only continuation surface with committed-evidence-only expiry. NOT CLAIMED: that DEFER is a live outcome (it remains reserved/non-emittable -- EMITTABLE_OUTCOMES unchanged); that any lifecycle (resume/resolve/expire/refuse) is implemented (it is not -- r149); that TO-S-01 moved (it did not); that any ordinary receipt carries continuation data (all NULL -- the surface is committed-but-unbound); that law or legend moved (stationary). FRAME: SCHEMA MOVED f343b870 -> 8255332f via amendment record 23 (0f113982; ordinary schema leg); law 30befd23 + legend db3c177d + registry 85 + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; ledger 22 -> 23; amendment_pin a72419ec -> 0f113982; gates 108 -> 109; ADRs 70 -> 71 (AD-71); CODEX re-pinned; uniform body version 6 -> 7. r147 -> r148 SCHEMA continuity link (amendment_link=True, moved_legs=[schema]). B4 declared-surface (== ugk/ diff vs r147): SUBSTRATE ugk/storage/store.py + ugk/amendment_ledger.json + ugk/adr.py; VERIFICATION ugk/conformance/continuation_record_surface_gate.py + ugk/conformance/run_gates_batch.py + ugk/conformance/effect_trail_integrity_gate.py + ugk/conformance/typed_effect_surface_gate.py; CODEX ugk/codex/CODEX.md + ugk/codex/CODEX_HASH.txt. OUT-OF-ugk schema-pin cascade: certify_release.py, tools/b2_conformance.py, tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the continuation SURFACE is PRODUCTION/certified but UNBOUND (DEFER reserved). r149 (DEFER law leg: EMITTABLE + TO-S-01 extension + emit/hold/resume/resolve/expire/refuse lifecycle, resume through execute(), deterministic committed-evidence expiry) is the SEPARATE next increment. CRISIS, multi-root, D_cap verdict-source wiring, evidence-admission increment 3, GCNL/GCML/CPVM remain unopened.",bound_invariants=("TO-S-01",))
ADR_72=_adr(id="AD-72",context="r148 (AD-71) committed the continuation-record SURFACE (eight nullable UGK-BODY-v7 columns) -- the support record TO-S-01 names -- but left DEFER RESERVED / non-emittable (committed-but-unbound), no lifecycle. The Governor authorized r149 as the DEFER law/lifecycle leg completing Lane 3: add DEFER to the emittable terminal-outcome path GATED on a valid HELD continuation; extend TO-S-01 ADDITIVELY for DEFER correspondence; implement emit/hold/resume/resolve/expire/refuse; resume MUST re-enter execute() with NO bypass; expiry MUST be deterministic committed-evidence (never wall-clock); CRISIS stays reserved; existing ADMIT/REFUSE/STRUCTURAL_ERROR unchanged.",decision="r149 makes DEFER LIVE and binds the continuation lifecycle in law (LAW LEG). (1) TO-S-01 EXTENDED ADDITIVELY: a receipt commits DEFER IFF it commits a valid HELD continuation (continuation_id recomputes from {op,authority,parameters,jurisdiction}+anchor; state=='HELD'; model_id=='continuation_record_model_v1'; expiry committed-evidence-only); a DEFER without a valid HELD continuation fails closed; gate_refuse->REFUSE / protocol_error->STRUCTURAL_ERROR / otherwise->ADMIT UNCHANGED; CRISIS reserved. (2) NEW INVARIANT DEFER-S-01 (gate defer_lifecycle_gate, DOMAIN_PHYSICS, depends_on TO-S-01+CTR-S-01): append-only HELD->{RESUMED,EXPIRED,REFUSED}, RESUMED->RESOLVED; every transition is a LATER receipt SHARING continuation_id, never a mutation; RESUME re-enters the kernel W/G/E execute() path on the captured op with NO bypass and its ordinary terminal IS the RESOLVE; EXPIRE is a PURE function of committed chain evidence (committed receipt height or explicit committed trigger), never wall-clock; invalid/malformed/already-terminal/expired continuations REFUSE cleanly; no new refusal cause; CRISIS out of scope. (3) EMIT GATING: store._assert_emittable(outcome, continuation) permits DEFER ONLY with a valid HELD continuation (else ReservedOutcomeError); CRISIS never; ADMIT/REFUSE/STRUCTURAL_ERROR unchanged (continuation defaults None). (4) KERNEL: defer_operation() emits DEFER + HELD continuation; resume_continuation() loads the HELD record, refuses cleanly (recording EXPIRED/REFUSED) if missing/terminal/expired, else re-invokes self.execute() on the captured op and records a RESOLVED transition; _continuation_marker() writes append-only transitions. (5) SURFACE SUFFICED -- SCHEMA STATIONARY: the lifecycle is representable on the r148 surface alone (every event shares the deterministic continuation_id with a distinct continuation_state); NO continuation_ref/parent_ref column was needed, so the r148 halt-and-report-on-schema did NOT fire. _validate_continuation recomputes+checks the id when an anchor is supplied (EMIT) and accepts the carried id when not (append-only TRANSITION linkage) -- a function-body refinement, NOT a column; schema stays 8255332f. (6) GATE: defer_lifecycle_gate (gates 109 -> 110) founds a kernel and proves the full pack. FRAME: LAW LEG -- law MOVED 30befd23 -> 5ecdf476 via amendment record 24 (85a50b5f; ordinary; law leg; invariants_added=['DEFER-S-01']); REGISTRY 85 -> 86; SCHEMA 8255332f STATIONARY (surface sufficed); LEGEND db3c177d STATIONARY; ledger 23 -> 24; amendment_pin 0f113982 -> 85a50b5f; genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; gates 109 -> 110; ADRs 71 -> 72 (AD-72); body version 7 UNCHANGED; CODEX re-pinned; DEFER-S-01 typed IR in sci_typing.json. CURRENT-LAW PIN CASCADE (full-64-hex 30befd23 -> 5ecdf476; historical short-prefix refs untouched): ugk/conformance/a1_conservativity_gate.py + tools/b1..b5a_conformance.py + tools/release/certify_release.py + tools/schema_hash_conformance.py + tools/grbsa/verifier.py + tools/grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py + construction/cgproj/phase6_full_validation_gate.py. r147 -> r148 was SCHEMA; r148 -> r149 is a LAW continuity link (amendment_link=True, moved_legs=[law]). SCOPE-BOUNDED: NO schema/legend move; CRISIS reserved; NO multi-root; NO D_cap verdict-source wiring; NO evidence-admission increment 3; NO GCNL/GCML/CPVM; resume strictly re-enters execute() (no bypass); expiry strictly committed-evidence.",alternatives=("Amend ONLY TO-S-01 (no DEFER-S-01): NOT TAKEN -- the lifecycle deserves its own typed invariant+gate; TO-S-01 carries correspondence, DEFER-S-01 carries lifecycle.","Add a continuation_ref/parent_ref column: REJECTED -- the deterministic continuation_id IS the linkage and continuation_state IS the phase; the r148 surface sufficed, schema stationary (halt-and-report did not fire).","Resume by replaying the stored decision rather than re-entering execute(): REJECTED -- that bypasses governance; resume MUST re-run the full W/G/E path under current law.","Wall-clock/duration expiry: REJECTED -- pure committed-evidence (receipt_height / explicit_trigger) only.","Make DEFER freely emittable (unconditional EMITTABLE_OUTCOMES): REJECTED -- DEFER emittable ONLY with a valid HELD continuation; unbacked DEFER fails closed.","Mutate the HELD record in place: REJECTED -- append-only; transitions are later receipts sharing continuation_id."),consequences="DEFER is now a LIVE governed terminal outcome: emittable only with a valid HELD continuation, resumable only by re-entering execute(), resolvable only to an ordinary ADMIT/REFUSE/STRUCTURAL_ERROR, expirable only by committed evidence, refusable cleanly when invalid/expired/terminal. Lane 3 COMPLETE. NOT CLAIMED: CRISIS live (reserved/fail-closed); resume bypasses governance (re-enters execute()); expiry consults wall-clock (committed-evidence only); schema/legend moved (stationary -- surface sufficed); ADMIT/REFUSE/STRUCTURAL_ERROR changed (unchanged). FRAME: law MOVED 30befd23 -> 5ecdf476 (amendment record 24, 85a50b5f, ordinary law leg, invariants_added=['DEFER-S-01']); registry 85 -> 86; schema 8255332f + legend db3c177d + genesis 5fe68bbc UNMOVED; ledger 23 -> 24; amendment_pin 0f113982 -> 85a50b5f; gates 109 -> 110; ADRs 71 -> 72 (AD-72); body version 7 unchanged; CODEX re-pinned. r148 -> r149 LAW continuity link (amendment_link=True, moved_legs=[law]). B4 declared-surface (== ugk/ diff vs r148): SUBSTRATE ugk/invariants.py + ugk/kernel.py + ugk/storage/store.py + ugk/adr.py + ugk/amendment_ledger.json + ugk/codex/sci_typing.json; VERIFICATION ugk/conformance/defer_lifecycle_gate.py + ugk/conformance/run_gates_batch.py; CODEX ugk/codex/CODEX.md + ugk/codex/CODEX_HASH.txt. OUT-OF-ugk current-law pin cascade: a1_conservativity_gate.py (in-ugk) + tools/b1..b5a + certify_release.py + schema_hash_conformance.py + grbsa/verifier.py + grbsa/g6_aggregate_validation_gate.py + cgproj/phase6_full_validation_gate.py. SCAFFOLD/STUB/PRODUCTION: the DEFER continuation lifecycle is PRODUCTION/certified and LIVE. CRISIS, multi-root, D_cap verdict-source wiring, evidence-admission increment 3, GCNL/GCML/CPVM remain unopened.",bound_invariants=("TO-S-01","DEFER-S-01"))
